LAURA: Are Vanessa 
and Merkin around?

00:20:49.000 --> 00:20:50.000
SAM: Mertin.

00:20:50.000 --> 00:20:51.000
LAURA: Mertin.

00:20:51.000 --> 00:20:52.760
SAM: Merkin is a different thing.

00:20:52.760 --> 00:20:54.480
MATT: (laughs) Yeah, 
a very different thing.

00:20:54.480 --> 00:20:57.168
I guess it depends on 
if he shaved recently.

00:20:58.250 --> 00:21:01.820
He looks toward the back room,
where her main office is, and he goes,

00:21:01.820 --> 00:21:03.860
"You're welcome to go ahead
and knock on the door

00:21:03.860 --> 00:21:05.570
"if you're feeling frisky."

00:21:05.570 --> 00:21:09.530
LAURA: Should we try to sell Vanessa
some of our dragon bits?

00:21:09.530 --> 00:21:11.000
TRAVIS: We should sell to a merchant?

00:21:11.000 --> 00:21:13.620
LAURA: Well, they tend to be in the--

00:21:13.620 --> 00:21:15.000
TALIESIN: They may have a buyer.

00:21:15.000 --> 00:21:16.000
LAURA and MARISHA: Yeah.

00:21:16.000 --> 00:21:17.500
TRAVIS: Love that you 
asked me that question.

00:21:17.500 --> 00:21:19.000
LAURA: I know, right?
What was I thinking?

00:21:19.000 --> 00:21:20.000
TRAVIS: I don't know. (laughs)

00:21:20.000 --> 00:21:21.500
TALIESIN: Keep a few of the scales, obviously.

00:21:21.500 --> 00:21:23.000
TRAVIS: We can tell 
what my place in the party is.

00:21:23.000 --> 00:21:24.500
LAURA: Of course. Grog, come with me.

00:21:24.500 --> 00:21:27.000
MARISHA: Oh, wait, keep the teeth.
Keep enough teeth for us.

00:21:27.000 --> 00:21:29.000
TALIESIN: We'll talk 
about the cold bag for now

00:21:29.000 --> 00:21:31.000
and see if there's anything else
they want to talk about.

00:21:31.000 --> 00:21:33.000
MARISHA: I have an idea for teeth.

00:21:33.000 --> 00:21:35.000
LAURA: Can I go find Vanessa?

00:21:35.000 --> 00:21:39.000
MATT: You go 
and knock on the door. (knocks)

00:21:39.000 --> 00:21:43.000
There's a brief pause. 
Knock again. (knocks)

00:21:43.000 --> 00:21:45.400
LAURA: (sing-song) Vanessa?
Vox Machina here-- oh, hi.

00:21:45.400 --> 00:21:48.000
MATT: The door (whoosh) swings open.
You have to duck backwards.

00:21:48.000 --> 00:21:51.000
It (thump) slams onto
the other side of the wall there,

00:21:51.000 --> 00:21:54.000
knocking a few knick-knacks
that were on a nearby shelf over.

00:21:54.000 --> 00:21:56.000
And Vanessa swings out.

00:21:56.000 --> 00:22:00.000
"What? Who's calling-- ah.
It has been some time.

00:22:00.000 --> 00:22:02.000
"How nice of you to come and visit.

00:22:02.000 --> 00:22:05.000
"May I... be of service to you?"

00:22:05.000 --> 00:22:07.000
LAURA: Oh, well, we were wondering
if we could be of service to you.

00:22:07.000 --> 00:22:11.410
We happen to have acquired
a great many dragon bits

00:22:11.410 --> 00:22:14.000
and we thought you might be in need of

00:22:14.000 --> 00:22:18.000
buying them for your sellers-- buyers.

00:22:18.000 --> 00:22:19.000
Your people.

00:22:19.000 --> 00:22:20.000
SAM: Fencing them.

00:22:20.000 --> 00:22:21.000
LAURA: Fence-- you know.

00:22:21.000 --> 00:22:22.000
TALIESIN: I really thought 
you'd be better at this.

00:22:22.000 --> 00:22:23.000
MATT: "There is no fencing."

00:22:23.000 --> 00:22:24.610
LAURA: No fencing, no. No, you're--

00:22:24.610 --> 00:22:26.000
MATT: "We run a legitimate business."

00:22:26.000 --> 00:22:27.000
LAURA: Legal buyers.

00:22:27.000 --> 00:22:29.000
MATT: "Good. 
As was I hoping to hear this.

00:22:29.000 --> 00:22:30.730
"Let me check my ledger."

00:22:30.730 --> 00:22:32.000
She turns around 
and goes back to her desk.

00:22:32.000 --> 00:22:35.040
Her tail flicks behind her as she steps 
over to her table, leans over.

00:22:35.040 --> 00:22:37.000
"(muttering) Ah!"

00:22:37.000 --> 00:22:40.290
Pulls one of the books. (blows)
Starts thumbing through it.

00:22:40.290 --> 00:22:45.000
(mutters) "What color dragon?"

00:22:45.000 --> 00:22:47.000
LAURA: Black.

00:22:47.000 --> 00:22:49.000
MATT: "Chromatic."

00:22:49.000 --> 00:22:51.290
SAM: (quietly) Ancient.

00:22:51.290 --> 00:22:53.740
LAURA: Ancient black dragon.

00:22:53.740 --> 00:22:58.000
MARISHA: Yeah, you might have heard 
about him. Umbrasyl... (chuckles)

00:23:00.650 --> 00:23:04.000
SAM: You're super salty today.

00:23:04.000 --> 00:23:06.710
TRAVIS: Tone it down two notches.

00:23:06.710 --> 00:23:10.936
MATT: "There is currently
no contract for a black dragon.

00:23:10.936 --> 00:23:17.064
"I do have one up for a bronze 
or perhaps a white, but..."

00:23:17.064 --> 00:23:19.460
LAURA: Oh, white! 
Do we have any white bits left?

00:23:19.460 --> 00:23:20.750
TRAVIS: Yeah.

00:23:20.750 --> 00:23:22.000
ASHLEY: We should have white 
from back in the day.

00:23:22.000 --> 00:23:24.000
LAURA: What, do you want scales or...

00:23:24.000 --> 00:23:27.000
MATT: "Specifically hide.
If there is white dragonhide?"

00:23:27.000 --> 00:23:28.000
TRAVIS: We have 60 pounds of--

00:23:28.000 --> 00:23:30.000
LAURA: That was the dragon
we killed for you before,

00:23:30.000 --> 00:23:31.190
because we didn't bring the--

00:23:31.190 --> 00:23:33.500
TALIESIN: No, it was before that one.

00:23:33.500 --> 00:23:36.240
LAURA: No, but we killed one with Zahra.
We killed a white dragon.

00:23:36.240 --> 00:23:38.110
MATT: "That was 
for a different contract.

00:23:38.110 --> 00:23:40.000
"This is for a newer one I came by."

00:23:40.000 --> 00:23:45.000
LAURA: We've killed four dragons?!
Four fucking dragons. Go us.

00:23:45.000 --> 00:23:46.460
MARISHA: Yes, we have. Yes.

00:23:46.460 --> 00:23:48.720
TRAVIS: Excuse us 
while we reminisce, apparently.

00:23:48.720 --> 00:23:50.770
MATT: "(deadpan) Yes, it is amazing.

00:23:50.770 --> 00:23:53.730
"The things you've accomplished.
I am blown away.

00:23:53.730 --> 00:23:57.080
"But in light of your capabilities,

00:23:57.080 --> 00:23:59.000
"I do not require anything black dragon.

00:23:59.000 --> 00:24:01.000
"However, if a contract comes in,
I know who to call.

00:24:01.000 --> 00:24:02.760
"Hold onto that,
because that would save you a trip."

00:24:02.760 --> 00:24:03.960
LAURA and MARISHA: All right.

00:24:03.960 --> 00:24:06.110
TALIESIN: We do have
some white scales left over, don't we?

00:24:06.110 --> 00:24:07.090
LAURA: Yes, I think so.

00:24:07.090 --> 00:24:09.610
TRAVIS: Yeah, we do.
We have 60 pounds of scales.

00:24:09.610 --> 00:24:11.000
MATT: "Is this hide or scales?"

00:24:11.000 --> 00:24:13.000
TRAVIS: Just scales. 
No hide, unfortunately.

00:24:13.000 --> 00:24:17.010
MATT: "Well, I could definitely do

00:24:17.010 --> 00:24:19.000
"a bit of business for you there.

00:24:19.000 --> 00:24:21.420
"The hide would fetch more, but--
60 pounds, you said?"

00:24:21.420 --> 00:24:24.000
TRAVIS: Yeah. 64, to be exact.

00:24:24.000 --> 00:24:27.020
LAURA: Of white dragon scales.
MATT: "64 of white dragon scales, okay."

00:24:27.020 --> 00:24:32.230
MATT: "I would be willing to continue
at least part of this contract

00:24:32.230 --> 00:24:39.000
"for this applicant for...
let's say... 4,500 gold pieces."

00:24:39.000 --> 00:24:43.000
LAURA: 5,000 gold pieces, 
I think is a fair price.

00:24:43.000 --> 00:24:45.000
MATT: "This is not about bartering.

00:24:45.000 --> 00:24:47.000
"This is what the contract says, my dear.

00:24:47.000 --> 00:24:50.000
"This is beyond 
a situation of conversation.

00:24:50.000 --> 00:24:53.000
"The paperwork is already signed."

00:24:53.000 --> 00:24:56.230
LAURA: What if we gave you 
less dragon scales?

00:24:56.230 --> 00:24:59.970
Would you have said less money?

00:24:59.970 --> 00:25:03.000
SAM: That's typically how it works.

00:25:03.000 --> 00:25:08.400
TALIESIN and MARISHA: (laugh)

00:25:08.400 --> 00:25:12.530
MATT: "Vex'ahlia. My dear.

00:25:12.530 --> 00:25:18.000
"My delightful little 
dragon-hating half-elf.

00:25:18.000 --> 00:25:20.000
"We've been good to you.

00:25:20.000 --> 00:25:22.070
"We've done many great things for you.
You've done great things for us.

00:25:22.070 --> 00:25:23.380
"This is a fantastic arrangement."

00:25:23.380 --> 00:25:26.000
(thud) She slams the book shut 
and sets it down.

00:25:26.000 --> 00:25:29.490
"But you have signed on with us,

00:25:29.490 --> 00:25:32.000
"and the deal is to fulfill contracts

00:25:32.000 --> 00:25:33.500
"as they are signed, as they are written,

00:25:33.500 --> 00:25:35.000
"as they are agreed upon by the person.

00:25:35.000 --> 00:25:36.500
"If you wish not to accept this contract,

00:25:36.500 --> 00:25:37.910
"we can just wait 
until somebody else picks it up

00:25:37.910 --> 00:25:39.490
"and goes out and fulfills this need

00:25:39.490 --> 00:25:42.000
"at the price 
at which they are requesting for this.

00:25:42.000 --> 00:25:44.000
"You're welcome to keep the scales."

00:25:44.000 --> 00:25:45.000
LAURA: I think we'll keep them

00:25:45.000 --> 00:25:47.000
and we'll sell them to other vendors, then.

00:25:47.000 --> 00:25:48.940
SAM: Haven't we had them for years?

00:25:48.940 --> 00:25:50.760
TALIESIN: I have a thing 
I'm thinking about.

00:25:50.760 --> 00:25:52.710
MATT: "See? Then it's easy 
for you to get rid of them.

00:25:52.710 --> 00:25:55.440
"If they've been a problem for you,
then I'm sure this would be easy."

00:25:55.440 --> 00:25:57.520
SAM: Where are we going to sell these?
The world's on fire!

00:25:57.520 --> 00:26:01.000
MARISHA: Okay, hang on. 
We know it's here.

00:26:01.000 --> 00:26:03.770
There aren't that many
white dragons walking around--

00:26:03.770 --> 00:26:05.230
TALIESIN: Certainly not anymore.

00:26:05.230 --> 00:26:08.000
MARISHA: Certainly not anymore.
We know it's here.

00:26:08.000 --> 00:26:11.000
Why don't we sleep on it. 
Think about it.

00:26:11.000 --> 00:26:13.000
If we're ever in a pinch for money,
we can come back.

00:26:13.000 --> 00:26:15.000
TRAVIS: Yeah. Sounds good.

00:26:15.000 --> 00:26:17.000
LAURA: Vanessa, you're so kind.

00:26:17.000 --> 00:26:18.720
TRAVIS: Besides, I've been working
on that dragon immunity potion.

00:26:18.720 --> 00:26:20.340
LAURA: I'm so sorry.

00:26:20.340 --> 00:26:22.660
MATT: "That is all right. Goodbye."

00:26:22.660 --> 00:26:24.770
And she shoos you out.

00:26:24.770 --> 00:26:27.000
MARISHA: Oh, wait, Vanessa. Wait.

00:26:27.000 --> 00:26:30.000
MATT: "Yes, other female half-elf?"

00:26:30.000 --> 00:26:33.420
MARISHA: That's me.
Where's the temple of the Raven Queen?

00:26:33.420 --> 00:26:37.000
MATT: "Oh, you're looking for 
the Duskmeadow. Raven's Crest."

00:26:37.000 --> 00:26:39.330
She points loosely outward,

00:26:39.330 --> 00:26:43.460
kind of southeast of the direction
of the Slayer's Take guildhall.

00:26:43.460 --> 00:26:46.000
"It's kind of hard to miss.
It's giant, black, ominous.

00:26:46.000 --> 00:26:48.890
"(chuckles) You'll see it."

00:26:48.890 --> 00:26:51.000
And she bops your nose
a little bit with her finger.

00:26:51.000 --> 00:26:53.000
"Now, please. Out of my office.
I have work to get done."

00:26:53.000 --> 00:26:54.770
LAURA: Thank you, Vanessa.
MARISHA: Okay, bye.

00:26:54.770 --> 00:26:56.000
SAM: Thank you. 
Kord's strength to you.

00:26:56.000 --> 00:26:58.220
MATT: "That does nothing for me."

00:26:58.220 --> 00:27:00.000
(slamming) Slams the door shut.

00:27:00.000 --> 00:27:01.000
LAURA: They were worth a lot more

00:27:01.000 --> 00:27:02.500
than what she was offering, 
just for the record.

00:27:02.500 --> 00:27:03.500
They are worth so much more.

00:27:03.500 --> 00:27:05.000
SAM: To whom? 
We haven't ever sold them

00:27:05.000 --> 00:27:07.000
or come across anyone 
who wanted them before.

00:27:07.000 --> 00:27:09.000
TALIESIN: This is no reason
to get rid of something for wholesale.

00:27:09.000 --> 00:27:10.516
LAURA: Well, we've not really tried.

00:27:10.516 --> 00:27:12.000
That doesn't mean 
we should just give them away.

00:27:12.000 --> 00:27:13.660
SAM: We also are almost full

00:27:13.660 --> 00:27:15.520
in our Bag of Holding, 
might I remind you,

00:27:15.520 --> 00:27:17.570
and 64 pounds
would free up quite some--

00:27:17.570 --> 00:27:19.000
LAURA: It's not 64 pounds.

00:27:19.000 --> 00:27:20.350
SAM: It's 64 pounds.
TRAVIS: It's 64.

00:27:20.350 --> 00:27:22.560
LAURA: Oh, it was 64 pounds. (groans)
MATT: (laughs)

00:27:22.560 --> 00:27:25.000
TRAVIS: Like I just told you.
ASHLEY: 64 pounds of scales.

00:27:25.000 --> 00:27:26.500
TRAVIS: But I could 
get rid of some other stuff.

00:27:26.500 --> 00:27:28.000
LAURA: Well, they're worth 
like 20,000 gold.

00:27:28.000 --> 00:27:29.500
SAM: To whom?

00:27:29.500 --> 00:27:31.000
LAURA: You don't care.

00:27:31.000 --> 00:27:36.000
TRAVIS: We also have 15 cases
of expensive-ass bottles of wine.

00:27:36.000 --> 00:27:40.000
TALIESIN: I'm just going 
to point out, since--

00:27:40.000 --> 00:27:42.000
LIAM, LAURA, AND MARISHA: 
We should drink those.

00:27:42.000 --> 00:27:43.500
TALIESIN: We should drink those, 
first of all.

00:27:43.500 --> 00:27:45.000
That is the only thing that makes sense.

00:27:45.000 --> 00:27:48.000
And I feel-- and I apologize
if it seems like I say this a lot,

00:27:48.000 --> 00:27:51.850
but I do have a castle
that we can drop things at,

00:27:51.850 --> 00:27:56.000
and we can leave them there,
perhaps get back to them at a later date.

00:27:56.000 --> 00:27:59.000
MARISHA: To be fair, Percy, 
you do a lot to remind us

00:27:59.000 --> 00:28:01.000
to try not to forget that you're titled.

00:28:01.000 --> 00:28:03.000
SAM: To be fair, have we ever

00:28:03.000 --> 00:28:06.000
gone back for something before, ever,

00:28:06.000 --> 00:28:07.500
in our entire travels?

00:28:07.500 --> 00:28:09.000
TALIESIN: Yes.
SAM: What?

00:28:09.000 --> 00:28:11.000
LIAM: We needn't stay here long.

00:28:11.000 --> 00:28:15.000
I don't think what I'm here for
is going to take too long.

00:28:15.000 --> 00:28:17.580
I hope.
We could go to Whitestone next.

00:28:17.580 --> 00:28:20.300
TALIESIN: Yes, drop everything off,

00:28:20.300 --> 00:28:24.000
create a little nest of what we need.

00:28:24.000 --> 00:28:26.000
LAURA: All right. 
Let's go find your queen.

00:28:26.000 --> 00:28:28.000
TRAVIS: (quietly) 
There is some gross shit in this bag.

00:28:28.000 --> 00:28:29.650
(laughter)

00:28:29.650 --> 00:28:31.000
TALIESIN: You found the troll dick, 
didn't you?

00:28:31.000 --> 00:28:32.000
LAURA: What do you have in there?

00:28:32.000 --> 00:28:33.000
TRAVIS: There are six basilisk eggs.

00:28:33.000 --> 00:28:35.000
LAURA: Are they still good?
MARISHA: Those are probably bad.

00:28:35.000 --> 00:28:37.000
TALIESIN: Oh, I bet those
have gone really bad.

00:28:37.000 --> 00:28:39.000
TRAVIS: I reach into the Bag of Holding
and think about one basilisk egg.

00:28:39.000 --> 00:28:41.000
LIAM: I'm sure they smell like Grog.

00:28:41.000 --> 00:28:42.000
MATT: You pull out a basilisk egg.

00:28:42.000 --> 00:28:44.000
TALIESIN: Do they just turn to stone?

00:28:44.000 --> 00:28:47.000
MATT: It's roughly that size.
It's a dull grayish-blue hint.

00:28:47.000 --> 00:28:49.000
LIAM: Sulfuric?
TRAVIS: Can I get the smell?

00:28:49.000 --> 00:28:53.020
MATT: It has a somewhat, very vague 
sulfurous scent on the outside of the egg.

00:28:53.020 --> 00:28:56.000
TRAVIS: I'll put it back in the bag.

00:28:56.000 --> 00:28:57.000
ASHLEY: Oh, Vanessa!

00:28:57.000 --> 00:28:58.000
LAURA: We could make stink-bombs with it.

00:28:58.000 --> 00:29:00.000
MARISHA AND TALIESIN: Ooh.
LIAM: Yeah, we could.

00:29:00.000 --> 00:29:01.500
MARISHA: Good idea. I like that.

00:29:01.500 --> 00:29:03.000
TRAVIS: All right. So what's next?

00:29:03.000 --> 00:29:05.000
LAURA: We go see the Raven Queen.

00:29:05.000 --> 00:29:08.000
You go see the Raven Queen
and we wait outside.

00:29:08.000 --> 00:29:09.500
LIAM: I didn't say anything.
LAURA: Uselessly.

00:29:09.500 --> 00:29:11.000
LIAM: I didn't say anything!

00:29:11.000 --> 00:29:13.000
TALIESIN: Is it in the direction 
where I have to go?

00:29:13.000 --> 00:29:15.000
MATT: Where are you heading?

00:29:15.000 --> 00:29:17.500
TALIESIN: I need to resupply everything.

00:29:17.500 --> 00:29:20.000
MATT: That's the opposite direction.
TALIESIN: Okay.

00:29:20.000 --> 00:29:21.000
MATT: You're heading 
to the Braving Grounds.

00:29:21.000 --> 00:29:22.000
They're heading to the Duskmeadow.

00:29:22.000 --> 00:29:24.000
TRAVIS: Oh! I like the sound of that. 
I'll go with you.

00:29:24.000 --> 00:29:25.000
TALIESIN: Yes, you will.

00:29:25.000 --> 00:29:26.000
SAM: I'll come with you, as well.

00:29:26.000 --> 00:29:27.220
TRAVIS: Yeah, three! Who else?

00:29:27.220 --> 00:29:30.000
Any other takers
while Vax goes and gets a tattoo?

00:29:30.000 --> 00:29:32.000
MATT: (laughs)

00:29:32.000 --> 00:29:33.550
LIAM: Another tattoo?

00:29:33.550 --> 00:29:36.000
TRAVIS: Well, I thought that--
is that not what you're doing?

00:29:36.000 --> 00:29:38.000
LAURA: That's what he's doing, Grog.
LIAM: It is. I'm getting a tattoo.

00:29:38.000 --> 00:29:39.500
ASHLEY: Close. Something like that.

00:29:39.500 --> 00:29:41.000
LIAM: It will say "Phillip the Brave".

00:29:41.000 --> 00:29:43.000
TRAVIS: (gasps)
LIAM: Across the small of my back.

00:29:43.000 --> 00:29:47.000
TRAVIS: Phillip. Full name, Phillip.

00:29:47.000 --> 00:29:49.000
TALIESIN: This is out of--

00:29:49.000 --> 00:29:51.000
I don't know if this is going to be
any help or anything,

00:29:51.000 --> 00:29:53.000
by the way, Vax, but just in case.

00:29:53.000 --> 00:29:55.000
I'm going to reach in

00:29:55.000 --> 00:29:59.000
and pull out the mask 
and hand it to Vax.

00:30:00.180 --> 00:30:02.230
Just in case.

00:30:03.170 --> 00:30:05.816
LIAM: (slowly) I don't know.

00:30:06.720 --> 00:30:08.000
Thank you.

00:30:08.000 --> 00:30:09.350
MARISHA: Percy?

00:30:09.350 --> 00:30:10.680
TALIESIN: Yes?

00:30:10.680 --> 00:30:13.000
MARISHA: Do you still have 
that raven's skull I gave you?

00:30:13.000 --> 00:30:15.000
TALIESIN: I do. We'll talk about that.
MARISHA: All right.

00:30:15.000 --> 00:30:19.780
TALIESIN: But I've found in moments

00:30:19.780 --> 00:30:22.000
when I was feeling less than brave

00:30:22.000 --> 00:30:26.000
that pretending to be
somebody else on occasion,

00:30:26.000 --> 00:30:31.000
even afterwards, can be helpful.

00:30:31.000 --> 00:30:33.000
LIAM: Is there anything left 
inside of this?

00:30:33.000 --> 00:30:35.500
TALIESIN: Just some spit.

00:30:35.500 --> 00:30:36.750
LIAM: That's wonderful.
LAURA: (laughs)

00:30:36.750 --> 00:30:39.000
TALIESIN: And something that smells nice 
in the front that will help.

00:30:39.000 --> 00:30:42.590
It helps cleanse the air.

00:30:42.590 --> 00:30:44.570
LIAM: All right, Percival.

00:30:45.590 --> 00:30:49.870
TALIESIN: I don't know why. 
I'm feeling... what would be the word?

00:30:49.870 --> 00:30:51.510
Superstitious.

00:30:52.290 --> 00:30:54.250
MARISHA: Oh, I was 
going to say "giving."

00:30:55.720 --> 00:30:59.380
LAURA: She's ornery today.
MARISHA: Sorry. Angry.

00:30:59.380 --> 00:31:02.310
TALIESIN: You know, 
I kind of like it.

00:31:02.310 --> 00:31:07.000
LIAM: You know. Enough chit-chat.
Let's get this shit done.

00:31:07.000 --> 00:31:08.000
MATT AND TRAVIS: All right.

00:31:08.000 --> 00:31:10.000
MATT: So you three 
are going to the Braving Grounds.

00:31:10.000 --> 00:31:12.000
You four are going to the Duskmeadow.

00:31:12.000 --> 00:31:13.000
LAURA: We are.

00:31:13.000 --> 00:31:16.000
MATT: Okay. All right, so.

00:31:16.000 --> 00:31:19.750
You three are making your way
towards the Braving Grounds.

00:31:19.750 --> 00:31:21.810
Following suit after Percival,

00:31:21.810 --> 00:31:25.000
you make your way up
not quite to the Trial Forge,

00:31:25.000 --> 00:31:28.000
which is where you had 
your last discussion

00:31:28.000 --> 00:31:31.000
and brief showdown 
with Earthbreaker Groon.

00:31:31.000 --> 00:31:34.160
Still seeing the large statue of Kord

00:31:34.160 --> 00:31:36.410
looming over the entirety of the realm.

00:31:36.410 --> 00:31:40.000
You can still see the large columns
of dark smoke and soot

00:31:40.000 --> 00:31:45.000
coming out of the various forges,
the various mining encampments,

00:31:45.000 --> 00:31:46.320
and a lot of the folks there

00:31:46.320 --> 00:31:50.000
that are working on different pieces 
of iron and metal.

00:31:50.000 --> 00:31:56.000
You, I assume, make your way
to a very familiar abode. (laughs)

00:31:56.000 --> 00:31:59.000
TALIESIN: Of all the options of the world
that you've given me...

00:31:59.000 --> 00:32:02.000
MATT: All right.

00:32:02.000 --> 00:32:05.000
(laughter)

00:32:05.000 --> 00:32:07.000
TALIESIN: This is really your fault 
as much as it's mine.

00:32:07.000 --> 00:32:13.000
MATT: You come up to the outside 
of a familiar hovel.

00:32:13.000 --> 00:32:15.100
Previously damaged,
missing part of its roof.

00:32:15.100 --> 00:32:17.000
The roof is mostly repaired.

00:32:17.000 --> 00:32:20.660
You actually see two individuals 
are over the top of it,

00:32:20.660 --> 00:32:24.000
hammering pieces of wood into it.

00:32:24.000 --> 00:32:26.720
Not a very fine job, 
but definitely enough patchwork

00:32:26.720 --> 00:32:29.530
to keep the rain and snow 
from pouring in.

00:32:29.530 --> 00:32:32.500
The door is partially open 
as you approach.

00:32:34.000 --> 00:32:38.000
TALIESIN: (sighs heavily)

00:32:38.000 --> 00:32:40.000
SAM: You might be blown up 
if you go in there.

00:32:40.000 --> 00:32:41.000
TALIESIN: I know.

00:32:41.000 --> 00:32:43.000
TRAVIS: Should we wait outside?

00:32:43.000 --> 00:32:47.000
TALIESIN: Let's just all be ginger.

00:32:47.000 --> 00:32:52.000
(louder) Hello? Victor, are you home?

00:32:52.000 --> 00:32:55.000
It's Percy.

00:32:55.000 --> 00:32:58.000
MATT: Silence.

00:32:58.000 --> 00:33:00.000
SAM: Want me to go in 
and investigate?

00:33:00.000 --> 00:33:05.000
TALIESIN: Hold on. 
(louder) Hello, you up there? Hello?

00:33:05.000 --> 00:33:06.590
MATT: (hammering noises)

00:33:06.590 --> 00:33:08.000
"What?"

00:33:08.000 --> 00:33:13.000
TALIESIN: Where is the owner 
of this domicile?

00:33:13.000 --> 00:33:15.000
MATT: "I don't know. 
I haven't seen him."

00:33:15.000 --> 00:33:17.000
TALIESIN: How long has he been gone for?

00:33:17.000 --> 00:33:21.000
MATT: "(mutters) 
(louder) Couple of hours."

00:33:21.000 --> 00:33:23.740
SAM: Oh, good. Not dead, then.
TRAVIS: He's dead.

00:33:23.740 --> 00:33:27.000
(laughter)

00:33:27.000 --> 00:33:30.000
TALIESIN: Do you have any idea
where he's been off to?

00:33:30.000 --> 00:33:32.000
MATT: "I haven't seen him leave."

00:33:32.000 --> 00:33:34.000
(hammering noises)

00:33:34.000 --> 00:33:35.800
TALIESIN: Well, I'm going to pop in
and check really quickly,

00:33:35.800 --> 00:33:36.860
just letting you know.

00:33:36.860 --> 00:33:38.260
MATT: "Your funeral."

00:33:38.260 --> 00:33:41.000
(hammering noises)

00:33:41.000 --> 00:33:44.920
TALIESIN: I gingerly open the door.
Can I check for traps?

00:33:44.920 --> 00:33:46.000
TRAVIS: Attaboy.

00:33:46.000 --> 00:33:48.000
MATT: You may. 
Make an investigation check.

00:33:48.000 --> 00:33:51.000
TRAVIS: Yeah, we're standing right here.

00:33:51.000 --> 00:33:55.000
TALIESIN: Oh, yay, that's not that bad.

00:33:55.000 --> 00:34:00.000
Investigation? I never use that.
11. No, 12. 12.

00:34:00.000 --> 00:34:01.360
MATT: 12, okay.

00:34:01.360 --> 00:34:05.600
(creak) You move the door open
and kind of search the ground

00:34:05.600 --> 00:34:11.000
and the area before it
and the actual frame of the door itself.

00:34:11.000 --> 00:34:12.060
No traps.

00:34:12.060 --> 00:34:13.170
TALIESIN: All right.

00:34:13.170 --> 00:34:16.000
MATT: Glancing inside, though,
you can see a little bit of light.

00:34:16.000 --> 00:34:17.500
It looks like there's
a hooded lantern across the way

00:34:17.500 --> 00:34:19.000
and just a little bit of light is flickering

00:34:19.000 --> 00:34:22.000
and it's kind of 
going against the wall nearest to you,

00:34:22.000 --> 00:34:23.389
to your right, as you enter.

00:34:23.389 --> 00:34:28.000
The same familiar smell of fresh earth,

00:34:28.000 --> 00:34:32.000
really, really, really dry dust

00:34:32.000 --> 00:34:39.000
and a very familiar smell
of explosive black powder material.

00:34:39.000 --> 00:34:41.000
TALIESIN: Oh, dear.

00:34:41.000 --> 00:34:43.000
SAM: Is Victor in there?

00:34:43.000 --> 00:34:45.000
TALIESIN: No, I don't see anybody in here.

00:34:45.000 --> 00:34:46.000
SAM: Well, should we just

00:34:46.000 --> 00:34:48.659
purchase what you need
via the honor system

00:34:48.659 --> 00:34:50.210
and leave some coin behind?

00:34:50.210 --> 00:34:54.770
TALIESIN: He's not necessarily
always a believer in coin.

00:34:54.770 --> 00:34:56.750
Sometimes he just wants some trade.

00:34:56.750 --> 00:35:00.000
Also, I need to talk to him 
about some personal issues.

00:35:00.000 --> 00:35:03.440
MATT: (thud) You see off to the side,

00:35:03.440 --> 00:35:05.260
what you didn't initially notice 
as you entered,

00:35:05.260 --> 00:35:09.020
what appears to be a wooden trapdoor
in the far corner that (thud).

00:35:09.020 --> 00:35:11.030
TALIESIN: Oh, sweet gods of Pelor!

00:35:11.030 --> 00:35:14.430
MATT: (repeated thuds)

00:35:14.430 --> 00:35:17.000
And you notice 
that apparently something--

00:35:17.000 --> 00:35:19.000
a large sack 
of some heavy material

00:35:19.000 --> 00:35:21.560
has rolled off a nearby table

00:35:21.560 --> 00:35:24.000
and is now currently 
holding the door down.

00:35:24.000 --> 00:35:25.000
TALIESIN: Okay.

00:35:25.000 --> 00:35:27.000
MATT: You hear a muffled,
"I'm inside!"

00:35:27.000 --> 00:35:28.500
TALIESIN: I'm going to go 
try and lift it.

00:35:28.500 --> 00:35:30.000
TALIESIN: (grunts)

00:35:30.000 --> 00:35:33.000
MATT: You lift it up, 
set it off to the side. (boosh)

00:35:33.000 --> 00:35:39.600
"(coughing) What's going on?
You trying to kill me?"

00:35:39.600 --> 00:35:45.000
TALIESIN: (laughs) No! Hello, Victor.
I was just to give you money.

00:35:45.000 --> 00:35:47.000
You were stuck--
you had gotten stuck down--

00:35:47.000 --> 00:35:48.280
what is down there?

00:35:48.280 --> 00:35:50.710
MATT: "This is my mining building."

00:35:50.710 --> 00:35:52.590
SAM: Your mine?

00:35:52.590 --> 00:35:54.000
TALIESIN: His Mayan building.

00:35:54.000 --> 00:35:56.370
Can you not 
understand simple English?

00:35:56.370 --> 00:35:58.478
MATT: "Don't put things 
on top of the door.

00:35:58.478 --> 00:36:00.328
"It makes it hard to get out!"

00:36:00.328 --> 00:36:02.260
SAM: (whispering) 
Something's happened to him.

00:36:02.260 --> 00:36:03.850
TALIESIN: Are you all right?

00:36:03.850 --> 00:36:06.000
MATT: "I'm okay!"

00:36:06.000 --> 00:36:08.000
TALIESIN: Are you sure?

00:36:08.000 --> 00:36:10.000
MATT: "No, I've been locked 
down here for hours!"

00:36:10.000 --> 00:36:12.000
ASHLEY: Oh no.

00:36:12.000 --> 00:36:15.420
TALIESIN: Grog, Scanlan?

00:36:15.420 --> 00:36:19.000
(stutters) Come on in, he's fine.

00:36:19.000 --> 00:36:20.000
MATT: "Help me out!"

00:36:20.000 --> 00:36:21.000
MATT: He raises his hands up.

00:36:21.000 --> 00:36:24.930
You can see now,
where once was two, now is none.

00:36:24.930 --> 00:36:29.000
(sounds of dismay)

00:36:29.000 --> 00:36:30.630
MATT: (grunts)

00:36:30.630 --> 00:36:33.000
LIAM: You have to build him a hand.
TALIESIN: I know.

00:36:33.000 --> 00:36:36.000
MATT: (grunts)
"I can't wait all day, here!"

00:36:36.000 --> 00:36:38.000
SAM: Grog, can you get him out,
can you lift him up?

00:36:38.000 --> 00:36:42.000
TALIESIN: Grog, can you lift the poor--
TRAVIS: All right, yeah.

00:36:42.000 --> 00:36:44.270
TRAVIS: I grab the stump
and I pick him up into the air.

00:36:44.270 --> 00:36:46.000
MATT: (screams)

00:36:46.000 --> 00:36:48.580
TRAVIS: I shake him a little bit.

00:36:48.580 --> 00:36:50.730
TALIESIN: I need him mostly intact.

00:36:50.730 --> 00:36:52.930
TRAVIS: Oh. So on the ground?

00:36:52.930 --> 00:36:54.800
TALIESIN: Treat him slightly better
than you would treat

00:36:54.800 --> 00:36:56.333
a member of your own family.

00:36:56.333 --> 00:36:58.016
MATT: "Don't shake me too hard."

00:36:58.016 --> 00:37:00.000
TALIESIN: More than slightly better. 
Much better.

00:37:00.000 --> 00:37:02.000
LAURA: Oh, don't shake him too hard--
I'm not there.

00:37:02.000 --> 00:37:04.053
TRAVIS: Oh. Gas.

00:37:04.053 --> 00:37:05.293
MATT: "Sure."

00:37:05.293 --> 00:37:07.000
TRAVIS: I put him gently 
back on the ground.

00:37:07.000 --> 00:37:08.000
MATT: "Thank you."

00:37:08.000 --> 00:37:09.580
He pats you on the head 
with his nub.

00:37:09.580 --> 00:37:10.700
SAM: Ugh.

00:37:10.700 --> 00:37:13.070
MATT: Goes over. You can see 
he's kind of bandaged.

00:37:13.070 --> 00:37:17.030
He goes over and then pulls the ladder up
that he didn't use, closes the--

00:37:17.030 --> 00:37:21.000
TRAVIS: (laughing) The ladder 
he didn't use?

00:37:21.000 --> 00:37:25.220
MATT: "Okay. So. What do you want?"

00:37:25.220 --> 00:37:27.200
TALIESIN: Well, I was hoping to buy

00:37:27.200 --> 00:37:30.650
a little bit more black powder 
from you, if possible,

00:37:30.650 --> 00:37:33.000
and I'm curious if you had 
anything else for sale,

00:37:33.000 --> 00:37:35.830
and I wanted to ask you 
a couple of questions,

00:37:35.830 --> 00:37:38.000
just about other customers again.

00:37:38.000 --> 00:37:40.560
MATT: "That's a lot."
TALIESIN: I know.

00:37:40.560 --> 00:37:42.620
MATT: "I have powder."

00:37:42.620 --> 00:37:43.730
TALIESIN: You do.

00:37:43.730 --> 00:37:47.000
MATT: "I can sell you more powder.
Question one: yes. How much?"

00:37:47.000 --> 00:37:49.000
TALIESIN: One question?

00:37:49.000 --> 00:37:50.000
LIAM: First question.

00:37:50.000 --> 00:37:52.000
TALIESIN: First question.

00:37:52.000 --> 00:37:56.000
Has a one-armed lady, 
a one-handed lady,

00:37:56.000 --> 00:37:59.000
a doctor come by to purchase--

00:37:59.000 --> 00:38:02.405
MATT: "Not a lady. 
I am an honorable man!"

00:38:04.500 --> 00:38:05.980
TRAVIS: Don't insult him.
TALIESIN: I know.

00:38:05.980 --> 00:38:10.000
TALIESIN: And I would never 
insult your honor

00:38:10.000 --> 00:38:13.000
or preferences of any kind.

00:38:13.000 --> 00:38:16.188
MATT: "Are you saying I'm pretty?"

00:38:16.188 --> 00:38:19.000
TALIESIN: Victor, I think you know 
how I feel about that,

00:38:19.000 --> 00:38:22.000
but you're 
a very attractive man, and--

00:38:22.000 --> 00:38:24.000
MATT: "Your friend's hitting on me."
TRAVIS: I know it.

00:38:24.000 --> 00:38:25.500
MATT: "I'm taken."

00:38:25.500 --> 00:38:27.000
TRAVIS: He's taken.

00:38:27.000 --> 00:38:29.000
TALIESIN: Are you dating right now?

00:38:29.000 --> 00:38:31.000
MATT: "No, I'm just taken."

00:38:31.000 --> 00:38:32.000
TALIESIN: Okay.

00:38:32.000 --> 00:38:35.394
(laughs) I can't. 
I'm sorry. I'm good.

00:38:37.000 --> 00:38:38.840
MATT: "(shouting) How much?"

00:38:38.840 --> 00:38:40.500
TALIESIN: Well, I was going to offer,

00:38:40.500 --> 00:38:42.000
I was originally going to offer 
some gold if you like,

00:38:42.000 --> 00:38:45.046
but if you'd like,
I could make you a tool

00:38:45.046 --> 00:38:48.000
you could use 
with your current predicament.

00:38:48.000 --> 00:38:51.000
Some sort of simple
clawing mechanism

00:38:51.000 --> 00:38:55.000
for grasping, lifting,
not getting caught in your mine.

00:38:55.000 --> 00:38:58.000
MATT: "Maybe. Maybe.
Maybe a trade? Maybe a claw?"

00:38:58.000 --> 00:39:00.000
TALIESIN: I love trade. 
Trade is brilliant.

00:39:00.000 --> 00:39:03.325
MATT: "Build and bring.
Build and bring, and we trade."

00:39:04.000 --> 00:39:07.000
TALIESIN: I would ask one other thing,
if I am to do this for you.

00:39:07.000 --> 00:39:08.500
MATT: "Oh, so many questions!

00:39:08.500 --> 00:39:11.000
"Does he have questions, too?
Does he have questions, too?!"

00:39:11.000 --> 00:39:12.500
SAM: I do 
have a question, actually.

00:39:12.500 --> 00:39:14.000
TALIESIN: You have a question?
SAM: Yes, I do.

00:39:14.000 --> 00:39:17.000
TRAVIS: I don't, no. 
I don't have any questions. None.

00:39:17.000 --> 00:39:19.000
MATT: (sighs) "I like him. 
What's your question?"

00:39:19.000 --> 00:39:20.500
SAM: I'm just looking 
for a hat shop.

00:39:20.500 --> 00:39:22.000
Is there a hat shop around here?

00:39:22.000 --> 00:39:23.000
MATT: (considering noise)

00:39:23.000 --> 00:39:28.000
And he starts pulling around
from a pile of oiled rags and shit

00:39:28.000 --> 00:39:30.000
and he pulls up
what looks like a small burlap sack

00:39:30.000 --> 00:39:32.000
that's torn somewhat at the opening.

00:39:32.000 --> 00:39:34.000
"Hat."

00:39:34.000 --> 00:39:38.000
SAM: Oh, god. Ugh.
All right, thank you. Thank you.

00:39:38.000 --> 00:39:40.000
MATT: "My pleasure. 
Happy to help." (chuckles)

00:39:40.000 --> 00:39:41.000
SAM: Okay.

00:39:41.000 --> 00:39:43.000
TALIESIN: That was everything
I could have hoped for, and more.

00:39:43.000 --> 00:39:45.000
MATT: "Don't get near the fire."

00:39:45.000 --> 00:39:47.000
TALIESIN: Really, don't.
SAM: Thank you.

00:39:47.000 --> 00:39:51.000
TALIESIN: Has Dr. Ripley--
has a woman come by to buy black powder,

00:39:51.000 --> 00:39:53.500
one hand, one mechanical hand,

00:39:53.500 --> 00:39:56.000
one normal hand? Mechanical hand?

00:39:56.000 --> 00:39:58.000
MATT: "Is that the one
you're saying you can make?"

00:39:58.000 --> 00:40:00.000
TALIESIN: I'm going 
to make you something,

00:40:00.000 --> 00:40:02.700
nice and useful claw piece, yes.

00:40:02.700 --> 00:40:05.000
MATT: "So you're saying 
that this woman

00:40:05.000 --> 00:40:07.000
"made a better hand 
than you can make?"

00:40:07.000 --> 00:40:08.500
TALIESIN: No, I can make 
a better hand.

00:40:08.500 --> 00:40:11.780
MATT: "Then make me a better hand!
Why would you give me a lesser hand?!"

00:40:11.780 --> 00:40:15.080
TALIESIN: You're going to need to give me
quite a bit of black powder for that.

00:40:15.080 --> 00:40:17.000
And more questions.

00:40:17.000 --> 00:40:20.000
TRAVIS: Ooh.
MATT: "Really?"

00:40:20.000 --> 00:40:23.000
(laughter)

00:40:23.000 --> 00:40:25.700
MATT: "I've had a bad day."

00:40:25.700 --> 00:40:28.260
TALIESIN: Is that recent?
SAM: That happened today?

00:40:28.260 --> 00:40:30.000
TALIESIN: It doesn't look that recent.

00:40:30.000 --> 00:40:31.500
MATT: (ripping sounds)

00:40:31.500 --> 00:40:33.000
He starts unwrapping the wound.

00:40:33.000 --> 00:40:35.000
TALIESIN: Oh, that's recent.
That's wet. That's very wet.

00:40:35.000 --> 00:40:36.340
MATT: It's pretty recent.

00:40:36.340 --> 00:40:39.974
TALIESIN: I can work with that.
I can work with that.

00:40:41.000 --> 00:40:43.640
I'm going to go construct you something

00:40:43.640 --> 00:40:48.020
that will be perfect for your needs.
I have a great idea.

00:40:48.020 --> 00:40:53.000
I will need another hogshead and a half 
of black powder

00:40:53.000 --> 00:40:56.000
and a little information
about another customer

00:40:56.000 --> 00:41:00.000
and then I will leave you 
to your work. Is that fair?

00:41:00.000 --> 00:41:01.500
MATT: "Fair!"

00:41:01.500 --> 00:41:05.430
He turns around, rushes over,
and grabs the same phantom hogshead

00:41:05.430 --> 00:41:06.650
that he has lying around his place.

00:41:06.650 --> 00:41:08.000
TALIESIN: He eats a lot of pork.

00:41:08.000 --> 00:41:10.650
MATT: Before he fills it with powder,
he goes over to Scanlan and goes,

00:41:10.650 --> 00:41:14.500
"(hums) Too big."

00:41:14.500 --> 00:41:16.000
TRAVIS: Good hat.

00:41:16.000 --> 00:41:19.000
MATT: Fills it with black powder,
carefully brings it over,

00:41:19.000 --> 00:41:21.000
holding it under his arm.

00:41:21.000 --> 00:41:22.660
(grunts)

00:41:22.660 --> 00:41:25.000
TALIESIN: Thank you. (grunts)

00:41:25.000 --> 00:41:27.000
I will put this 
in something reasonable.

00:41:27.000 --> 00:41:32.680
I'll be back 
in just a little bit with--

00:41:32.680 --> 00:41:35.730
actually, do you have a glove
that you used to wear,

00:41:35.730 --> 00:41:37.940
or anything like that? 
Do you have something?

00:41:37.940 --> 00:41:39.000
MATT: "Yes!"

00:41:39.000 --> 00:41:41.810
He pulls out the glove 
that was on the hand,

00:41:41.810 --> 00:41:44.000
(laughing) and you can see
that it's blown apart,

00:41:44.000 --> 00:41:45.360
hand burned to cinders--

00:41:45.360 --> 00:41:46.960
TALIESIN: I can 
take measurements from that.

00:41:46.960 --> 00:41:51.880
MATT: It's more a sleeve 
with a charcoaled edge.

00:41:51.880 --> 00:41:55.000
TALIESIN: I'm going to be busy. 
Can you cast the--

00:41:55.000 --> 00:41:57.000
SAM: No, but Keyleth can,

00:41:57.000 --> 00:41:59.000
and I think that would save you 
a lot of time.

00:41:59.000 --> 00:42:01.000
MARISHA: I'm not here.
TALIESIN: She's not here.

00:42:01.000 --> 00:42:03.000
SAM: No, but we can go get her 
and come back.

00:42:03.000 --> 00:42:05.680
TALIESIN: To?
SAM: To just fix his hand.

00:42:05.680 --> 00:42:07.500
TALIESIN: I don't think 
she can just fix his hand.

00:42:07.500 --> 00:42:09.670
SAM: Someone can restore something.
Maybe Pike can.

00:42:09.670 --> 00:42:12.000
MARISHA: I can. 
Not today, but I can over time.

00:42:12.000 --> 00:42:14.000
TRAVIS: Want me to give it a try?

00:42:14.000 --> 00:42:17.670
TALIESIN: While I'm tempted-- 
would you just--

00:42:17.670 --> 00:42:19.333
I feel like I made a deal.

00:42:19.333 --> 00:42:21.000
I'm just going to have to see to it.

00:42:21.000 --> 00:42:23.190
SAM: I think he would prefer
a real hand than a claw hand.

00:42:23.190 --> 00:42:25.470
TALIESIN: Would you prefer 
a real hand or a claw hand?

00:42:25.470 --> 00:42:28.000
MATT: "Depends. 
How cool is the claw hand?"

00:42:28.000 --> 00:42:29.630
TRAVIS AND SAM: (laugh)

00:42:29.630 --> 00:42:31.410
TALIESIN: That's what I thought.

00:42:33.310 --> 00:42:35.000
SAM: I would much rather 
you spend time

00:42:35.000 --> 00:42:37.000
on projects for us 
than projects for him.

00:42:37.000 --> 00:42:38.500
TALIESIN: This is projects for us.

00:42:38.500 --> 00:42:40.590
TRAVIS: I vote for the claw. 
It's pretty cool.

00:42:40.590 --> 00:42:42.500
TALIESIN: And believe me, I would like--

00:42:42.500 --> 00:42:44.000
MATT: "Cooler than that lady's hand?"

00:42:44.000 --> 00:42:45.500
TALIESIN: Keeping him happy is pertinent.

00:42:45.500 --> 00:42:47.000
I can make this myself, 
it's just very difficult.

00:42:47.000 --> 00:42:49.000
SAM: We have party members
who can regrow his hand.

00:42:49.000 --> 00:42:50.510
TRAVIS: Hey, Percy.
TALIESIN: Yes?

00:42:50.510 --> 00:42:53.170
TRAVIS: He wants the claw to be cooler 
than that lady's claw hand.

00:42:53.170 --> 00:42:56.000
TALIESIN: That's very easy to do.
She has no aesthetics whatsoever.

00:42:56.000 --> 00:42:58.570
TRAVIS: All right. 
Then eff the old original hand.

00:42:58.570 --> 00:43:00.320
Let's give him 
a reasonable claw, yeah?

00:43:00.320 --> 00:43:02.500
TALIESIN: Don't worry about it.
SAM: All right.

00:43:02.500 --> 00:43:04.000
TALIESIN: It'll be fine.

00:43:04.000 --> 00:43:05.500
And if you can't do the mansion,

00:43:05.500 --> 00:43:07.000
I know where I can 
go get some work done.

00:43:07.000 --> 00:43:09.130
SAM: Oh, you want me to make--
we have the Slayer's Take.

00:43:09.130 --> 00:43:11.000
They have a workshop, don't they?

00:43:11.000 --> 00:43:13.000
TALIESIN: If not, I know
where I can work on something.

00:43:13.000 --> 00:43:14.000
I will be back.

00:43:14.000 --> 00:43:15.840
I will not leave town
before I've delivered to you something--

00:43:15.840 --> 00:43:17.000
MATT: "(squawks)"

00:43:17.000 --> 00:43:18.770
He takes the hogshead.

00:43:18.770 --> 00:43:20.500
TALIESIN: Oh! Absolutely fair.

00:43:20.500 --> 00:43:22.000
MATT: "Trade when you bring hand."

00:43:22.000 --> 00:43:23.500
TALIESIN: Yes, of course.

00:43:23.500 --> 00:43:30.000
MATT: "Then I deliver with new hand.
Then all is well."

00:43:30.000 --> 00:43:31.000
TRAVIS: Yeah.

00:43:31.000 --> 00:43:32.650
MATT: "No more questions!"

00:43:32.650 --> 00:43:36.000
TALIESIN: No. That's fine.
We'll be back! It'll be good.

00:43:36.000 --> 00:43:39.000
MATT: "You're small."

00:43:39.000 --> 00:43:41.000
SAM: I need a big hat.

00:43:41.000 --> 00:43:43.710
MATT: "Can't help you, sorry."

00:43:43.710 --> 00:43:44.730
SAM: All right.

00:43:44.730 --> 00:43:46.630
TALIESIN: Are we going to go 
find a hat shop, then?

00:43:46.630 --> 00:43:49.000
SAM: Maybe, if we pass one.

00:43:49.000 --> 00:43:52.000
TALIESIN: All right. 
We will be back. Stay safe.

00:43:52.000 --> 00:43:55.000
MATT: "Okay. 
Don't touch the door, please!"

00:43:55.000 --> 00:44:00.430
TALIESIN: Yes. No. Just. 
We'll be back. Bye!

00:44:00.430 --> 00:44:04.060
TALIESIN: I'm going to go find
a workshop to work on something.

00:44:04.060 --> 00:44:07.000
TRAVIS: I like you. 
We'll see you later.

00:44:07.000 --> 00:44:09.000
MATT: "(chuckles) Heâ€™s big."

00:44:09.000 --> 00:44:11.000
TRAVIS: (chuckles)

00:44:11.000 --> 00:44:14.000
TALIESIN: And I'm just right.
It's... a thing.

00:44:14.000 --> 00:44:17.000
MATT: "I'm undecided about you."

00:44:17.000 --> 00:44:19.430
TALIESIN: You're not alone.

00:44:19.430 --> 00:44:22.000
I'm going to go see
if the Slayer's Take has--

00:44:22.000 --> 00:44:23.440
SAM: We're going to leave.

00:44:23.440 --> 00:44:26.930
TALIESIN: I cannot handle 
any more of that. That was brutal.

00:44:26.930 --> 00:44:28.000
SAM: Too good.

00:44:28.000 --> 00:44:31.220
TRAVIS: I feel like 
youâ€™re just on a higher level.

00:44:31.220 --> 00:44:33.000
ASHLEY: Right?
LAURA: So much.

00:44:33.000 --> 00:44:34.800
LAURA: I just thought you were
going to make him not there

00:44:34.800 --> 00:44:36.500
so you didn't have to do it.

00:44:36.500 --> 00:44:38.000
MATT: No no no.

00:44:38.000 --> 00:44:41.310
MARISHA: Yeah, yeah yeah.
He's just not home. Sorry, guys.

00:44:41.310 --> 00:44:43.000
ASHLEY: Oh, I love him.

00:44:43.000 --> 00:44:44.500
MARISHA: Victor's on vacation.

00:44:44.500 --> 00:44:46.410
TALIESIN: So, I'm going to go 
see if there's--

00:44:46.410 --> 00:44:48.000
if there's not a blacksmithing,

00:44:48.000 --> 00:44:50.000
if there's not somewhere I can do

00:44:50.000 --> 00:44:52.000
a bit of basic smithing work 
and technical work,

00:44:52.000 --> 00:44:54.560
then I'm going to go 
find that blacksmith from last time.

00:44:54.560 --> 00:44:57.940
MATT: There's basic materials to do

00:44:57.940 --> 00:45:00.500
essentially weapon repairs, 
armor repairs,

00:45:00.500 --> 00:45:03.000
minor armor construction
within the Slayer's Take.

00:45:03.000 --> 00:45:04.500
If you want something 
that's going to be

00:45:04.500 --> 00:45:06.580
a little more to the level 
of what you're doing,

00:45:06.580 --> 00:45:09.000
you may have to actually 
rent out a facility.

00:45:09.000 --> 00:45:12.000
TALIESIN: Well, I'm going to go find
that young chap from before.

00:45:12.000 --> 00:45:15.000
MATT: Okay. Yeah, easy enough to do.

00:45:15.000 --> 00:45:17.000
If you want to rent the forge 
for the day

00:45:17.000 --> 00:45:19.000
to craft whatever it is 
you're looking to craft,

00:45:19.000 --> 00:45:21.530
he's charging you 
50 gold for the day.

00:45:21.530 --> 00:45:23.000
TALIESIN: 50 gold for the day?

00:45:23.000 --> 00:45:26.000
Can I use all of his tools
and just my own materials?

00:45:26.000 --> 00:45:28.000
MATT: You have to supply 
your own material, but he'll let you rent.

00:45:28.000 --> 00:45:31.000
TALIESIN: I'm going to run and find Vax,
get my stuff, and go to work.

00:45:31.000 --> 00:45:35.520
MATT: Okay. You guys.

00:45:35.520 --> 00:45:40.650
You four make your way
over towards the Duskmeadow.

00:45:40.650 --> 00:45:42.000
LAURA: Trinket's out.

00:45:42.000 --> 00:45:44.000
MATT: Trinket's out? (whoosh)

00:45:44.000 --> 00:45:45.810
(bear moans)

00:45:45.810 --> 00:45:47.000
LAURA: Come on, Trinket.

00:45:47.000 --> 00:45:48.650
MATT: (grunts)

00:45:48.650 --> 00:45:51.700
He rolls his head against you,
licks the side of your face,

00:45:51.700 --> 00:45:55.000
happy to be out 
of that stuffy little necklace.

00:45:55.000 --> 00:45:59.000
You make your way towards the Duskmeadow,
which you've seen before.

00:45:59.000 --> 00:46:04.240
It's a very comparatively...

00:46:04.240 --> 00:46:06.300
glum-looking area of the town,

00:46:06.300 --> 00:46:08.760
hence the name that accompanies it,

00:46:08.760 --> 00:46:12.000
but this is the area 
of the city that contains

00:46:12.000 --> 00:46:18.000
the Raven's Crest,
the Amaranthine Oubliette.

00:46:18.000 --> 00:46:24.000
It also contains 
the entire town's catacombs.

00:46:24.000 --> 00:46:27.480
This is where, 
since this town's existence,

00:46:27.480 --> 00:46:29.160
all of the dead are interred

00:46:29.160 --> 00:46:34.000
perpetually deeper and deeper and deeper
beneath this part of the city.

00:46:34.000 --> 00:46:37.620
Also one of
the oldest libraries of the city

00:46:37.620 --> 00:46:39.800
is kept here as well.

00:46:39.800 --> 00:46:42.660
As you approach the outskirts--
and you can see a very fine line

00:46:42.660 --> 00:46:45.800
between this area and the Birth Heart,

00:46:45.800 --> 00:46:49.000
which is the Melora section of the city.

00:46:49.000 --> 00:46:52.000
There is a very, very wide river divide
between the two of them

00:46:52.000 --> 00:46:55.000
and it's like night and day, 
back and back.

00:46:55.000 --> 00:46:58.000
Very, very, very directly 
between the two of them.

00:46:58.000 --> 00:47:03.000
You can see on Melora's side
there's just stalks and stalks of corn

00:47:03.000 --> 00:47:08.000
and other vegetation 
that's being grown for food.

00:47:08.000 --> 00:47:11.000
There's almost like a lush forest
that curls around the outside of it

00:47:11.000 --> 00:47:15.000
that doesn't match 
the rest of the indigenous trees

00:47:15.000 --> 00:47:17.000
you've seen in this area of Othanzia.

00:47:17.000 --> 00:47:23.000
The entire Birth Heart area,
where this temple to Melora is,

00:47:23.000 --> 00:47:24.000
is just this

00:47:24.000 --> 00:47:26.790
plucked-out-of-nowhere section 
placed into it.

00:47:26.790 --> 00:47:28.190
And then you move over
to the Duskmeadow

00:47:28.190 --> 00:47:34.460
and it's just... like the color 
has left the vicinity.

00:47:34.460 --> 00:47:37.000
And there you see in the center
of this part of the town,

00:47:37.000 --> 00:47:43.530
this large, looming,
ominous obsidian and gold structure.

00:47:43.530 --> 00:47:47.500
It's like a giant black stone aerie.

00:47:47.500 --> 00:47:50.990
It has no intricacies 
from this distance that you can see.

00:47:50.990 --> 00:47:57.000
It's almost like a giant square building
that is just devoid of light,

00:47:57.000 --> 00:48:00.000
with little glimmers of gold
when the light catches it at moments.

00:48:01.810 --> 00:48:03.000
It's hard to miss

00:48:03.000 --> 00:48:06.710
and definitely stands as a centerpiece 
to this section of Vasselheim.

00:48:06.710 --> 00:48:08.240
LIAM: The whole walk over,

00:48:08.240 --> 00:48:11.840
I've been talking a lot,
mostly to Trinket.

00:48:11.840 --> 00:48:14.600
You know, scratching him 
behind the ears, saying,

00:48:14.600 --> 00:48:18.130
"Buddy, you've been 
trapped in there a while.

00:48:18.130 --> 00:48:19.710
"It's good to see you out."

00:48:19.710 --> 00:48:21.000
MATT: "(moans, snuffles)"

00:48:21.000 --> 00:48:23.550
LIAM: Come hug your uncle. Come.
LAURA: He doesn't mind it.

00:48:23.550 --> 00:48:26.000
LIAM: I'm sure he doesn't.
I'm just happy to see him.

00:48:26.000 --> 00:48:28.000
MATT: He presses his nose 
under yours

00:48:28.000 --> 00:48:30.050
and lifts your chin up
and you bite your lip a little

00:48:30.050 --> 00:48:32.000
from the sudden impact 
from this very large bear,

00:48:32.000 --> 00:48:34.000
but it's all with love.

00:48:34.000 --> 00:48:37.000
LIAM: Yeah. It's cold. You're sure 
you don't want to go back in?

00:48:37.000 --> 00:48:39.910
Nah, you don't want to go back in. 
I know.

00:48:39.910 --> 00:48:41.000
MARISHA: (whispering) Hey, Pike.

00:48:41.000 --> 00:48:43.000
LIAM: Just nervous talking 
the whole way there.

00:48:43.000 --> 00:48:45.000
MARISHA: (whispering) 
I think Vax is talking to himself.

00:48:45.000 --> 00:48:47.000
ASHLEY: (whispering) 
He's very nervous right now.

00:48:47.000 --> 00:48:48.710
ASHLEY: This is a big deal.
MARISHA: Yeah.

00:48:48.710 --> 00:48:55.000
ASHLEY: This temple is very...
it's lovely.

00:48:55.000 --> 00:49:00.000
MARISHA: It's gorgeous. 
It's very intimidating.

00:49:00.000 --> 00:49:03.020
Do you know anything about this?
You've lived here for a while, Pike.

00:49:03.020 --> 00:49:05.000
ASHLEY: I've never been by.

00:49:05.000 --> 00:49:07.000
MARISHA: Never been in?
ASHLEY: I've never been in, no.

00:49:07.000 --> 00:49:10.000
MATT: You do know from your time here
and what little you've heard

00:49:10.000 --> 00:49:12.000
that part of the purpose 
of this vicinity

00:49:12.000 --> 00:49:15.500
is not just to inter the dead
within part of these catacombs.

00:49:15.500 --> 00:49:22.000
The library here 
is kind of a loose partnership

00:49:22.000 --> 00:49:26.500
between the people worshipers of her
and those who follow Ioun.

00:49:26.500 --> 00:49:31.000
It is a center for knowledge and history
kept within the city.

00:49:31.000 --> 00:49:35.540
But you'll see throughout the town
and the landscaped outer wall

00:49:35.540 --> 00:49:38.740
that surrounds this entire portion 
of Vasselheim,

00:49:38.740 --> 00:49:45.020
there are repetitive glyphs
that line this entire area.

00:49:45.020 --> 00:49:48.840
And from what you've heard,
at the very least, most of these glyphs,

00:49:48.840 --> 00:49:51.000
which you see 
across the corners of roadways,

00:49:51.000 --> 00:49:56.820
and many of which surround
the entrance to the catacombs,

00:49:56.820 --> 00:50:02.620
it is a perpetual enchantment that is 
to seal any sort of possible undeath.

00:50:02.620 --> 00:50:05.380
There once was 
a terrible scourge of undeath

00:50:05.380 --> 00:50:08.000
in this part of the landscape, 
long ago,

00:50:08.000 --> 00:50:11.000
that corresponded with a battle 
hundreds of years ago,

00:50:11.000 --> 00:50:13.500
and since then, the reinforcement 
has been put in place

00:50:13.500 --> 00:50:15.000
to prevent that 
from happening again.

00:50:15.000 --> 00:50:17.000
So the downside is

00:50:17.000 --> 00:50:18.780
that the power of these glyphs 
that prevent undeath

00:50:18.780 --> 00:50:23.000
also prevent any actual vegetation
from existing in this area as well.

00:50:23.000 --> 00:50:25.680
So all the ground 
that you've come across:

00:50:25.680 --> 00:50:29.410
no grass, no natural vegetation.

00:50:29.410 --> 00:50:33.000
It's just dirt and ash and dust.

00:50:33.000 --> 00:50:36.970
MARISHA: Can we recognize the language
in which the runes come from?

00:50:36.970 --> 00:50:43.390
MATT: The magic itself 
is divine in nature,

00:50:43.390 --> 00:50:46.000
but it's based in the same
very, very base Draconic glyphs

00:50:46.000 --> 00:50:48.000
that a lot of arcane magic 
is based on.

00:50:48.000 --> 00:50:50.160
It's very-- it's &lt;i&gt;old&lt;/i&gt; magic.

00:50:50.160 --> 00:50:53.100
ASHLEY: (laughs) It's old.

00:50:53.100 --> 00:50:58.010
MATT: Yeah. It's based 
in some sort of divine ritual.

00:50:58.010 --> 00:51:00.500
MARISHA: What did you say 
the name was

00:51:00.500 --> 00:51:02.000
of the Raven Queen's temple, again?

00:51:02.000 --> 00:51:05.000
MATT: The temple itself 
is referred to as Raven's Crest.

00:51:05.000 --> 00:51:06.340
MARISHA: Raven's Crest?

00:51:06.340 --> 00:51:07.500
MATT: Raven's Crest, yes.

00:51:07.500 --> 00:51:08.960
MARISHA: Okay.

00:51:08.960 --> 00:51:11.330
ASHLEY: How are you feeling, Vax?

00:51:11.330 --> 00:51:13.740
LIAM: I'm all right.

00:51:13.740 --> 00:51:16.880
I'm just going to talk 
to my sister for a minute.

00:51:16.880 --> 00:51:18.000
ASHLEY: Okay.

00:51:21.520 --> 00:51:24.000
LIAM: You know, 
I know you want to--

00:51:24.000 --> 00:51:27.000
I know you.
I know you want to be here.

00:51:27.000 --> 00:51:29.000
LAURA: I know you don't 
want me to come.

00:51:29.000 --> 00:51:31.000
LIAM: I don't. 
I really don't.

00:51:31.000 --> 00:51:36.000
LAURA: I know. 
And I won't, if you're sure.

00:51:36.000 --> 00:51:40.130
I put you in this place 
and I feel terrible about it

00:51:40.130 --> 00:51:42.170
and I know you're extremely nervous.

00:51:42.170 --> 00:51:45.070
Trinket can sense it, too.
He's very in tune with those emotions.

00:51:45.070 --> 00:51:46.650
And I just--

00:51:46.650 --> 00:51:48.850
LIAM: Listen to me.

00:51:48.850 --> 00:51:52.620
You did not 
put me in this place.

00:51:52.620 --> 00:51:55.500
No one put me in this place.

00:51:55.500 --> 00:51:58.040
LIAM: And everything's going to be fine.
LAURA: Everything will be fine!

00:51:58.040 --> 00:52:02.890
LIAM: And I tug her sleeves
and make them a little more orderly

00:52:02.890 --> 00:52:07.580
and I move a bit of hair out of her face
and I do a button that's not done.

00:52:07.580 --> 00:52:09.000
LAURA: (laughs)

00:52:09.000 --> 00:52:12.730
LIAM: Everything's going to be fine.
LAURA: I wanted it unbuttoned, actually.

00:52:12.730 --> 00:52:16.020
LIAM: That's all right. Just wait here
I'll be out in a bit, all right?

00:52:16.020 --> 00:52:18.000
LAURA: Yes.
LIAM: Everything's fine.

00:52:18.000 --> 00:52:20.020
LAURA: I know. Everything's fine.
LIAM: Yeah.

00:52:20.020 --> 00:52:22.000
LAURA: You don't need 
to be nervous, either.

00:52:22.000 --> 00:52:23.500
LIAM: I'm not.

00:52:23.500 --> 00:52:28.000
LAURA: I will be here waiting for you
when you come out.

00:52:28.000 --> 00:52:30.000
LIAM: I know. I'll see you--

00:52:30.000 --> 00:52:32.000
LAURA: I love you.

00:52:32.000 --> 00:52:34.000
LIAM: You know I love you, too.

00:52:34.000 --> 00:52:36.000
LAURA: I'm proud of you, you know.

00:52:36.000 --> 00:52:38.000
She's just going to love you so much.

00:52:38.000 --> 00:52:39.000
And who knows,

00:52:39.000 --> 00:52:41.500
you might have a new girlfriend 
when you come out.

00:52:41.500 --> 00:52:43.000
(laughs nervously, sighs)

00:52:43.000 --> 00:52:45.020
I've heard other people 
have dated gods before.

00:52:45.020 --> 00:52:49.000
I've heard it's done.
That Cashew guy. Anyway.

00:52:49.000 --> 00:52:50.500
LIAM: You're going 
to wait here for me, right?

00:52:50.500 --> 00:52:53.500
LAURA: I'll be right here.

00:52:53.500 --> 00:52:55.000
LIAM: And then I drop the smile

00:52:55.000 --> 00:52:56.000
as I walk off towards the other two.

00:52:56.000 --> 00:52:57.000
MATT: Okay.

00:52:57.000 --> 00:52:58.000
Which, as you turn and look,

00:52:58.000 --> 00:53:00.000
when you originally approached

00:53:00.000 --> 00:53:03.000
the stairs that lead up to the entrance 
of this large structure,

00:53:03.000 --> 00:53:05.000
it was just empty, doors closed.

00:53:05.000 --> 00:53:08.000
There was no guard post 
on the outside.

00:53:08.000 --> 00:53:13.000
It was just these two looming,
almost dark glass-type doors

00:53:13.000 --> 00:53:15.050
about 12 feet tall
and about 8 feet wide on each side

00:53:15.050 --> 00:53:16.120
that are just locked shut.

00:53:16.120 --> 00:53:18.000
As soon as you turn 
to walk towards them,

00:53:18.000 --> 00:53:21.000
the doors open and you see a figure 
standing there at the door,

00:53:21.000 --> 00:53:22.500
just looking directly at you.

00:53:22.500 --> 00:53:23.750
Or at least you assume 
is looking right at you.

00:53:23.750 --> 00:53:25.000
It's hard to see.

00:53:25.000 --> 00:53:30.000
This individual, 
somewhat lithe in physicality,

00:53:30.000 --> 00:53:33.000
is wearing long, dark robes

00:53:33.000 --> 00:53:36.000
and their face is shrouded
in opaque black cloth,

00:53:36.000 --> 00:53:38.000
like a death shroud
that just blocks the entire face.

00:53:38.000 --> 00:53:42.000
You can see 
the hint of a jawline, a nose.

00:53:42.000 --> 00:53:45.000
It looks to be a person
of some background in there,

00:53:45.000 --> 00:53:48.000
but they're just standing there,
watching you.

00:53:48.000 --> 00:53:50.910
And as soon as you react 
to their appearance,

00:53:50.910 --> 00:53:52.880
the hand just beckons quietly.

00:53:54.000 --> 00:53:56.110
LIAM: Were you expecting me?

00:53:58.610 --> 00:54:01.000
All right.

00:54:01.000 --> 00:54:05.440
I've brought a couple of friends.
Is that permissible here?

00:54:09.310 --> 00:54:11.310
They'll keep quiet.

00:54:12.000 --> 00:54:14.550
MARISHA: I turn to Vex.

00:54:14.550 --> 00:54:16.000
LAURA: Keep him safe.

00:54:16.000 --> 00:54:18.990
MARISHA: I swear to you.

00:54:18.990 --> 00:54:21.840
We're all coming out of here alive.

00:54:21.840 --> 00:54:23.440
LAURA: I know.

00:54:23.440 --> 00:54:27.000
MARISHA: But if like an hour passes 
and we don't,

00:54:27.000 --> 00:54:30.000
maybe come in?

00:54:30.000 --> 00:54:31.500
But we're all 
coming out of here alive,

00:54:31.500 --> 00:54:32.500
so don't worry about it.

00:54:32.500 --> 00:54:33.640
It's fine.

00:54:33.640 --> 00:54:35.000
ASHLEY: And I squeeze her hand.

00:54:35.000 --> 00:54:38.000
I'll make sure 
he gets out okay. I promise.

00:54:38.000 --> 00:54:41.000
LAURA: All right.
ASHLEY: Okay. Please be safe.

00:54:41.000 --> 00:54:42.630
LAURA: It'll be fine.
ASHLEY: It'll be fine. Yes.

00:54:42.630 --> 00:54:45.470
LAURA: I'll just be right here.
Waiting here with Trinket.

00:54:45.470 --> 00:54:46.500
ASHLEY: Okay.

00:54:46.500 --> 00:54:49.030
LAURA: Just calmly leaning 
against a wall. No big deal.

00:54:49.030 --> 00:54:50.000
ASHLEY: Okay.

00:54:50.000 --> 00:54:52.650
MARISHA: We've faced 
way more terrifying things

00:54:52.650 --> 00:54:58.000
than a few albeit creepy 
men in robes.

00:54:58.000 --> 00:54:59.530
LAURA: I don't even think she's that bad.

00:54:59.530 --> 00:55:01.159
She's not going to be bad.

00:55:01.159 --> 00:55:02.237
LIAM: Guys.
LAURA: Just go.

00:55:02.237 --> 00:55:04.250
ASHLEY: Okay. We'll go. 
We'll go in with you.

00:55:04.250 --> 00:55:05.570
MATT: All right.

00:55:05.570 --> 00:55:09.750
As you step up to the stairs,
the figure leads you all inside,

00:55:09.750 --> 00:55:13.840
and as you step into the main center
of this initial walkway chamber,

00:55:13.840 --> 00:55:15.800
the figure doesn't enter with you.

00:55:15.800 --> 00:55:17.510
It just closes the door behind you.

00:55:17.510 --> 00:55:18.670
(echoing thud)

00:55:18.670 --> 00:55:21.000
You can feel
the hint of vibration of impact

00:55:21.000 --> 00:55:23.000
as the doors close shut.

00:55:23.000 --> 00:55:24.000
MARISHA: It's dark?

00:55:24.000 --> 00:55:26.470
MATT: It's lowly-lit on the inside,
and it's interesting.

00:55:26.470 --> 00:55:28.000
From the outside, it looks like

00:55:28.000 --> 00:55:31.000
a black, solid,
impossible-to-see-through building.

00:55:31.000 --> 00:55:33.000
From the inside, 
you can actually look out

00:55:33.000 --> 00:55:34.370
and the entire building

00:55:34.370 --> 00:55:40.000
is made of this glass,
this somewhat-warped, dark glass.

00:55:40.000 --> 00:55:43.850
And you can see almost
the entirety of the outside

00:55:43.850 --> 00:55:44.960
from your position.

00:55:44.960 --> 00:55:46.830
The doors are held aloft into it.

00:55:46.830 --> 00:55:48.720
It's like a one-way 
type enchantment,

00:55:48.720 --> 00:55:53.300
or the construct, the material itself,
is somewhat translucent from this side.

00:55:53.300 --> 00:55:57.670
MARISHA: Like an interrogation room?
Like one-way mirror type of thing?

00:55:57.670 --> 00:56:00.190
MATT: Kind of. Or like a very,
very dark pair of sunglasses,

00:56:00.190 --> 00:56:05.000
but made of naturally-formed rock, almost.

00:56:05.000 --> 00:56:06.900
LIAM: Noticing that, I turn

00:56:06.900 --> 00:56:11.890
and just sort of look at my sister
for 5 or 10 more seconds.

00:56:11.890 --> 00:56:16.130
MATT: She doesn't see you
and she just stands there quietly,

00:56:16.130 --> 00:56:19.000
looking around, 
inspecting the vicinity.

00:56:19.000 --> 00:56:22.000
Pets Trinket a little.

00:56:22.000 --> 00:56:26.000
LIAM: (hesitantly) Let's do this.

00:56:26.000 --> 00:56:27.690
SAM: (chuckles)

00:56:27.690 --> 00:56:31.000
ASHLEY: Do I feel anything, 
being in here?

00:56:31.000 --> 00:56:33.670
MATT: You just feel 
a natural tremble

00:56:33.670 --> 00:56:37.000
stepping into a place 
of powerful divine influence

00:56:37.000 --> 00:56:39.430
that is not 
the warm comfort of Sarenrae,

00:56:39.430 --> 00:56:41.000
which has protected you before.

00:56:41.000 --> 00:56:44.000
Now, you understand the way
many deities work in these lands,

00:56:44.000 --> 00:56:47.000
and your place in it,
and Sarenrae's place in it,

00:56:47.000 --> 00:56:49.000
and you know enough 
about the Raven Queen

00:56:49.000 --> 00:56:53.000
to know that this is not 
an unwelcome place, per se.

00:56:53.000 --> 00:56:55.000
Go ahead and roll a religion check.

00:57:05.000 --> 00:57:06.000
ASHLEY: 23.

00:57:06.000 --> 00:57:11.000
MATT: 23. 
You understand the Raven Queen

00:57:11.000 --> 00:57:15.520
has also not always been

00:57:15.520 --> 00:57:19.000
the one who holds sway

00:57:19.000 --> 00:57:22.000
over the domain of death,
the domain of winter,

00:57:22.000 --> 00:57:25.000
the domain of fate.

00:57:25.000 --> 00:57:28.000
Once mortal,
the Raven Queen ascended

00:57:28.000 --> 00:57:32.330
as, essentially, a follower
and a partner

00:57:32.330 --> 00:57:34.210
to the previous god of death,

00:57:34.210 --> 00:57:37.000
which his name
has been erased from the books.

00:57:37.000 --> 00:57:44.000
This mortal ascended many,
many years ago, pre-Second Spark,

00:57:44.000 --> 00:57:48.000
and has since taken what was once

00:57:48.000 --> 00:57:53.000
a tyrannical position of death
and afterlife and souls

00:57:53.000 --> 00:57:56.000
and took it instead
as the natural transition that it is.

00:57:56.000 --> 00:58:00.000
However, 
due to a lack of respect,

00:58:00.000 --> 00:58:05.000
or at least, a lack of, 
for lack of a better term,

00:58:05.000 --> 00:58:09.330
belief or trust from the other gods,

00:58:09.330 --> 00:58:13.000
she only gained dominion
over the actual moment of transition,

00:58:13.000 --> 00:58:15.000
not of the actual souls 
of the afterlife.

00:58:15.000 --> 00:58:20.000
That influence was given to others.

00:58:20.000 --> 00:58:24.000
But the Raven Queen represents

00:58:24.000 --> 00:58:27.000
one of the most feared elements of life,

00:58:27.000 --> 00:58:28.500
which is the end of it,

00:58:28.500 --> 00:58:33.000
but you also know 
that that is a natural thing.

00:58:33.000 --> 00:58:36.000
Your personal belief is up to you.

00:58:36.000 --> 00:58:39.000
The sense you get here is that...

00:58:39.000 --> 00:58:42.280
being an individual 
that worships life,

00:58:42.280 --> 00:58:47.000
that worships redemption,
that worships second chances,

00:58:47.000 --> 00:58:49.000
you can't help
but swallow a little hard

00:58:49.000 --> 00:58:52.000
at the idea of a god that's purpose
is to make sure

00:58:52.000 --> 00:58:55.010
that if you're destined 
to have once chance,

00:58:55.010 --> 00:58:56.510
it stays one chance.

00:58:56.510 --> 00:58:58.230
ASHLEY: Okay.

00:58:58.230 --> 00:59:00.500
MATT: As you begin 
to walk down this hall,

00:59:00.500 --> 00:59:02.000
ever so slow as it is,

00:59:02.000 --> 00:59:05.190
each footfall deafening 
in the clack.

00:59:05.190 --> 00:59:08.000
(clicking footsteps)

00:59:08.000 --> 00:59:11.000
The hallway leads on
for another hundred feet or so

00:59:11.000 --> 00:59:16.000
before the glass,
somewhat translucent material

00:59:16.000 --> 00:59:18.000
shifts into the next chamber,

00:59:18.000 --> 00:59:19.500
into an almost

00:59:19.500 --> 00:59:23.000
deep gray and ivory ice-like interior.

00:59:23.000 --> 00:59:25.000
The dark,
coal-black exterior you've seen

00:59:25.000 --> 00:59:27.000
now transitions into what feels like

00:59:27.000 --> 00:59:31.180
a very finely-carved 
piece of architecture

00:59:31.180 --> 00:59:33.630
from ice and bone.

00:59:33.630 --> 00:59:38.700
MARISHA: Do I get the sense
as a druid, as an Ashari,

00:59:38.700 --> 00:59:42.000
that we've switched into another plane?

00:59:42.000 --> 00:59:47.420
MATT: Go ahead and roll an arcana check,

00:59:47.420 --> 00:59:51.000
as this is not so much
a nature-based thing, yeah.

00:59:51.000 --> 00:59:55.000
MARISHA: Oh! I rolled a 19. 
(laughs) 21.

00:59:55.000 --> 00:59:57.000
LIAM: Oh dear, oh my.
LAURA: Oh gosh, oh jeez.

00:59:57.000 --> 00:59:58.720
MARISHA: Oh goodness gracious.

00:59:58.720 --> 01:00:01.000
MATT: From your understanding

01:00:01.000 --> 01:00:02.500
of transitional magic between planes,

01:00:02.500 --> 01:00:05.000
there has been
no actual shift between planes,

01:00:05.000 --> 01:00:08.000
it's just the material itself

01:00:08.000 --> 01:00:13.000
is different upon the interior
of this building.

01:00:13.000 --> 01:00:14.500
As soon as you enter this place,

01:00:14.500 --> 01:00:17.000
you do see another figure
walking towards you.

01:00:17.000 --> 01:00:19.000
Similar long, dark robes.

01:00:19.000 --> 01:00:21.000
However, the veil 
has been pulled back,

01:00:21.000 --> 01:00:23.230
and you see before you 
what looks to be

01:00:23.230 --> 01:00:29.000
an older elven woman with very, 
very bright silver hair

01:00:29.000 --> 01:00:33.000
that just kind of falls long,
past her shoulders,

01:00:33.000 --> 01:00:38.000
down to her back about mid-waist,
or down to the bottom of her waist.

01:00:38.000 --> 01:00:39.000
With a smile.

01:00:39.000 --> 01:00:45.000
You can see as she walks towards you,
a very welcoming grin.

01:00:45.000 --> 01:00:48.000
As she approaches,
she pays very little mind to you three,

01:00:48.000 --> 01:00:49.500
but directly to you, says,

01:00:49.500 --> 01:00:51.000
LAURA: (whispers) I'm not there.

01:00:51.000 --> 01:00:54.000
MATT: "You walk with Her sight on you.

01:00:54.000 --> 01:00:56.000
"You are ever welcome here."

01:00:58.590 --> 01:01:00.460
LIAM: I've come

01:01:00.460 --> 01:01:07.000
to understand
my place in Her sight.

01:01:09.000 --> 01:01:13.020
MATT: "Then I think, perhaps, 
you are here for communion.

01:01:13.020 --> 01:01:19.000
"Come. Our most sacred chamber.
The communion pool awaits.

01:01:19.000 --> 01:01:22.350
"Only you may have entry,
unfortunately."

01:01:27.000 --> 01:01:28.600
LIAM: Right.

01:01:32.000 --> 01:01:36.010
LIAM: I plant a kiss on the cheek 
of each of the women.

01:01:40.000 --> 01:01:43.000
MARISHA: Do you need anything
before you go in?

01:01:43.000 --> 01:01:47.000
Any enhancement of any kind?

01:01:47.000 --> 01:01:50.000
LIAM: Just cross 
your fingers for me, okay?

01:01:50.000 --> 01:01:53.000
MARISHA: Okay.

01:01:53.000 --> 01:01:55.750
I just kind of squeeze his hand.

01:01:55.750 --> 01:01:57.000
ASHLEY: Same.

01:01:57.000 --> 01:02:00.000
Be careful.

01:02:00.000 --> 01:02:03.000
MARISHA: We're right out here
on the other side of this door.

01:02:03.000 --> 01:02:09.000
If anything terrible happens,
you have the earpiece.

01:02:09.000 --> 01:02:12.000
No one will stop Pike and I
from getting through there

01:02:12.000 --> 01:02:15.000
if something terrible goes wrong.

01:02:17.000 --> 01:02:18.500
Rules be damned.

01:02:18.500 --> 01:02:24.000
LIAM: I made my bed. Now I gotta lie in it.

01:02:24.000 --> 01:02:26.000
I'll see you soon.

01:02:28.000 --> 01:02:29.590
I follow.

01:02:29.590 --> 01:02:33.060
MATT: "Come, champion. 
The Lady of Fates awaits."

01:02:33.060 --> 01:02:36.000
And she turns around
and leads you 30 more feet

01:02:36.000 --> 01:02:39.000
to what looks to be
an ascending staircase

01:02:39.000 --> 01:02:42.760
that just enters
up and out of the sight of you two.

01:02:45.730 --> 01:02:47.780
ASHLEY: We'll just hang out, yeah?

01:02:47.780 --> 01:02:50.000
MARISHA: I guess we'll wait, yeah.

01:02:50.000 --> 01:02:54.000
MATT: You ascend
a few feet behind her,

01:02:54.000 --> 01:02:57.000
about 40 or so feet,

01:02:57.000 --> 01:03:01.000
until it comes
to a single large doorway

01:03:01.000 --> 01:03:03.000
of deep, deep dark oak wood

01:03:03.000 --> 01:03:06.000
with what looks to be
a dark iron ring in the center.

01:03:06.000 --> 01:03:10.930
As she steps up to it, she takes it 
and (thud) knocks on it twice.

01:03:10.930 --> 01:03:17.170
(deep creak) It just shifts open
and leads into a central chamber now

01:03:17.170 --> 01:03:22.000
that looks about a hundred feet high,

01:03:22.000 --> 01:03:24.540
and it is a large steepled dome

01:03:24.540 --> 01:03:28.000
of what looks to be nothing
but stained glass.

01:03:28.000 --> 01:03:31.000
It's awe-inspiring.

01:03:31.000 --> 01:03:34.000
It's beautiful: the colors,
the light as it peeks through.

01:03:36.000 --> 01:03:38.000
The source of light,
diffused as it is by the clouds,

01:03:38.000 --> 01:03:39.500
is sourceless in here.

01:03:39.500 --> 01:03:41.000
It seems like there are beams of light
coming from all directions

01:03:41.000 --> 01:03:43.500
and all the colors
are just strewn across the floor

01:03:43.500 --> 01:03:47.630
in what looks like this
perpetually-shifting kaleidoscope

01:03:47.630 --> 01:03:54.390
of dots of reds and blues and purples
and yellows and pinks and whites.

01:03:54.390 --> 01:03:59.000
You can see, across the room,
there are three other figures

01:03:59.000 --> 01:04:01.840
that are all dressed
in the same dark robes,

01:04:01.840 --> 01:04:05.000
the veils over their heads,
of varying size.

01:04:05.000 --> 01:04:09.000
You can't make out
what their racial background is, per se,

01:04:09.000 --> 01:04:13.500
but they are all stationed
around the center of the room,

01:04:13.500 --> 01:04:15.000
in which lies, from what you can see,

01:04:15.000 --> 01:04:21.000
a very, very large round pool
of some sort of deep crimson liquid.

01:04:28.000 --> 01:04:31.000
LIAM: I have come to pay a debt,

01:04:32.230 --> 01:04:37.580
and I do so gladly
and without question.

01:04:40.000 --> 01:04:41.910
What would you have of me?

01:04:43.000 --> 01:04:46.000
MATT: "You came to speak with the Lady.

01:04:46.000 --> 01:04:48.000
"Well, the way is before you."

01:04:48.000 --> 01:04:50.050
She gestures to the pool.

01:04:54.000 --> 01:04:56.000
LIAM: I walk slow and straight in.

01:04:57.000 --> 01:04:59.610
MATT: You step into it. (squelch)

01:04:59.610 --> 01:05:02.000
It comes up to your ankles,
to your knees.

01:05:02.000 --> 01:05:06.000
And what catches you first
is that the liquid is very thick.

01:05:06.000 --> 01:05:08.000
It is viscous in a familiar way.

01:05:08.000 --> 01:05:12.000
This is most definitively
a pool of blood.

01:05:14.000 --> 01:05:18.000
And it is cold. It is ice-cold.

01:05:18.000 --> 01:05:22.000
As you step in, you can feel that
as it begins to seep into your boots

01:05:22.000 --> 01:05:24.600
and begins to find its way
into the crevices of your outfit

01:05:24.600 --> 01:05:27.000
as you get down into your waist,
it's just chilling.

01:05:27.000 --> 01:05:30.000
You can't help but to stand up straight
as you step further in,

01:05:30.000 --> 01:05:32.000
not quite sure of how deep it gets.

01:05:32.000 --> 01:05:35.000
And it gets deeper. And deeper.

01:05:35.000 --> 01:05:38.000
Up past your chest,
up past your shoulders,

01:05:38.000 --> 01:05:40.940
and you're not even
halfway into the center of the pool

01:05:40.940 --> 01:05:43.000
before it's going past your nose.

01:05:43.000 --> 01:05:44.790
LIAM: I keep going.

01:05:44.790 --> 01:05:49.000
MATT: You take your last breath, hold it,

01:05:49.000 --> 01:05:52.000
and submerge yourself in the pool.

01:05:52.000 --> 01:05:55.750
Darkness around you,
the cold sensation.

01:05:58.520 --> 01:05:59.850
Nothing...

01:06:01.670 --> 01:06:03.060
Nothing...

01:06:06.290 --> 01:06:07.590
Nothing...

01:06:08.480 --> 01:06:12.150
LIAM: I open my mouth and inhale.

01:06:13.870 --> 01:06:16.590
MATT: As you do, 
you feel the blood fill your lungs

01:06:16.590 --> 01:06:21.000
and immediately your lungs begin to seize
with the lack of oxygen.

01:06:21.000 --> 01:06:24.000
You instinctually begin
to reach up for the water and pull,

01:06:24.000 --> 01:06:26.000
but you can't rise.

01:06:26.000 --> 01:06:28.000
You can't get up.

01:06:28.000 --> 01:06:33.940
And at that point, the cold, piercing pain
of the liquid in your lungs

01:06:33.940 --> 01:06:36.000
becomes warm.

01:06:36.000 --> 01:06:39.000
All the liquid around you
becomes warm.

01:06:39.000 --> 01:06:42.050
And in the darkness,
where you cannot see,

01:06:42.050 --> 01:06:45.790
you calm, as suddenly your breathing
is no longer difficult.

01:06:45.790 --> 01:06:48.360
It's natural. It's like air.

01:06:52.000 --> 01:06:57.420
And it's reminiscent
of being in the womb,

01:06:57.420 --> 01:06:59.640
of the moment of birth
you'd forgotten so long ago,

01:06:59.640 --> 01:07:03.000
that you're just surrounded
in darkness and comfort.

01:07:03.000 --> 01:07:04.790
And piercing the center
of this darkness before you,

01:07:04.790 --> 01:07:07.470
you see
a very faint bead of white light

01:07:07.470 --> 01:07:12.000
just begin to spark
and grow, and grow,

01:07:12.000 --> 01:07:16.000
and as that light widens out,
it becomes a face.

01:07:16.000 --> 01:07:18.000
A porcelain face.

01:07:18.000 --> 01:07:24.000
A nose, lips, a chin,
empty dark sockets,

01:07:24.000 --> 01:07:28.690
long dark hair
that goes to crimson and surrounds you.

01:07:31.000 --> 01:07:33.690
You see a small hand
reach up behind

01:07:33.690 --> 01:07:36.000
and lift you from your legs.

01:07:36.000 --> 01:07:38.880
And for what you thought
was only a few feet of liquid,

01:07:38.880 --> 01:07:41.000
you look around you
and it is an endless space,

01:07:41.000 --> 01:07:43.000
a space you've been before,

01:07:43.000 --> 01:07:48.000
a space that you once visited
in your sleep, in your dreams.

01:07:48.000 --> 01:07:49.500
You look down below and you can see

01:07:49.500 --> 01:07:54.910
the infinite skein of threads
that you were once given inspection to.

01:07:54.910 --> 01:07:59.000
As you look down, you see the very palm
of the Raven Queen

01:07:59.000 --> 01:08:01.000
holding you aloft in this space

01:08:01.000 --> 01:08:04.000
as the mask
pulls in close to you with a smile.

01:08:04.000 --> 01:08:05.500
The lips don't move,

01:08:05.500 --> 01:08:09.000
but you hear a voice
from all directions in your head.

01:08:09.000 --> 01:08:12.210
A comforting voice.
A welcoming voice.

01:08:15.000 --> 01:08:17.000
"My champion.

01:08:17.000 --> 01:08:21.580
"Vax'ildan.
You've come to me at last."

01:08:24.720 --> 01:08:27.410
LIAM: This was always
supposed to happen, wasn't it?

01:08:29.000 --> 01:08:32.000
MATT: "There is destiny,

01:08:32.000 --> 01:08:36.000
"but you still guide your path
where it must go.

01:08:36.000 --> 01:08:39.000
"Especially you, fate-touched.

01:08:39.000 --> 01:08:44.020
"You're one of the few 
that bends threads near and around you.

01:08:44.020 --> 01:08:47.000
"That's why you're 
so interesting to me."

01:08:55.000 --> 01:09:00.000
LIAM: (haltingly)
I give myself willingly to you

01:09:00.000 --> 01:09:04.569
for the bargain that was struck,

01:09:04.569 --> 01:09:08.000
although I question
if the bargain

01:09:08.000 --> 01:09:12.000
was just the surface reason
for this to happen.

01:09:15.590 --> 01:09:19.740
MATT: "When one such as your...

01:09:19.740 --> 01:09:25.430
"unique essence walks these realms,

01:09:25.430 --> 01:09:29.000
"do not think I am
the only one to take interest.

01:09:29.000 --> 01:09:31.689
"And do not think you are
the only one, either.

01:09:34.000 --> 01:09:37.000
"But I was there
to seize the opportunity when it arose,

01:09:37.000 --> 01:09:41.000
"and as such, you are now mine.

01:09:41.000 --> 01:09:46.000
"And I know that you hate me.
I know that you fear me.

01:09:46.000 --> 01:09:48.000
"Most do.

01:09:48.000 --> 01:09:51.390
"But only because they are
without understanding.

01:09:52.840 --> 01:09:57.000
"Without death, life has no meaning.

01:09:57.000 --> 01:09:59.590
"Finality drives change,

01:09:59.590 --> 01:10:01.840
"innovation,

01:10:01.840 --> 01:10:04.030
"greatness.

01:10:04.030 --> 01:10:06.000
"It is the end that I bring

01:10:06.000 --> 01:10:13.000
"that drives all of your gracious creations
of this land

01:10:13.000 --> 01:10:17.470
"to make the world better than we did,
than those before me did."

01:10:21.000 --> 01:10:24.000
LIAM: I would learn your ways.

01:10:24.000 --> 01:10:27.000
I will learn your purpose.

01:10:27.000 --> 01:10:29.000
And I will serve.

01:10:32.000 --> 01:10:35.450
MATT: "Then understand
the wholeness of what it is you serve

01:10:35.450 --> 01:10:39.000
"and what you represent, champion.

01:10:39.000 --> 01:10:43.000
"Even after death, the soul is carried
to another purpose,

01:10:43.000 --> 01:10:47.560
"but it is that transition
where it is at its most vulnerable.

01:10:49.740 --> 01:10:55.000
"It is my charge, my gift--
your gift, now--

01:10:55.000 --> 01:10:58.550
"to safeguard that beautiful moment.

01:11:01.000 --> 01:11:04.000
"There are those that find
the immortal soul

01:11:04.000 --> 01:11:09.580
"one of the most pure
and powerful means

01:11:09.580 --> 01:11:14.950
"of energy, of sourced power,
in this world.

01:11:16.000 --> 01:11:18.000
"That is an abomination.

01:11:18.000 --> 01:11:23.000
"There are those
that wish to halt the process

01:11:23.000 --> 01:11:27.590
"and live eternally
in some form of undeath or the other.

01:11:27.590 --> 01:11:30.000
"That is an abomination.

01:11:34.000 --> 01:11:36.000
"There is also a difference

01:11:36.000 --> 01:11:40.000
"between bending your thread 
around destiny, fate-touched,

01:11:40.000 --> 01:11:42.000
"and perverting the thread entirely,

01:11:42.000 --> 01:11:44.000
"for death is sacred.

01:11:44.000 --> 01:11:48.000
"But not all deaths are destined,
in that moment.

01:11:48.000 --> 01:11:52.000
"Some destinies require one
to endure beyond the moment.

01:11:52.000 --> 01:11:57.000
"To meet that moment many times
before the final death is to come.

01:11:57.000 --> 01:11:59.000
"We must guide these moments
across this web."

01:11:59.000 --> 01:12:02.000
And as she sweeps her hand out.

01:12:02.000 --> 01:12:04.270
Where she holds you in one palm,
another hand reaches out,

01:12:04.270 --> 01:12:08.000
and the entire web of threads
just glows below you

01:12:08.000 --> 01:12:11.000
in this curling wave
out into infinity, into the horizons,

01:12:11.000 --> 01:12:14.000
endless, to each side of you and beyond.

01:12:18.000 --> 01:12:22.000
"So, to bend destiny, 
to bend these fates,

01:12:22.000 --> 01:12:25.000
"is within our sphere of influence.

01:12:27.000 --> 01:12:30.000
"It's those that find a way
to cheat this destiny,

01:12:30.000 --> 01:12:34.000
"halt the progression,

01:12:34.000 --> 01:12:38.000
"corrupt their thread to the point
it sickens those around them.

01:12:38.000 --> 01:12:40.000
"Undeath, wayward necromancy.

01:12:40.000 --> 01:12:44.000
"Perversion
of the sanctity of the cycle,

01:12:44.000 --> 01:12:46.000
"of our very domain, is an atrocity

01:12:46.000 --> 01:12:51.000
"and must be stopped 
and stamped out.

01:12:54.000 --> 01:12:58.000
"That is our cause.

01:12:58.000 --> 01:13:00.640
"Your cause, now.

01:13:02.320 --> 01:13:04.160
"Do you still accept this gift?"

01:13:06.000 --> 01:13:07.630
LIAM: (whispering) I do.

01:13:10.000 --> 01:13:14.780
MATT: "You, Vax'ildan.
I've had my eye on you for some time."

01:13:16.000 --> 01:13:20.000
And the smile curls
into this much wider smile.

01:13:20.000 --> 01:13:25.000
To the point it seems 
somewhat perturbing.

01:13:25.000 --> 01:13:31.000
"Your dual nature:
rushing prematurely towards your end,

01:13:31.000 --> 01:13:34.000
"wantonly throwing your life
before the flames,

01:13:34.000 --> 01:13:37.000
"only to pull away
in those last moments.

01:13:37.000 --> 01:13:39.000
"Instinct.

01:13:39.000 --> 01:13:45.000
"You test your path constantly,
without knowing

01:13:45.000 --> 01:13:48.850
"you've been preparing 
for this mantle your entire life.

01:13:51.000 --> 01:13:54.000
"My beautiful champion."

01:13:56.000 --> 01:13:59.000
The smile subsides.

01:13:59.000 --> 01:14:05.000
The face goes stone.
Lack of expression. Blank.

01:14:05.000 --> 01:14:08.000
The hand pulls back
and you now can see

01:14:08.000 --> 01:14:10.000
the full immensity of her size.

01:14:10.000 --> 01:14:12.770
Her body infinitely long, 
looking down

01:14:12.770 --> 01:14:15.000
before it disappears 
into darkness.

01:14:15.000 --> 01:14:17.000
And as you look up,

01:14:17.000 --> 01:14:18.500
suddenly the mask
is there before you,

01:14:18.500 --> 01:14:22.000
but normal, human-sized.

01:14:22.000 --> 01:14:24.000
You're no longer in her hand.

01:14:24.000 --> 01:14:25.870
You're standing on a floor,

01:14:25.870 --> 01:14:29.810
a floor of the same white,
ice-bone type substance

01:14:29.810 --> 01:14:35.000
that the interior of Raven's Crest
seems to be built from.

01:14:35.000 --> 01:14:38.000
And for a brief moment,
you see before you

01:14:38.000 --> 01:14:43.000
the woman before the god,
the ascended mortal,

01:14:43.000 --> 01:14:46.000
no larger than you.

01:14:46.000 --> 01:14:48.000
From the hair
that topples down the sides,

01:14:48.000 --> 01:14:52.990
the hand reaches up
and grabs the mask and pulls it away.

01:14:54.750 --> 01:14:57.000
Beneath the mask you see

01:14:57.000 --> 01:15:00.430
a very beautiful, 
very sad-looking woman.

01:15:02.000 --> 01:15:07.000
But her eyes 
are cold and red in the iris.

01:15:07.000 --> 01:15:10.850
Her skin flawless and smooth.
White, pale, sunless.

01:15:12.700 --> 01:15:15.000
Her brows thinned and furrowed.

01:15:15.000 --> 01:15:18.000
She steps forward
and touches the side of your face.

01:15:22.000 --> 01:15:26.720
"There are those
who will be frightened of you.

01:15:28.000 --> 01:15:31.890
"But know what we do

01:15:31.890 --> 01:15:35.160
"is one of the most important gifts 
of all."

01:15:37.000 --> 01:15:39.000
And she grabs your head, 
pulls you down,

01:15:39.000 --> 01:15:41.940
and kisses you on the forehead.

01:15:41.940 --> 01:15:46.000
At which point, suddenly your lungs 
fill once again with searing white pain.

01:15:46.000 --> 01:15:48.000
You find yourself scrambling about,

01:15:48.000 --> 01:15:51.760
instinctually spilling out liquid
all around you,

01:15:51.760 --> 01:15:55.500
and you finally (coughs) come out 
on top of the communion pool.

01:15:55.500 --> 01:15:58.500
Your eyes open and you can see 
just red crimson pouring in your vision.

01:15:58.500 --> 01:16:03.000
You rub it out
and you're in the chamber alone.

01:16:03.000 --> 01:16:06.000
Eyes wide, swimming around,

01:16:06.000 --> 01:16:11.000
you can see the figures on the side
come to the edges.

01:16:11.000 --> 01:16:12.610
They all bow.

01:16:14.160 --> 01:16:16.000
The figure that led you in

01:16:16.000 --> 01:16:19.000
stands at the mouth of this pool
where you entered.

01:16:19.000 --> 01:16:22.500
She's smiling.
She has her hand extended.

01:16:22.500 --> 01:16:24.000
LIAM: I take it.

01:16:24.000 --> 01:16:26.500
MATT: She lifts you out of the pool.

01:16:26.500 --> 01:16:28.000
One of the other figures runs up

01:16:28.000 --> 01:16:30.700
and takes
one of the dark robes that they have

01:16:30.700 --> 01:16:32.200
and pulls it off around them,

01:16:32.200 --> 01:16:37.000
revealing just a simple
dark blue and black outfit beneath.

01:16:37.000 --> 01:16:41.000
Still wearing the veil,
but wraps the dark robe around you

01:16:41.000 --> 01:16:45.000
as the liquid is now
back to its freezing cold sensation.

01:16:45.000 --> 01:16:48.000
Your teeth are chattering.

01:16:48.000 --> 01:16:51.000
They lead you back
to the door you entered,

01:16:51.000 --> 01:16:54.500
down the stairs,
and into the central chamber

01:16:54.500 --> 01:16:56.000
where both Keyleth and Pike await.

01:16:56.000 --> 01:17:00.000
You guys turn and see,
descending the stairs,

01:17:00.000 --> 01:17:02.470
being flanked, essentially,

01:17:02.470 --> 01:17:05.000
by two of the members
of the Raven's Crest,

01:17:05.000 --> 01:17:09.000
both of the shoulders
with the dark robe wrapped around

01:17:09.000 --> 01:17:14.000
a very cold and somewhat
freaked-out looking Vax'ildan,

01:17:14.000 --> 01:17:16.620
who has smeared red across his face.

01:17:16.620 --> 01:17:21.000
His hair is thick
with viscous crimson liquid.

01:17:21.000 --> 01:17:24.370
ASHLEY: I run over.
You okay?

01:17:24.370 --> 01:17:28.030
MARISHA: I stand
at the bottom of the stairs and I watch.

01:17:28.030 --> 01:17:31.000
LIAM: (hoarsely)
I got answers in there,

01:17:31.000 --> 01:17:33.770
but they led to more questions.

01:17:33.770 --> 01:17:37.000
What am I to do
with those questions?

01:17:37.000 --> 01:17:39.000
MATT: The woman
who had led you in there

01:17:39.000 --> 01:17:41.000
smiles and says,

01:17:41.000 --> 01:17:43.000
"That is the nature of death.

01:17:43.000 --> 01:17:46.000
"We can't have all the answers,
my friend.

01:17:46.000 --> 01:17:49.000
"It is the pursuit of those answers
that drives us.

01:17:52.180 --> 01:17:54.000
"Do you trust Her?"

01:17:57.000 --> 01:17:58.560
LIAM: I do.

01:17:58.560 --> 01:18:02.000
MATT: "Then perhaps
you'll find those answers one day."

01:18:07.510 --> 01:18:08.860
LIAM: Thank you.

01:18:09.560 --> 01:18:11.300
MATT: "Thank you."

01:18:14.000 --> 01:18:16.500
They pull the robe off

01:18:16.500 --> 01:18:18.470
and they all head
back up into the chamber,

01:18:18.470 --> 01:18:21.000
leaving you all there
in the room alone.

01:18:21.000 --> 01:18:23.090
MARISHA: I walk over.

01:18:26.000 --> 01:18:29.270
ASHLEY: (whispering)
I'm just going to stay where he is.

01:18:32.000 --> 01:18:34.540
LIAM: I'm shell-shocked.

01:18:40.710 --> 01:18:42.710
MARISHA: You look well.

01:18:45.000 --> 01:18:48.000
LIAM: It's going to be good.

01:18:48.000 --> 01:18:53.000
MARISHA: What did she say to you?
Did she speak to you at all?

01:18:55.000 --> 01:18:57.530
LIAM: (whispering) Yeah.

01:18:59.530 --> 01:19:01.480
MARISHA: (shocked laugh)

01:19:01.480 --> 01:19:03.300
LIAM: Do you speak?

01:19:05.000 --> 01:19:07.000
ASHLEY: Yes?
LIAM: To her?

01:19:10.000 --> 01:19:12.750
ASHLEY: Sometimes.

01:19:14.000 --> 01:19:16.560
LIAM: Do you understand?

01:19:20.000 --> 01:19:25.000
ASHLEY: I don't think
any of us can fully understand.

01:19:28.000 --> 01:19:32.000
I think, if we did,
then we would be gods.

01:19:38.000 --> 01:19:40.350
MARISHA: Do you believe?

01:19:43.000 --> 01:19:50.160
LIAM: Yeah. Yeah. I do.

01:19:50.160 --> 01:19:56.850
I don't know what...
I don't know why, but...

01:20:00.000 --> 01:20:04.000
this was fate.

01:20:06.000 --> 01:20:10.000
MARISHA: Is that what she told you,
that this was fate?

01:20:10.000 --> 01:20:12.000
LIAM: No.

01:20:14.000 --> 01:20:16.000
I know it here.

01:20:20.000 --> 01:20:21.320
MARISHA: Why?

01:20:26.730 --> 01:20:29.820
LIAM: Everything has led to it.

01:20:31.350 --> 01:20:35.990
You and I wouldn't be standing here
if my sister hadn't stolen a broom.

01:20:37.540 --> 01:20:39.850
Where's the sense in that?

01:20:39.850 --> 01:20:41.850
What else is it?

01:20:46.420 --> 01:20:53.000
I teleported into the stomach of a dragon
with a gnome

01:20:53.000 --> 01:20:56.000
and I am still standing here.

01:20:56.000 --> 01:20:58.000
If it is not fate, what is it?

01:21:04.000 --> 01:21:07.000
MARISHA: I don't know.

01:21:07.000 --> 01:21:12.700
As someone
who is constantly questioning mine,

01:21:12.700 --> 01:21:15.160
I don't think
I'm the right person to ask.

01:21:17.000 --> 01:21:19.000
But I do know one thing--

01:21:21.000 --> 01:21:24.000
and I grab his hands--

01:21:25.440 --> 01:21:31.000
you were amazing
and talented and special

01:21:31.000 --> 01:21:34.000
way before she found you.

01:21:37.000 --> 01:21:41.000
If anything,
we can call her a god.

01:21:41.000 --> 01:21:45.000
We can also call her
a great opportunist.

01:21:49.000 --> 01:21:52.420
She didn't give you
anything special.

01:21:54.000 --> 01:21:56.760
The Vax that I see before me right now

01:21:56.760 --> 01:22:01.000
is no different than the Vax
that I saw before me ten minutes ago.

01:22:10.000 --> 01:22:11.500
I'm not saying

01:22:11.500 --> 01:22:15.000
that what you experienced
wasn't real and true.

01:22:15.000 --> 01:22:18.780
I believe you whole-heartedly.

01:22:24.000 --> 01:22:27.000
LIAM: This is real.

01:22:27.000 --> 01:22:29.000
This was meant to be.

01:22:32.000 --> 01:22:35.000
And I am on board.

01:22:35.000 --> 01:22:39.800
MARISHA: Is it what was meant to be
or what you just really wanted?

01:22:39.800 --> 01:22:42.000
And it found you?

01:22:43.060 --> 01:22:46.890
LIAM: (disbelieving laughter)

01:22:46.890 --> 01:22:49.890
It is not what I wanted.

01:22:56.000 --> 01:23:02.000
Thank you. Thank you.

01:23:02.000 --> 01:23:05.270
I need to see my sister.

01:23:06.770 --> 01:23:09.000
And I head off towards the exit.

01:23:09.000 --> 01:23:12.000
MATT: You guys make your way
to the outside of Raven's Crest.

01:23:12.000 --> 01:23:13.500
The doors open once again.

01:23:13.500 --> 01:23:16.000
The figure that let you in
is waiting for you, opens the door.

01:23:16.000 --> 01:23:17.500
As you see the doors open--

01:23:17.500 --> 01:23:20.000
LAURA: I jump up immediately.
I've bitten off all my fingernails.

01:23:20.000 --> 01:23:23.000
MATT: (laughs) Rushing down the stairs,
you see Pike, Keyleth,

01:23:23.000 --> 01:23:26.000
and your brother

01:23:26.000 --> 01:23:28.410
in a little better spirits
than when he first entered,

01:23:28.410 --> 01:23:31.000
if a little damper and redder.

01:23:31.000 --> 01:23:33.500
LAURA: Is that blood?
Is that blood all over you?

01:23:33.500 --> 01:23:35.000
Did she hurt you?

01:23:35.000 --> 01:23:37.000
LIAM: It was really weird, 
but it's fine.

01:23:37.000 --> 01:23:39.000
I told you I'd be fine, 
and I'm fine.

01:23:39.000 --> 01:23:41.000
LAURA: I get out a rag
and I start wiping everything off.

01:23:41.000 --> 01:23:44.000
(laughs) You're alive, though.

01:23:44.000 --> 01:23:46.000
LIAM: (laughs) Yeah,
doesn't make any sense, does it.

01:23:46.000 --> 01:23:47.500
LAURA: (laughing) Oh my god,
are you stronger now?

01:23:47.500 --> 01:23:49.000
Are you so strong?

01:23:49.000 --> 01:23:51.000
LIAM: I think I might be
a bit weaker, actually.

01:23:51.000 --> 01:23:54.000
LAURA: Oh, I don't believe it.
LIAM: I have the jelly-legs.

01:23:54.000 --> 01:23:56.500
LAURA: (laughs) Do you want
to ride Trinket for a while?

01:23:56.500 --> 01:23:58.000
LIAM: Could I?
LAURA: Yes!

01:23:58.000 --> 01:24:01.000
LIAM: He's going to get sticky.
LAURA: No, he loves the taste of blood.

01:24:01.000 --> 01:24:03.360
MATT: (sad moaning)

01:24:03.360 --> 01:24:05.500
LAURA: (laughs) Oh, Trinket.

01:24:05.500 --> 01:24:07.000
MATT: Trinket comes over

01:24:07.000 --> 01:24:09.860
and begrudgingly lowers himself
so you can climb on.

01:24:09.860 --> 01:24:11.500
LIAM: No, don't lick.
Don't lick.

01:24:11.500 --> 01:24:14.000
LAURA: He's very light.
Scrawny, scrawny, scrawny.

01:24:14.000 --> 01:24:16.000
LIAM: But don't lick, Trink, please.

01:24:16.000 --> 01:24:18.390
MATT: (grunts)

01:24:18.390 --> 01:24:20.000
ASHLEY: Just one kiss?
One little lick?

01:24:20.000 --> 01:24:22.000
LAURA: (laughs)

01:24:22.000 --> 01:24:25.000
LIAM: Later, buddy. Later.

01:24:25.000 --> 01:24:28.000
LIAM: I climb on top.

01:24:28.000 --> 01:24:32.000
LAURA: Aren't you glad
you got out of the Pokeball for this?

01:24:32.000 --> 01:24:36.990
LIAM: I give a quick look
back at my friends.

01:24:40.000 --> 01:24:42.000
and then I take a nap on Trinket.

01:24:42.000 --> 01:24:44.230
MATT: Okay.

01:24:44.230 --> 01:24:48.000
LAURA: So everything's good, then.
He's good? Everything's fine?

01:24:48.000 --> 01:24:53.000
ASHLEY: I think so... I mean, it's--
it was very different,

01:24:53.000 --> 01:24:55.000
but that doesn't mean it's wrong.

01:24:55.000 --> 01:24:58.000
LAURA: He talked to her?
MARISHA: He talked to her.

01:24:58.000 --> 01:24:59.500
LAURA: Were you there?
ASHLEY: No.

01:24:59.500 --> 01:25:01.000
MARISHA: They didn't let us 
in the room.

01:25:01.000 --> 01:25:03.140
LAURA: Oh. Well, I'll find out.

01:25:03.140 --> 01:25:04.450
MARISHA: We stood outside.

01:25:04.450 --> 01:25:07.910
He didn't talk much about it.
Maybe you can find out more.

01:25:07.910 --> 01:25:12.000
All he said was
that he knows that this was fate.

01:25:12.000 --> 01:25:14.000
LAURA: Well, good.
He has a purpose.

01:25:14.000 --> 01:25:15.670
ASHLEY: Yeah.

01:25:15.670 --> 01:25:18.750
MARISHA: Oh. Yeah.
Well, that's one way of looking at it.

01:25:18.750 --> 01:25:19.800
