01:35:10.580 --> 01:35:12.000
(laughter)

01:35:12.000 --> 01:35:13.500
MATT: Deidre goes,

01:35:13.500 --> 01:35:17.280
"(laughs) You silly, tiny man--

01:35:17.280 --> 01:35:20.000
"No, seriously. We have a price 
agreed upon. Pay it."

01:35:20.000 --> 01:35:22.000
TRAVIS: Yeah, no, I got it.
I got 50 gold of my own.

01:35:22.000 --> 01:35:25.660
SAM: All right. 20 from me, 
50 from him. We'll take them both.

01:35:25.660 --> 01:35:28.000
MATT: "Ooh, all up front? All right.
It'll be ready for you shortly."

01:35:28.000 --> 01:35:29.500
She takes the coin.

01:35:29.500 --> 01:35:31.160
"Thank you for the patronage.

01:35:31.160 --> 01:35:33.000
"Return here in about...
ooh, an hour,

01:35:33.000 --> 01:35:35.500
"and the hat
shall be prepared for you, sir--

01:35:35.500 --> 01:35:37.000
"what's your name?"

01:35:37.000 --> 01:35:39.000
SAM: My name's Scanlan Shorthalt.

01:35:39.000 --> 01:35:42.000
MATT: "Scanlan Shorthalt.
All right, come soon."

01:35:42.000 --> 01:35:44.000
SAM: See you soon.

01:35:44.000 --> 01:35:47.000
TRAVIS: Can I hit my head
on the doorway on the way out?

01:35:47.000 --> 01:35:50.000
MATT: (shoomp)
LAURA AND MARISHA: (laugh)

01:35:50.000 --> 01:35:52.000
MATT: (creak) You have to
kind of pull it out.

01:35:52.000 --> 01:35:53.500
Yeah. You leave a nice big groove.

01:35:53.500 --> 01:35:55.000
TRAVIS: It is nice, right?
MATT: Yeah.

01:35:55.000 --> 01:35:56.800
TRAVIS: Okay, good.

01:35:56.800 --> 01:36:00.500
MATT: (laughs) All right,
eventually you all gather again

01:36:00.500 --> 01:36:06.000
back at the hall of the Slayer's Take.

01:36:06.000 --> 01:36:09.000
You guys have just settled in

01:36:09.000 --> 01:36:13.190
and are free to continue
any discussion you like

01:36:13.190 --> 01:36:19.000
as you see Scanlan and Grog come in.

01:36:19.000 --> 01:36:22.620
Say, you've since retrieved your hat

01:36:22.620 --> 01:36:26.000
with your various
wonderfully-crafted accoutrements.

01:36:26.000 --> 01:36:29.000
TRAVIS: 'Sup, bitches.
LAURA: Wow.

01:36:29.000 --> 01:36:30.500
SAM: Look at that.
ASHLEY: Whoa.

01:36:30.500 --> 01:36:32.000
TRAVIS: What happened?
SAM: Look at that.

01:36:32.000 --> 01:36:34.000
ASHLEY: (gasps) Ohh...
TRAVIS: I know, right? Wait for it.

01:36:34.000 --> 01:36:36.000
LIAM: (laughs)

01:36:36.000 --> 01:36:41.000
LAURA: Whoa. Grog, you're so monstrous.
ASHLEY: What? Grog, that is so scary.

01:36:41.000 --> 01:36:42.500
MARISHA: That's like
another 12 inches to you.

01:36:42.500 --> 01:36:44.000
TRAVIS: I know.
MARISHA: You look so tall.

01:36:44.000 --> 01:36:47.000
TRAVIS: It, like, changes
my whole battle strategy.

01:36:47.000 --> 01:36:49.450
I'm now literally
the point of the spear.

01:36:49.450 --> 01:36:54.050
ASHLEY: (gasps) You're so scary.
TALIESIN: How have we lived with this idiot?

01:36:54.050 --> 01:36:57.100
TRAVIS: (laughs) I'm a sea monster!
ASHLEY: (roars)

01:36:57.100 --> 01:37:00.160
TRAVIS: I'm like
the most wicked narwhal of all time!

01:37:00.160 --> 01:37:02.600
Give me a pool! (laughs)

01:37:02.600 --> 01:37:05.000
ASHLEY: Can I try it on?
TRAVIS: Yeah, you want to?

01:37:05.000 --> 01:37:07.000
TRAVIS: (laughing)
I put it on Pike's head.

01:37:07.000 --> 01:37:08.830
ASHLEY: Whoa, it's so heavy.

01:37:08.830 --> 01:37:11.790
(all but Taliesin laugh)
TALIESIN: What is the world coming to?

01:37:11.790 --> 01:37:13.220
TRAVIS: Is it as tall as she is?

01:37:13.220 --> 01:37:16.000
MATT: You can see
the bottom of her mouth.

01:37:16.000 --> 01:37:18.000
ASHLEY: Oh, Grog.

01:37:18.000 --> 01:37:20.000
TRAVIS: Oh, yeah, look.

01:37:20.000 --> 01:37:23.000
Wait, turn around 180 degrees
and then run as fast as you can.

01:37:23.000 --> 01:37:25.000
MARISHA: Oh, yeah, go!
Go! Go! Go, Pike! Go, go!

01:37:25.000 --> 01:37:27.000
LAURA: (clapping) Go, Pike!
Go, Pike! Go, Pike!

01:37:27.000 --> 01:37:29.000
MATT: Okay, make a perception check.

01:37:29.000 --> 01:37:33.310
TALIESIN: (groans)
EVERYONE ELSE: (laughs)

01:37:36.510 --> 01:37:38.000
ASHLEY: 9.

01:37:38.000 --> 01:37:40.000
MATT: 9. You go running
straight out of the door--

01:37:40.000 --> 01:37:41.500
LAURA: No!

01:37:41.500 --> 01:37:43.620
MATT: You guys are like,
"Oh. No, Pike!"

01:37:43.620 --> 01:37:46.000
She's already out the door,
over the stairs

01:37:46.000 --> 01:37:48.000
(repeated thuds),
outside of the hall.

01:37:48.000 --> 01:37:49.500
(sounds of dismay)

01:37:49.500 --> 01:37:51.500
TRAVIS and LAURA: Oh no!

01:37:51.500 --> 01:37:53.000
ASHLEY: I'm okay!

01:37:53.000 --> 01:37:54.500
MATT: You guys rush out to go catch her

01:37:54.500 --> 01:37:57.130
and the helmet is actually
embedded partway into the ground

01:37:57.130 --> 01:37:58.770
and she's kind of--

01:37:58.770 --> 01:38:00.000
MARISHA: Yeah!

01:38:00.000 --> 01:38:04.000
MATT: And she's just laughing.

01:38:04.000 --> 01:38:06.000
ASHLEY: (laughing) Grog,
get me out of this helmet.

01:38:06.000 --> 01:38:08.000
TRAVIS: I pick her up by the feet.

01:38:08.000 --> 01:38:10.470
TRAVIS: That was excellent. (giggles)

01:38:10.470 --> 01:38:13.850
ASHLEY: As he's holding me up like that
I try to stab him with it.

01:38:15.710 --> 01:38:19.000
TRAVIS: I yank it off of her head
and put her back on the ground.

01:38:19.000 --> 01:38:21.230
LIAM: Vax has been
laughing hysterically,

01:38:21.230 --> 01:38:24.000
giggle fits,
clutching his ribs the entire time.

01:38:24.000 --> 01:38:27.000
And then is there
any of the staff here?

01:38:27.000 --> 01:38:29.000
Anyone that's here? Anyone else?

01:38:29.000 --> 01:38:33.000
MATT: You haven't seen Mertin.
Vanessa doesn't seem to have left.

01:38:33.000 --> 01:38:34.500
LIAM: What about underlings?

01:38:34.500 --> 01:38:36.000
MATT: I mean, there are

01:38:36.000 --> 01:38:37.500
a few individuals here
that are part of the guildhall.

01:38:37.500 --> 01:38:41.000
The hierarchy here
is more like the few that run it,

01:38:41.000 --> 01:38:43.000
and then everyone else
comes and goes as they please.

01:38:43.000 --> 01:38:45.580
LIAM: Yeah, yeah, come here, you.
Do you have a tub?

01:38:45.580 --> 01:38:48.660
Do you have a bath? Look at me.
Do you have a bath? I need a bath.

01:38:48.660 --> 01:38:50.000
MATT: "You look pretty rough."

01:38:50.000 --> 01:38:51.000
LIAM: Yeah?

01:38:51.000 --> 01:38:52.500
MATT: "Yeah. We could--

01:38:52.500 --> 01:38:54.720
"we got a washroom in the back,
if you need it."

01:38:54.720 --> 01:38:58.000
LIAM: Is it hot?
I feel like I need it to be hot.

01:38:58.000 --> 01:39:00.000
MATT: "You get what you get. 
It's water, buddy."

01:39:00.000 --> 01:39:01.500
LIAM: Okay.
That's perfect, thank you.

01:39:01.500 --> 01:39:03.000
Grog, put that hat on again.

01:39:03.000 --> 01:39:08.000
TRAVIS: Oh, yeah, hold on. (foomp)
LIAM: (laughs hysterically)

01:39:08.000 --> 01:39:09.500
LIAM: All the way down the hall
to take a bath.

01:39:09.500 --> 01:39:11.000
SAM: It's crazy. Did you guys
get him drunk or something?

01:39:11.000 --> 01:39:12.500
TALIESIN: I don't know
what you people did, but...

01:39:12.500 --> 01:39:14.000
ASHLEY: Well, he just...

01:39:14.000 --> 01:39:15.500
TRAVIS: People respond to fear differently.

01:39:15.500 --> 01:39:17.000
SAM: I guess so.
LAURA: He's gone insane.

01:39:17.000 --> 01:39:18.500
MARISHA: He might have saw
the face of a god.

01:39:18.500 --> 01:39:21.920
SAM: Whatever.
TRAVIS: He did?

01:39:21.920 --> 01:39:23.470
MARISHA: Yeah.

01:39:23.470 --> 01:39:25.500
ASHLEY: Yeah. The head of--

01:39:25.500 --> 01:39:28.000
TRAVIS: By the way,
why is he covered in bloodbath?

01:39:28.000 --> 01:39:30.000
ASHLEY: I think that was part of the--

01:39:30.000 --> 01:39:32.000
MARISHA: Ritual? Communion?

01:39:32.000 --> 01:39:35.000
ASHLEY: Getting to know his new god.

01:39:35.000 --> 01:39:37.000
TRAVIS: Did he kill a lot of people?

01:39:37.000 --> 01:39:38.500
ASHLEY: Maybe he had to. I don't know.

01:39:38.500 --> 01:39:40.000
TRAVIS: He did?
LAURA: So many, Grog.

01:39:40.000 --> 01:39:42.500
TRAVIS: Oh my god.
LAURA: Yeah. It was a giant battle.

01:39:42.500 --> 01:39:44.300
TRAVIS: Like, how many on two hands?

01:39:44.300 --> 01:39:47.140
LAURA: Like at least this many.

01:39:47.140 --> 01:39:51.000
TRAVIS: That's a legendary amount.
LAURA: That's more than six.

01:39:51.000 --> 01:39:52.200
LAURA: I know.
ASHLEY: Yeah.

01:39:52.200 --> 01:39:55.000
LIAM: Somewhere deep in the building,
far away:

01:39:55.000 --> 01:40:00.000
LIAM: This is not hot!

01:40:00.000 --> 01:40:02.000
MATT: The gruff individual chuckles.

01:40:02.000 --> 01:40:05.000
"Heh. It never is."

01:40:07.500 --> 01:40:09.000
I need you to make a tinkering check.

01:40:09.000 --> 01:40:10.000
TALIESIN: Okay.

01:40:10.000 --> 01:40:13.000
I'm sitting with my tea and my tools,
trying to ignore these people.

01:40:13.000 --> 01:40:15.060
LAURA: Can I heat water up
in the fireplace?

01:40:15.060 --> 01:40:16.620
MATT: Yeah, yeah,
it'll take you a little while.

01:40:16.620 --> 01:40:19.000
TALIESIN: Please don't explode.

01:40:19.000 --> 01:40:21.000
SAM: When I delivered
the materials to him--

01:40:21.000 --> 01:40:24.000
TALIESIN: Oh, Jesus H. Fucking Christ.
MARISHA: Oh no, Taliesin...

01:40:24.000 --> 01:40:26.000
SAM: Could I have inspired him at all,
when I delivered the materials?

01:40:26.000 --> 01:40:27.500
TALIESIN: Please.
MATT: Sure.

01:40:27.500 --> 01:40:30.000
SAM: All right.
MARISHA: Please inspire.

01:40:30.000 --> 01:40:33.320
SAM: I will inspire--
oh my god, it's not even worth it.

01:40:33.320 --> 01:40:36.750
TALIESIN: (muffled) Please inspire.
Do it. Do it, you bloody gnome!

01:40:36.750 --> 01:40:38.460
SAM: Okay.
So when I delivered everything,

01:40:38.460 --> 01:40:42.000
I just sang him a little song
to inspire him. And I sang,

01:40:42.000 --> 01:40:46.000
SAM: (singing) 
Percy's gun, won't you come

01:40:46.000 --> 01:40:49.630
and kill up all the dragons?

01:40:49.630 --> 01:40:55.500
(others join in) Percy's gun,
won't you come, won't you come?

01:40:55.500 --> 01:40:57.000
ASHLEY AND LIAM: Percy's gun!

01:40:57.000 --> 01:40:59.000
(laughter)

01:40:59.000 --> 01:41:01.000
MATT: Oh my god.
All right, take your d10.

01:41:01.000 --> 01:41:02.500
LAURA: Ten! Ten! Ten!
LIAM: Do it! Do it!

01:41:02.500 --> 01:41:04.000
MARISHA: Oh my god, it's a 10!
TALIESIN: Better!

01:41:04.000 --> 01:41:05.500
SAM: That was a 10.
TALIESIN: Thank you.

01:41:05.500 --> 01:41:07.000
MARISHA: I get excited. Sorry.
LIAM: Pretty good song.

01:41:07.000 --> 01:41:09.500
TALIESIN: Proficiency,
tinkering, plus the--

01:41:09.500 --> 01:41:11.000
MATT: Well, your proficiency
is what you get with the roll

01:41:11.000 --> 01:41:12.000
and then it's your dex bonus.

01:41:12.000 --> 01:41:17.000
TALIESIN: Okay, so proficiency,
dex, okay, thank you, god.

01:41:17.000 --> 01:41:19.000
TALIESIN: (muttering) That's 11...
LIAM: (hums Black Hole Sun)

01:41:19.000 --> 01:41:21.000
TALIESIN: 23.
MATT: 23. What did you roll naturally?

01:41:21.000 --> 01:41:22.500
SAM: A 2.
TALIESIN: 2.

01:41:22.500 --> 01:41:24.000
LIAM: (laughs)
LAURA: Whoa.

01:41:24.000 --> 01:41:25.860
SAM: Plus 10.
MATT: Ah.

01:41:25.860 --> 01:41:27.000
TALIESIN AND MARISHA: Plus 10.

01:41:27.000 --> 01:41:29.000
TALIESIN: Made it 12.
MATT: Wow. All righty.

01:41:29.000 --> 01:41:31.000
TALIESIN: It's not complicated,
but I've got a good design,

01:41:31.000 --> 01:41:34.000
and it has two nifty things.

01:41:34.000 --> 01:41:35.500
MATT: What are the nifty things?

01:41:35.500 --> 01:41:37.000
SAM: Fingers.

01:41:37.000 --> 01:41:38.500
TALIESIN: It doesn't actually
have fingers.

01:41:38.500 --> 01:41:42.000
It's a mitt piece, strap-on,

01:41:42.000 --> 01:41:45.000
it can lock the thumb
and lock the hand

01:41:45.000 --> 01:41:47.000
so you can open it, lock,
close it, lock.

01:41:47.000 --> 01:41:49.000
It's got little flip-locks.

01:41:49.000 --> 01:41:50.000
MATT: Mm-hm.

01:41:50.000 --> 01:41:52.000
TALIESIN: You can detach the hand

01:41:52.000 --> 01:41:54.690
and put a pick spike on
for mining. Like a mining punch.

01:41:54.690 --> 01:41:56.320
LIAM: Is it like Young Frankenstein?

01:41:56.320 --> 01:41:58.000
(mechanical sound effects)

01:41:58.000 --> 01:42:02.500
TALIESIN: It's more Dustin Hoffman "Hook",
but, you know.

01:42:02.500 --> 01:42:04.000
MARISHA: Oh, sure.
LAURA: Oh, that's nice.

01:42:04.000 --> 01:42:05.500
MARISHA: I was thinking
Go-Go-Gadget Finger.

01:42:05.500 --> 01:42:07.000
TALIESIN: Because it's got
the click, pull, click.

01:42:07.000 --> 01:42:10.000
MATT: Right.

01:42:10.000 --> 01:42:11.500
TALIESIN: I can do it
with all these things.

01:42:11.500 --> 01:42:13.000
I can graph it. So.

01:42:13.000 --> 01:42:14.000
MATT: (laughs)

01:42:14.000 --> 01:42:16.000
TALIESIN: Reasonable.
It's not pretty.

01:42:16.000 --> 01:42:17.500
MATT: It takes you a few hours

01:42:17.500 --> 01:42:19.000
and gets you into
the early parts of the evening,

01:42:19.000 --> 01:42:25.000
but you do manage
to go ahead and complete it.

01:42:25.000 --> 01:42:28.000
You manage to get it finished up

01:42:28.000 --> 01:42:31.000
and you're pretty proud of your work,
actually, and you feel--

01:42:31.000 --> 01:42:33.450
the whistle you're still doing
as you do the final bits,

01:42:33.450 --> 01:42:35.000
you realize is the song
that Scanlan sang for you,

01:42:35.000 --> 01:42:36.500
just looping in your head.

01:42:36.500 --> 01:42:38.000
It happened to push you
through your work

01:42:38.000 --> 01:42:40.500
and get your final piece completed.

01:42:40.500 --> 01:42:42.320
TALIESIN: I also carved
a little message inside

01:42:42.320 --> 01:42:45.000
that will not matter
unless it actually becomes pertinent.

01:42:45.000 --> 01:42:48.000
MATT: Okay.

01:42:48.000 --> 01:42:49.780
TALIESIN: You don't get to know
until you ask offscreen.

01:42:49.780 --> 01:42:50.970
SAM: You don't know.
LAURA: (laughs) Ohhh.

01:42:50.970 --> 01:42:52.170
MATT: Okay. I'm excited. Okay.

01:42:52.170 --> 01:42:53.820
MARISHA: That's right, DM.
TRAVIS: That never happens.

01:42:53.820 --> 01:42:58.100
MATT: (laughs) Try me. Okay.
Do you go and deliver it?

01:42:58.100 --> 01:42:59.920
TALIESIN: I do go and deliver it.

01:42:59.920 --> 01:43:03.000
MATT: Okay.
As the sun begins to set in Vasselheim,

01:43:03.000 --> 01:43:05.910
you make your way back over
to the Braving Grounds,

01:43:05.910 --> 01:43:11.000
which as you look across, too,
as the night goes dark,

01:43:11.000 --> 01:43:13.420
the Braving Grounds itself
has a whole different life to it.

01:43:13.420 --> 01:43:18.020
There are so many forges
and smelters going that there's--

01:43:18.020 --> 01:43:20.200
most buildings have
this bright orange glow

01:43:20.200 --> 01:43:22.190
through the ceiling
and these various openings

01:43:22.190 --> 01:43:25.000
where fumes and smoke and exhaust
are sent up

01:43:25.000 --> 01:43:29.000
from the various
production constructs and such.

01:43:29.000 --> 01:43:32.000
It has this very luminescent look
in comparison to a lot of the city.

01:43:32.000 --> 01:43:33.190
It's very interesting.

01:43:33.190 --> 01:43:36.000
It reminds you of the deep,
deep portions of Kraghammer,

01:43:36.000 --> 01:43:41.000
where most of
the actual fire and melted rock

01:43:41.000 --> 01:43:45.000
was being smelted
and gathered and heated.

01:43:45.000 --> 01:43:47.000
So you make your way to the hovel.

01:43:47.000 --> 01:43:50.410
The roof workers are no longer there,
and the door is closed.

01:43:53.380 --> 01:43:58.000
TALIESIN: (knocks) Victor?
I've got your hand.

01:43:59.600 --> 01:44:02.000
MATT: "(muffled) I'm sleeping."

01:44:02.000 --> 01:44:04.000
TALIESIN: Do you want your hand?

01:44:04.000 --> 01:44:06.000
MATT: "(muffled) You want me to sleep?"

01:44:08.000 --> 01:44:10.270
TALIESIN: I don't see why
they're mutually exclusive.

01:44:10.270 --> 01:44:12.000
MARISHA: (laughs)

01:44:12.000 --> 01:44:14.000
MATT: You hear (scraping sound)
a bunch of different locks fiddling.

01:44:14.000 --> 01:44:16.000
(series of clicks) (fwoosh)

01:44:16.000 --> 01:44:18.000
And the door opens
and you see Victor,

01:44:18.000 --> 01:44:20.000
clean-faced for the first time
you've really seen him before,

01:44:20.000 --> 01:44:22.000
and he has a nightcap

01:44:22.000 --> 01:44:23.500
which sort of (foomf)
in front of his face,

01:44:23.500 --> 01:44:25.000
with a little puffball at the end.

01:44:25.000 --> 01:44:26.000
He's like,

01:44:26.000 --> 01:44:29.010
"I told you.
I was trying-- oh! Hey.

01:44:29.010 --> 01:44:32.000
"(hesitantly) Percival?"

01:44:32.000 --> 01:44:34.590
TALIESIN: Yes, that's quite good.
I love your hat.

01:44:34.590 --> 01:44:36.500
MATT: "Thank you.
It's comfy to sleep in."

01:44:36.500 --> 01:44:38.330
TALIESIN: It looks it.
MATT: "Did you bring my hand?"

01:44:38.330 --> 01:44:40.860
TALIESIN: I did. I grabbed your hand
and I will show you.

01:44:40.860 --> 01:44:42.190
It is very special.

01:44:42.190 --> 01:44:43.500
MATT: "Come in! Come in! (grunts)"

01:44:43.500 --> 01:44:45.000
And opens the door.

01:44:45.000 --> 01:44:46.500
You see he's wearing
this long nightgown

01:44:46.500 --> 01:44:48.000
that is covered in patches
and tears in it.

01:44:48.000 --> 01:44:51.000
Most of it
has been turned black through soot,

01:44:51.000 --> 01:44:53.000
but the cap is perfect.
Perfect condition.

01:44:53.000 --> 01:44:55.500
TALIESIN: I have a special
set of pajamas myself, so I understand.

01:44:55.500 --> 01:44:57.000
MATT: "They are comfortable."

01:44:57.000 --> 01:45:01.000
As he walks in,
still bandaged on the arm,

01:45:01.000 --> 01:45:03.000
you can see there's

01:45:03.000 --> 01:45:06.000
a small kettle of tea
set by the small fireplace right there.

01:45:06.000 --> 01:45:08.530
It's a tiny little table
and a tiny little stool

01:45:08.530 --> 01:45:11.000
that he's just kind of
sitting on right there.

01:45:11.000 --> 01:45:13.490
And he goes
and he reaches over for the kettle.

01:45:13.490 --> 01:45:15.370
"(groans)"

01:45:17.690 --> 01:45:19.640
Tries to pick up the cup
and just pours the tea into it.

01:45:19.640 --> 01:45:20.650
TALIESIN: (alarmed stuttering)

01:45:20.650 --> 01:45:23.900
TALIESIN: I'm going to stop
and attach and begin strapping this.

01:45:23.900 --> 01:45:25.000
MATT: "(confused stuttering)"

01:45:25.000 --> 01:45:27.000
TALIESIN: Let me show you. 
It attaches like this.

01:45:27.000 --> 01:45:28.000
MATT: "Ooh."

01:45:28.000 --> 01:45:31.000
TALIESIN: Here are the two switches.
(clicking)

01:45:31.000 --> 01:45:34.000
And for your mine.

01:45:34.000 --> 01:45:36.000
MATT: "Eh? Oh."

01:45:36.000 --> 01:45:37.500
TALIESIN: I grab,
hit the button, twist, pull.

01:45:37.500 --> 01:45:39.680
MATT: "Oh? Eh? I just got that!"

01:45:39.680 --> 01:45:43.000
TALIESIN: And I get the spike
and attach it.

01:45:43.000 --> 01:45:46.000
MATT: "Oh."

01:45:46.000 --> 01:45:48.000
TALIESIN: Remove it,
put the hand back on.

01:45:48.000 --> 01:45:50.000
Tea?

01:45:50.000 --> 01:45:52.990
MATT: (chuckle, click)

01:45:52.990 --> 01:45:58.000
(excited laughter) "Tea?"

01:45:58.000 --> 01:46:01.000
TALIESIN: Sure. Why not?
Always say yes.

01:46:01.000 --> 01:46:04.000
MARISHA: (laughs)

01:46:04.000 --> 01:46:05.500
MATT: "Need another cup. (grunts)"

01:46:05.500 --> 01:46:07.000
He stands up and goes over,

01:46:07.000 --> 01:46:08.500
still holding the kettle
and splashing everywhere,

01:46:08.500 --> 01:46:11.000
and he's flipping through cabinets
and knocking pieces of glass out.

01:46:11.000 --> 01:46:13.000
"Ah! Found it."

01:46:13.000 --> 01:46:15.000
Pulls out another little ceramic cup

01:46:15.000 --> 01:46:22.000
and pours the tea in,
sets it down. (chink, click)

01:46:22.000 --> 01:46:24.000
"(cackles)"

01:46:24.000 --> 01:46:27.000
SAM: (laughs)

01:46:27.000 --> 01:46:30.000
MATT: "To new hands!"
TALIESIN: To new hands.

01:46:30.000 --> 01:46:32.000
SAM: That's a great toast.

01:46:32.000 --> 01:46:35.000
MATT: It is pungent. It is bitter.

01:46:35.000 --> 01:46:38.000
MATT: It has been steeped way too long.
ASHLEY: Gunpowder tea.

01:46:38.000 --> 01:46:41.000
MATT: But it definitely
cleans out the sinuses.

01:46:41.000 --> 01:46:44.290
And there is a hint of gunpowder
to the flavoring.

01:46:44.290 --> 01:46:46.500
You get the sense
that pretty much everything in this room

01:46:46.500 --> 01:46:48.000
is marinated in some way,
shape, or form

01:46:48.000 --> 01:46:50.500
to be flammable.

01:46:50.500 --> 01:46:52.000
TALIESIN: (hoarsely) Victor.

01:46:52.000 --> 01:46:54.000
(laughter)

01:46:54.000 --> 01:46:56.000
MATT: "It can put hair on your balls."

01:46:56.000 --> 01:47:00.000
TALIESIN: Ohhh, probably.

01:47:00.000 --> 01:47:05.000
Has a woman been by
to buy black powder?

01:47:05.000 --> 01:47:09.000
(coughs) Has a woman been by?

01:47:09.000 --> 01:47:12.500
MATT: "Not in, uh, weeks, maybe."

01:47:12.500 --> 01:47:14.000
TALIESIN: Weeks?

01:47:14.000 --> 01:47:15.500
MATT: "Did you make her hand, too?"

01:47:15.500 --> 01:47:20.000
TALIESIN: I did not.
Do you know where she goes?

01:47:20.000 --> 01:47:22.470
MATT: "No. She paid well, though."

01:47:22.470 --> 01:47:24.000
TALIESIN: Did she? What did she pay?

01:47:24.000 --> 01:47:27.000
MATT: "Are you guys in a club now?
How many people want black powder?

01:47:27.000 --> 01:47:29.000
"Tell me! Tell them!
Bring them more.

01:47:29.000 --> 01:47:30.500
"I could use money."

01:47:30.500 --> 01:47:36.000
(others laugh)

01:47:38.000 --> 01:47:44.000
TALIESIN: How much black powder
did she buy, Victor?

01:47:44.000 --> 01:47:50.000
MATT: "Uh... (mutters to himself)"
(click, click)

01:47:50.000 --> 01:47:52.000
TALIESIN: Only counts to two.
I'm so sorry.

01:47:52.000 --> 01:47:55.000
(laughter)

01:47:55.000 --> 01:48:00.970
MATT: "Maybe... 12 hogsheads worth?"

01:48:00.970 --> 01:48:02.780
ASHLEY: Whoa.
TRAVIS AND MARISHA: Oh, shit.

01:48:02.780 --> 01:48:07.000
TALIESIN: Really?
And how often does she come by?

01:48:07.000 --> 01:48:09.000
MATT: "She only come by once."

01:48:09.000 --> 01:48:12.000
TALIESIN: Okay. (sighs)

01:48:14.000 --> 01:48:18.000
Thank you. I'm so pleased.

01:48:18.000 --> 01:48:20.310
I may stop by one last time
before I leave town,

01:48:20.310 --> 01:48:22.000
just to say goodbye. Thank you.

01:48:22.000 --> 01:48:24.000
MATT: "Please do! I have more tea.

01:48:24.000 --> 01:48:30.000
"Many different flavors.
This is, I call, dark roast."

01:48:30.000 --> 01:48:34.000
TALIESIN: It...
certainly scalded something.

01:48:34.000 --> 01:48:38.000
Thank you. That was very lovely
and that was very charming

01:48:38.000 --> 01:48:40.000
and I unfortunately have business in the--

01:48:40.000 --> 01:48:42.000
MATT: "I want to try the other one
before you go."

01:48:42.000 --> 01:48:44.000
TALIESIN: One more
and then I must go, thank you.

01:48:44.000 --> 01:48:47.000
MATT: "(click, creak)
Come on, need this, too."

01:48:47.000 --> 01:48:52.000
TALIESIN: Yes, of course.
MATT: "(creak, click) (cackles)"

01:48:52.000 --> 01:48:55.000
TALIESIN: (uncertain laughter)

01:48:55.000 --> 01:48:59.000
MATT: (thunk) He sticks it 
into the wooden stool and the table.

01:48:59.000 --> 01:49:03.000
Kind of breaks the wood
and snaps it.

01:49:03.000 --> 01:49:06.000
"Oh. (cackles)"

01:49:06.000 --> 01:49:09.000
TALIESIN: Remember
that it's attached to bone.

01:49:09.000 --> 01:49:12.000
You can still break your arm,
so be gentle.

01:49:12.000 --> 01:49:13.500
MATT: "Yes. Thank you!"

01:49:13.500 --> 01:49:15.000
TALIESIN: Thank you. Good night!
Have a lovely evening.

01:49:15.000 --> 01:49:16.260
MATT: "Good night!"
SAM: Aah.

01:49:16.260 --> 01:49:20.500
TALIESIN: Good night.
Aah. Pleasure, as always.

01:49:20.500 --> 01:49:22.000
Thank you.

01:49:22.000 --> 01:49:23.000
MATT: "(slurps)"

01:49:23.000 --> 01:49:25.500
TALIESIN: I leave
in a little bit of a panic.

01:49:25.500 --> 01:49:27.000
MATT: You leave
and he's just sitting there

01:49:27.000 --> 01:49:29.000
staring
at this long chisel point, going,

01:49:29.000 --> 01:49:33.000
"(quiet cackling)"

01:49:33.000 --> 01:49:34.680
SAM: His ring.
MARISHA: (laughs)

01:49:34.680 --> 01:49:38.000
MATT: The door
slowly closes behind you.

01:49:38.000 --> 01:49:39.500
TALIESIN: Yeah.
LIAM: A fighter is born.

01:49:39.500 --> 01:49:41.560
MARISHA: Yes, yeah,
just give him an anime weapon.

01:49:41.560 --> 01:49:45.000
TALIESIN: Yeah, okay.
We're sticking around for a day?

01:49:46.000 --> 01:49:47.500
SAM: I assume so. I don't know.

01:49:47.500 --> 01:49:49.000
We're going to spend the night,
at least.

01:49:49.000 --> 01:49:52.000
TALIESIN: I'm going to take
a long walk before I come back

01:49:52.000 --> 01:49:54.000
and I'm going to walk by
the Raven Queen temple

01:49:54.000 --> 01:49:58.000
and just... peek inside.

01:49:58.000 --> 01:50:02.000
MATT: Okay.
You make your way past the Quad Roads.

01:50:02.000 --> 01:50:06.330
At this point at night
the whole clientele has shifted.

01:50:06.330 --> 01:50:09.300
Most people coming here--
you hear laughter, you hear music.

01:50:09.300 --> 01:50:15.000
The Quad Roads is the New Orleans 
of the town, comparatively.

01:50:15.000 --> 01:50:17.000
It's still nowhere near as rambunctious
as many places you've been,

01:50:17.000 --> 01:50:19.000
but for what seems during the day

01:50:19.000 --> 01:50:23.000
to be a rather dour
and serious business type city,

01:50:23.000 --> 01:50:25.000
the Quad Roads
is where the celebration of humanity hits

01:50:25.000 --> 01:50:26.500
when the evening hours hit.

01:50:26.500 --> 01:50:28.000
So you come by

01:50:28.000 --> 01:50:30.000
and there's some taverns
that are open.

01:50:30.000 --> 01:50:34.000
You see, to a certain extent,

01:50:34.000 --> 01:50:38.000
what even appears to be
an adult entertainment district.

01:50:38.000 --> 01:50:40.000
LAURA: (laughs sarcastically)

01:50:40.000 --> 01:50:41.500
MATT: You make your way beyond--

01:50:41.500 --> 01:50:43.400
LIAM: (clears throat)
Ring-a-ding-ding.

01:50:43.400 --> 01:50:46.000
MATT: It's the oldest profession.

01:50:46.000 --> 01:50:49.000
You make your way all the way
to the outskirts of the Duskmeadow,

01:50:49.000 --> 01:50:51.000
and there, amongst the

01:50:51.000 --> 01:50:55.000
just barely peeking
through the cloudline starlight,

01:50:55.000 --> 01:51:00.000
the looming dark structure
that is Raven's Crest.

01:51:00.000 --> 01:51:03.000
TALIESIN: I'm just going to
gently open the door

01:51:03.000 --> 01:51:05.470
and peek inside
and see if anybody's inside.

01:51:05.470 --> 01:51:12.000
MATT: Okay. You go ahead
and push the door open. (creak)

01:51:12.000 --> 01:51:14.240
Doesn't appear to be anybody there.

01:51:20.000 --> 01:51:24.000
TALIESIN: I walk in just for a moment
and take a look around.

01:51:24.000 --> 01:51:28.000
MATT: Okay. You walk in.
(clicking footsteps)

01:51:28.000 --> 01:51:33.000
At this dark hour, looking around,
the obsidian-type walls

01:51:33.000 --> 01:51:35.000
are translucent glass
on the other side,

01:51:35.000 --> 01:51:36.500
though you can barely make out
through the material

01:51:36.500 --> 01:51:38.000
the details of the outside world,

01:51:38.000 --> 01:51:40.290
due to the lack of light
across the cityscape.

01:51:40.290 --> 01:51:41.700
Especially here in Duskmeadow,

01:51:41.700 --> 01:51:46.000
in which the magical lantern light
that illuminates the city streets

01:51:46.000 --> 01:51:49.940
are relatively sparse
on this side of Vasselheim.

01:51:49.940 --> 01:51:55.000
You take a few more steps in,
(clicking footsteps)

01:51:55.000 --> 01:52:00.000
footsteps echoing across the long,
thin, dark material of the floors.

01:52:00.000 --> 01:52:03.000
(creak, thud)

01:52:03.000 --> 01:52:05.000
LAURA: (gasps)
MATT: Door closes behind you.

01:52:05.000 --> 01:52:08.000
TRAVIS: (quietly) What would--
why would you do this?

01:52:08.000 --> 01:52:11.000
LIAM: Said the T. rex.

01:52:11.000 --> 01:52:13.000
TALIESIN: I'm going to
gently look around

01:52:13.000 --> 01:52:18.000
and slowly back up
and see if I can see anyone.

01:52:18.000 --> 01:52:24.000
TALIESIN: Hello? Hello?

01:52:24.000 --> 01:52:28.000
MATT: (echoing) Hello...
hello... hello.

01:52:40.000 --> 01:52:42.000
TALIESIN: What do I have to pay
to fix this?

01:52:42.000 --> 01:52:46.213
MATT: (echoing) This...
this... this... this.

01:52:52.453 --> 01:52:53.786
TALIESIN: I leave.

01:52:53.786 --> 01:52:55.750
MATT: (thump-crash)
You hear the sound

01:52:55.750 --> 01:52:58.000
of some sort of low,
distant hit and a rumble,

01:52:58.000 --> 01:53:02.500
and you see a distant light appear
in a chamber just beyond the walkway,

01:53:02.500 --> 01:53:04.000
just faint enough to illuminate

01:53:04.000 --> 01:53:07.000
and give the presence
of some sort of life or movement

01:53:07.000 --> 01:53:10.000
about a hundred or so feet ahead of you.

01:53:16.000 --> 01:53:18.000
TALIESIN: I walk briskly towards it.

01:53:18.000 --> 01:53:19.500
MATT: You enter the next chamber,

01:53:19.500 --> 01:53:21.000
where you see the interior
of this structure

01:53:21.000 --> 01:53:26.500
is ivory-white bone and glass,
with a blue hint,

01:53:26.500 --> 01:53:28.000
very much resembling the interior

01:53:28.000 --> 01:53:34.000
of a very naturally,
beautifully-carved ice cavern.

01:53:34.000 --> 01:53:35.500
There is a stairway that ascends,

01:53:35.500 --> 01:53:37.000
as well as other hallways
that lead out

01:53:37.000 --> 01:53:39.000
from the central nerve center

01:53:39.000 --> 01:53:43.000
of the lower floor
of the main structure.

01:53:43.000 --> 01:53:46.000
As you walk into this central chamber,

01:53:46.000 --> 01:53:49.000
you see, ever so faintly,
at the very top of the stairs,

01:53:49.000 --> 01:53:53.000
a pair of feet (footsteps)
walk and disappear up the stairs.

01:53:53.000 --> 01:53:55.000
TALIESIN: I'm going to 
charge after them.

01:53:55.000 --> 01:53:56.960
MATT: Okay. You go running
up the stairway. (thud thud)

01:53:56.960 --> 01:54:00.000
You get to the top, and you can see
at the very top of the stairs

01:54:00.000 --> 01:54:04.210
a dark wooden door
with a dark iron rim

01:54:04.210 --> 01:54:05.480
and what appears to be

01:54:05.480 --> 01:54:09.610
a large hanger or handle
or knocker bolted to it

01:54:09.610 --> 01:54:12.000
and it (thud) just closes

01:54:12.000 --> 01:54:17.000
as you come underneath
the top of the archway and up the stairs.

01:54:23.780 --> 01:54:25.000
TALIESIN: I knock.

01:54:25.000 --> 01:54:29.000
MATT: (doosh) Once?

01:54:29.000 --> 01:54:31.000
TALIESIN: Three times.

01:54:31.000 --> 01:54:33.000
MATT: (doosh doosh)
With each hit,

01:54:33.000 --> 01:54:36.000
you can hear the reverberation
of the echo of the knock

01:54:36.000 --> 01:54:39.000
through a much larger chamber beyond.

01:54:39.000 --> 01:54:44.000
As soon as you release
the actual door knocker,

01:54:44.000 --> 01:54:50.000
the door (thump-crash, creak)

01:54:50.000 --> 01:54:55.000
just creaks open ever so slightly
into a very, very dark chamber.

01:54:55.000 --> 01:54:59.000
You can see very, very little in here,
other than the basic outline

01:54:59.000 --> 01:55:03.000
of what looks to be
a little bit of floor,

01:55:03.000 --> 01:55:05.500
some sort of a smooth,
glassy surface

01:55:05.500 --> 01:55:07.000
that refracts
just a little bit of light

01:55:07.000 --> 01:55:09.000
that makes it through
what looks to be

01:55:09.000 --> 01:55:14.000
some sort of broken-up
glass dome-type structure above you.

01:55:14.000 --> 01:55:17.850
You can't make out much beyond that.
It's very dark in here.

01:55:19.890 --> 01:55:26.260
TALIESIN: Hello? Please. (sighs)

01:55:26.260 --> 01:55:30.000
Something terrible has happened.

01:55:30.000 --> 01:55:32.500
I don't understand how these games work.

01:55:32.500 --> 01:55:36.000
I need help to fix something.

01:55:39.000 --> 01:55:41.000
Something terrible has happened!

01:55:52.000 --> 01:55:54.500
You obviously
care little for this world.

01:55:54.500 --> 01:55:56.000
I start to back out.

01:55:56.000 --> 01:55:58.560
MATT: As you step out of the room,
you hear a whisper

01:55:58.560 --> 01:56:03.000
come from beyond the chamber,
within the darkness. It says,

01:56:03.000 --> 01:56:07.000
"Is it yourself
you wish to fix or something more?"

01:56:10.380 --> 01:56:13.640
TALIESIN: I don't think I can be fixed.

01:56:13.640 --> 01:56:16.000
There is something broken in the world.

01:56:18.000 --> 01:56:20.000
MATT: "Then come. Let us talk."

01:56:25.000 --> 01:56:27.760
TALIESIN: ...I don't understand
how these things work.

01:56:27.760 --> 01:56:33.000
I'm so sorry. 
Where do you wish me to go?

01:56:34.000 --> 01:56:35.500
MATT: "Have faith."

01:56:35.500 --> 01:56:37.000
TALIESIN: (disbelieving laugh)

01:56:37.000 --> 01:56:40.000
MATT: "Step in. Join me."

01:56:41.000 --> 01:56:47.000
TALIESIN: (sighs) ...I strip.

01:56:47.000 --> 01:56:49.000
TRAVIS: (gasps)

01:56:49.000 --> 01:56:51.000
TALIESIN: And put it aside.

01:56:51.000 --> 01:56:52.000
SAM: Put "it" aside?

01:56:52.000 --> 01:56:53.500
TALIESIN: Put my clothes
in the corner.

01:56:53.500 --> 01:56:55.000
SAM: Oh.
You're gonna jump her, eh?

01:56:55.000 --> 01:57:00.000
TALIESIN: You're filthy.
And I go into the pool.

01:57:00.000 --> 01:57:02.000
MATT: All right.

01:57:02.000 --> 01:57:06.500
As you step into the chamber,
freezing cold as your toes--

01:57:06.500 --> 01:57:08.000
TALIESIN: We're cold people.

01:57:08.000 --> 01:57:11.480
MATT: Your legs, your whole body
eventually finds itself

01:57:11.480 --> 01:57:18.000
stepping into this thick,
freezing liquid.

01:57:18.000 --> 01:57:20.000
You hear the whisper in your ears

01:57:20.000 --> 01:57:22.000
just as your head
reaches the level of the blood,

01:57:22.000 --> 01:57:23.520
that says,

01:57:26.000 --> 01:57:31.760
"Come. Come to me with your questions."

01:57:33.000 --> 01:57:36.000
Just as your head goes
beneath the surface.

01:57:36.000 --> 01:57:39.000
TALIESIN: (sighs) We're doing this.

01:57:41.000 --> 01:57:45.000
MATT: You're underneath
and in darkness,

01:57:45.000 --> 01:57:47.000
feeling around the thick material,

01:57:47.000 --> 01:57:50.000
kind of just
swishing your fingers around,

01:57:50.000 --> 01:57:51.500
but amongst the liquid,

01:57:51.500 --> 01:57:55.000
you still hear the whisper again
in your ear:

01:57:55.000 --> 01:57:59.000
"Come. Bring your questions."

01:57:59.000 --> 01:58:04.000
TALIESIN: And I swim down
until it's uncomfortable.

01:58:04.000 --> 01:58:08.740
MATT: You swim downward
and you touch the bottom of the pool.

01:58:08.740 --> 01:58:13.880
You reach a somewhat concave,

01:58:13.880 --> 01:58:16.630
smooth floor to the pool.

01:58:20.000 --> 01:58:22.000
TALIESIN: I'm going to
head to the surface.

01:58:22.000 --> 01:58:23.500
I don't know what's...

01:58:23.500 --> 01:58:26.000
MATT: You head to the surface.

01:58:26.000 --> 01:58:28.000
There's no surface.
It just keeps going.

01:58:28.000 --> 01:58:32.000
TALIESIN: (sighs)
I do not do well with this.

01:58:32.000 --> 01:58:35.000
MATT: You do not.
You begin to panic.

01:58:35.000 --> 01:58:36.500
TALIESIN: Yes, I do.

01:58:36.500 --> 01:58:38.000
MATT: You begin to reach around

01:58:38.000 --> 01:58:39.500
and try to swim up
and find the surface,

01:58:39.500 --> 01:58:40.500
but it just keeps going.

01:58:40.500 --> 01:58:42.000
The liquid's thick
and it's hard to pull through,

01:58:42.000 --> 01:58:43.500
and you can't open your eyes,
and you can't see anything,

01:58:43.500 --> 01:58:45.000
and the iron-like flavor

01:58:45.000 --> 01:58:48.000
is starting to find its way
to the inside of your mouth

01:58:48.000 --> 01:58:52.000
as it's seeping through your nose
and your ears.

01:58:52.000 --> 01:58:55.000
You begin to panic even further
as the cold is starting to take

01:58:55.000 --> 01:58:57.000
and you feel your muscles
beginning to shake and seize

01:58:57.000 --> 01:58:59.000
from the onset of hypothermia.

01:58:59.000 --> 01:59:01.000
You begin to head
to the bottom of the pool again,

01:59:01.000 --> 01:59:03.620
and this time,
you crack your head on the bottom

01:59:03.620 --> 01:59:06.420
in the middle of your stupor,
and you reach up and scream in pain.

01:59:06.420 --> 01:59:10.010
As you do, the blood fills your lungs
and you begin to feel yourself drown.

01:59:10.010 --> 01:59:11.500
You begin to shake and convulse

01:59:11.500 --> 01:59:13.000
as you begin to try to find a way
to force it out of your body

01:59:13.000 --> 01:59:15.000
and you can't.

01:59:15.000 --> 01:59:16.000
And at that moment,

01:59:16.000 --> 01:59:19.000
where all of a sudden
you realize that this is it.

01:59:19.000 --> 01:59:20.700
This is the end.

01:59:20.700 --> 01:59:24.460
This is how the tale of Percival
comes to an end.

01:59:26.000 --> 01:59:29.000
The sensation goes warm again.

01:59:29.000 --> 01:59:33.000
And it's like all that cold energy
goes away,

01:59:33.000 --> 01:59:37.000
and you're now swimming in water,
then air,

01:59:37.000 --> 01:59:42.000
and the pain subsides,
and you're breathing normally.

01:59:42.000 --> 01:59:46.000
But you still stand in darkness,
and you hear these distant footsteps.

01:59:46.000 --> 01:59:50.000
(clicking footsteps) Sourceless.

01:59:50.000 --> 01:59:54.000
No light, just shadow.

01:59:54.000 --> 01:59:55.500
And you look around 
over your shoulder

01:59:55.500 --> 01:59:57.000
and then right behind you,
you see immediately

01:59:57.000 --> 01:59:59.000
a white porcelain face,

01:59:59.000 --> 02:00:04.000
the head is just standing there
amongst the shadow.

02:00:07.000 --> 02:00:09.000
TALIESIN: (takes deep breaths)
Do you know what I've done?

02:00:09.000 --> 02:00:12.000
MATT: "I've watched."

02:00:17.000 --> 02:00:20.000
TALIESIN: I have questions.

02:00:20.000 --> 02:00:22.000
MATT: "Then ask them."

02:00:25.000 --> 02:00:31.450
TALIESIN: First is, can we stop it?

02:00:31.450 --> 02:00:35.000
Can we stop what's been released?

02:00:35.000 --> 02:00:37.000
Is there something I can do?

02:00:37.000 --> 02:00:40.000
MATT: "Many things
are released in this world.

02:00:40.000 --> 02:00:44.980
"Many terrible, many wonderful.
Many things.

02:00:46.000 --> 02:00:48.000
"Ask the right questions."

02:00:55.000 --> 02:00:57.550
TALIESIN: Did it choose me
because I was broken,

02:00:57.550 --> 02:00:58.980
or did it break me?

02:01:01.000 --> 02:01:04.960
MATT: The mask, which has not shown
any expression at this point,

02:01:04.960 --> 02:01:09.000
pulls back a little bit from you
and almost seems to grow in size.

02:01:09.000 --> 02:01:11.000
It's strange;

02:01:11.000 --> 02:01:14.000
the proportion seems to stay the same,
but suddenly your vision shifts

02:01:14.000 --> 02:01:15.000
and you realize, no,

02:01:15.000 --> 02:01:19.000
it's farther away from you
and is just suddenly immense,

02:01:19.000 --> 02:01:21.000
like your visual focus just changes

02:01:21.000 --> 02:01:23.000
and your whole perspective
suddenly causes you

02:01:23.000 --> 02:01:26.000
to lose sense of scale and balance.

02:01:26.000 --> 02:01:30.000
The voice comes in,
this time louder:

02:01:30.000 --> 02:01:34.000
"You were always broken, Percival.

02:01:34.000 --> 02:01:40.000
"And you were preyed upon,
just as it preys upon others,

02:01:40.000 --> 02:01:43.000
"and will continue to do so
until finally destroyed."

02:01:47.000 --> 02:01:50.000
TALIESIN: Can it be fixed?

02:01:50.000 --> 02:01:52.000
MATT: "Perhaps.

02:01:52.000 --> 02:01:58.000
"Your deeds will guide your path
to salvation or damnation.

02:01:58.000 --> 02:02:01.000
"The choice is yours.
You skirt that line still."

02:02:01.000 --> 02:02:06.000
TALIESIN: But the first deed is so...

02:02:06.000 --> 02:02:12.000
there's so much,
and I don't think any of them see it.

02:02:12.000 --> 02:02:19.000
I want it to die
before anybody sees it.

02:02:19.000 --> 02:02:21.000
Can you help?

02:02:21.000 --> 02:02:23.520
MATT: "I've already helped, Percival.

02:02:26.000 --> 02:02:28.000
"Do not think the path
that you and your allies walk

02:02:28.000 --> 02:02:31.000
"goes unseen.

02:02:33.000 --> 02:02:37.000
"There are many of those in this world
that represent the will of us,

02:02:37.000 --> 02:02:40.000
"just as there are those
who represent the will

02:02:40.000 --> 02:02:44.000
"of those that combat us
and always have.

02:02:47.000 --> 02:02:50.000
"There are a great many deeds
ahead of you.

02:02:50.000 --> 02:02:53.000
"It's your choice to take them.

02:02:53.000 --> 02:03:00.000
"Just know:
should you not watch yourself,

02:03:00.000 --> 02:03:03.000
"you may not find yourself
on our side."

02:03:03.000 --> 02:03:04.000
TALIESIN: I know.

02:03:11.460 --> 02:03:15.460
There is nowhere 
I can look for healing?

02:03:16.360 --> 02:03:18.840
Other than deeds?

02:03:21.000 --> 02:03:23.560
I like to fix things.

02:03:26.580 --> 02:03:29.530
MATT: "All life is inherently 
broken from the start, Percival.

02:03:29.530 --> 02:03:32.110
"Take solace in that.

02:03:32.110 --> 02:03:35.000
"There is no perfection in life.

02:03:35.000 --> 02:03:38.290
"Otherwise, what would be 
the purpose of death?

02:03:39.980 --> 02:03:43.000
"It's to try to find ways
to better yourself before the end

02:03:43.000 --> 02:03:45.110
"that gives us purpose.

02:03:48.000 --> 02:03:52.180
"You are all broken,
but also understand,"

02:03:52.180 --> 02:03:57.000
At this point, her voice 
gets very deep and very resonant.

02:03:57.000 --> 02:04:00.000
"Mortals can achieve great things.

02:04:00.000 --> 02:04:03.000
"I did."

02:04:03.000 --> 02:04:05.000
And the mask pulls back
into the shadows

02:04:05.000 --> 02:04:07.500
and suddenly (gasp, cough)

02:04:07.500 --> 02:04:10.170
you begin coughing,
finding your way to the surface,

02:04:10.170 --> 02:04:13.000
pouring blood out of your mouth
and coughing

02:04:13.000 --> 02:04:15.000
and eventually you find your way over,
breathing heavily,

02:04:15.000 --> 02:04:18.000
to the side of the pool and (grunt)
pull yourself onto the side.

02:04:18.000 --> 02:04:19.500
(cough) Cough the rest of it up.

02:04:19.500 --> 02:04:22.090
A little bit of moonlight peeks through,
and you can see

02:04:22.090 --> 02:04:26.000
the beams refracting through
the purples and reds and blues

02:04:26.000 --> 02:04:29.930
and just hints of specks of light

02:04:29.930 --> 02:04:31.540
that just shimmer
across the surface

02:04:31.540 --> 02:04:33.450
of this dark,
glass-like floor.

02:04:39.000 --> 02:04:42.000
TALIESIN: I'm going to take my sword

02:04:42.000 --> 02:04:46.000
and I'm going to very carefully
scrape my body clean of the blood,

02:04:46.000 --> 02:04:49.000
as much as I can,

02:04:49.000 --> 02:04:52.000
and I'm going to take
the back of my shirt

02:04:52.000 --> 02:04:56.000
and clean my hair off
as much as I can.

02:04:56.000 --> 02:05:00.000
I'm going to take
a vial of the blood in the pool.

02:05:00.000 --> 02:05:03.000
One tiny bit.

02:05:03.000 --> 02:05:04.440
MATT: You do so.

02:05:04.440 --> 02:05:07.220
TALIESIN: I'm going to
put my clothes back on...

02:05:12.000 --> 02:05:16.000
and I'm going to cast Hex on myself
for my walk home

02:05:16.000 --> 02:05:19.000
and banish it
before I come in the door.

02:05:19.000 --> 02:05:25.000
MATT: Okay. All righty.

02:05:25.000 --> 02:05:29.000
So, as Percival finally wanders in,

02:05:29.000 --> 02:05:30.000
is there anything else
anyone wants to achieve

02:05:30.000 --> 02:05:31.000
before the evening's done?

02:05:31.000 --> 02:05:32.500
SAM: I'd like to go to the Raven Queen.

02:05:32.500 --> 02:05:37.000
(laughter)

02:05:37.000 --> 02:05:38.000
SAM: No.

02:05:38.000 --> 02:05:39.000
LIAM: Are we next morning,

02:05:39.000 --> 02:05:40.500
or we're still evening,
at this point?

02:05:40.500 --> 02:05:42.000
MATT: We're still evening 
at the moment,

02:05:42.000 --> 02:05:43.500
if there's anything else
you wish to achieve. Otherwise--

02:05:43.500 --> 02:05:44.500
LAURA: I've been slowly heating water

02:05:44.500 --> 02:05:46.000
and giving it to Vax
to put in his bath.

02:05:46.000 --> 02:05:47.140
MATT: You do manage

02:05:47.140 --> 02:05:50.220
to draw a comfortable bath
for your brother and wash him clean.

02:05:50.220 --> 02:05:52.030
LAURA: I don't wash him!

02:05:52.030 --> 02:05:54.000
I just give him the fucking water.

02:05:54.000 --> 02:05:55.500
MATT: You aid him in washing 
himself clean. So you specify.

02:05:55.500 --> 02:05:59.000
LIAM: Thanks, man.

02:05:59.000 --> 02:06:01.500
TRAVIS: Do we see Percy
when he comes in?

02:06:01.500 --> 02:06:03.000
MATT: It's going to be late.

02:06:03.000 --> 02:06:04.500
TALIESIN: I'm going to walk quiet and late

02:06:04.500 --> 02:06:06.000
and go tinker
on a little thing for a minute

02:06:06.000 --> 02:06:08.000
until I pass out.

02:06:08.000 --> 02:06:10.000
MATT: Okay.
You do notice Percy enter.

02:06:10.000 --> 02:06:12.000
Looks a little frazzled,
but doesn't seem to--

02:06:12.000 --> 02:06:15.530
LAURA: Do I see any of the blood?
Passive perception?

02:06:15.530 --> 02:06:17.000
LIAM: You're in 
the tubby town, though.

02:06:17.000 --> 02:06:18.790
MATT: Make a perception check.

02:06:18.790 --> 02:06:22.330
I want you to make 
a dexterity check.

02:06:25.000 --> 02:06:27.000
MARISHA AND TALIESIN: (groan)

02:06:27.000 --> 02:06:29.000
LIAM: Sorry, Taliesin.

02:06:29.000 --> 02:06:31.000
SAM: You've got him.

02:06:31.000 --> 02:06:32.740
LIAM: Rolled high.
LAURA: 32.

02:06:32.740 --> 02:06:34.120
TALIESIN: 32?!

02:06:34.120 --> 02:06:36.730
Oh my god, what the--
I couldn't have rolled that.

02:06:36.730 --> 02:06:38.300
Like, that would've been 
a natural 20,

02:06:38.300 --> 02:06:40.000
would have been 
the only way around that.

02:06:40.000 --> 02:06:43.000
MATT: You see, just faintly 
behind one of his ears

02:06:43.000 --> 02:06:47.000
and at the edge of his collar
on his coat,

02:06:47.000 --> 02:06:54.000
just a bit of familiar crimson,
and a look of...

02:06:54.000 --> 02:06:56.000
a distant stare that is familiar.

02:07:02.000 --> 02:07:03.660
MATT: All right.

02:07:03.660 --> 02:07:05.500
Do you all wish to rest
for the evening?

02:07:05.500 --> 02:07:09.000
SAM: No, I would like
to take 12 hours to read my book.

02:07:09.000 --> 02:07:11.000
MATT: Okay, so the first 12 hours 
are completed,

02:07:11.000 --> 02:07:12.000
but you do not sleep?

02:07:12.000 --> 02:07:13.000
SAM: No.

02:07:13.000 --> 02:07:15.000
LIAM: It's a page-turner.

02:07:15.000 --> 02:07:17.000
SAM: Lots of centerfolds.

02:07:17.000 --> 02:07:19.420
(laughter)

02:07:19.420 --> 02:07:21.500
TRAVIS: Don't be stingy,
share those with me.

02:07:21.500 --> 02:07:23.000
MATT: Written by John Cleese.
It's a wonderful piece.

02:07:23.000 --> 02:07:26.000
LAURA: I also spend
a lot of time that night reading,

02:07:26.000 --> 02:07:28.000
but I'm reading
the book about the Raven Queen.

02:07:28.000 --> 02:07:29.700
MATT: Okay.

02:07:29.700 --> 02:07:32.200
LAURA: Pretty much
have it memorized at this point.

02:07:32.200 --> 02:07:35.000
MATT: Yeah, fair enough. All right.

02:07:35.000 --> 02:07:37.110
You guys all find yourself to rest,
except for Scanlan,

02:07:37.110 --> 02:07:38.500
who takes
a point of exhaustion

02:07:38.500 --> 02:07:40.000
for going through the night
without sleep.

02:07:40.000 --> 02:07:41.000
SAM: I don't know what that is,
but someone will tell me.

02:07:41.000 --> 02:07:42.000
TRAVIS: You'll find out.

02:07:42.000 --> 02:07:44.000
MATT: Yeah. Basically,
it means any ability checks,

02:07:44.000 --> 02:07:46.000
any skill checks
until you get a full night's rest

02:07:46.000 --> 02:07:48.410
are at disadvantage, yeah.

02:07:48.410 --> 02:07:50.870
