Is there anything
we need to finish,

02:23:13.500 --> 02:23:16.560
or do we want
to pick our next destination?

02:23:16.560 --> 02:23:18.500
SAM: Do they sell 
potions and things here in town--

02:23:18.500 --> 02:23:20.960
SAM: No, they don't.
TALIESIN: No, very specifically they don't.

02:23:20.960 --> 02:23:22.540
SAM: Then let's
get the hell out of here.

02:23:22.540 --> 02:23:24.070
There's nothing for us here.

02:23:24.070 --> 02:23:26.000
TRAVIS: What about the Feywild?
SAM: Oh, yeah.

02:23:26.000 --> 02:23:27.500
MARISHA: We did talk
about the Feywild.

02:23:27.500 --> 02:23:29.000
TALIESIN: Let's drop off our--

02:23:29.000 --> 02:23:30.500
LAURA: Don't tease me about the Feywild.

02:23:30.500 --> 02:23:32.000
TRAVIS: Wait, don't you have
to pick up something?

02:23:32.000 --> 02:23:34.000
TALIESIN: Oh, I already picked it up.
TRAVIS: Not you, you.

02:23:34.000 --> 02:23:36.000
SAM: Me?
TALIESIN: Oh, you have a hat.

02:23:36.000 --> 02:23:37.500
SAM: I thought we waited for the hat.

02:23:37.500 --> 02:23:39.000
MATT: Yeah, he picked up the hat.

02:23:39.000 --> 02:23:41.000
TRAVIS: Oh, shit, balls, ass.
All right.

02:23:41.000 --> 02:23:44.000
SAM: There's the Feywild.

02:23:44.000 --> 02:23:46.000
There's dropping stuff off
at Whitestone.

02:23:46.000 --> 02:23:50.000
There's Marquet,
which something is there in Marquet?

02:23:50.000 --> 02:23:51.500
LAURA: Is one of the Vestiges there?

02:23:51.500 --> 02:23:54.000
SAM: I don't know,
everyone just keeps talking about it.

02:23:54.000 --> 02:23:56.000
TRAVIS: Really?

02:23:56.000 --> 02:23:59.000
SAM: Wait, weren't we 
going to go to--

02:23:59.000 --> 02:24:02.000
MARISHA: One of the Vestiges
is in Marquet.

02:24:02.000 --> 02:24:04.290
LAURA: Which one?

02:24:04.290 --> 02:24:09.000
MARISHA: Hang on. Cabal's Ruin,
which is a magic-devouring cloak--

02:24:09.000 --> 02:24:13.000
TRAVIS: Hold on, hold on, hold on.
Are we alone in this room?

02:24:13.000 --> 02:24:17.000
MATT: You guys are right now
having breakfast in the guildhall.

02:24:17.000 --> 02:24:20.000
There's maybe two
other individuals in the room.

02:24:20.000 --> 02:24:22.000
One of them is
drunkenly asleep and snoring.

02:24:22.000 --> 02:24:24.000
The other appears to be
going about their business.

02:24:24.000 --> 02:24:25.500
TRAVIS: I'm just saying.

02:24:25.500 --> 02:24:29.000
MARISHA: (whispering)
Okay, I'll speak quietly.

02:24:29.000 --> 02:24:33.000
There's apparently
a magic-devouring cloak

02:24:33.000 --> 02:24:39.000
who is being worn by the--

02:24:39.000 --> 02:24:42.000
it's in Ank'Harel.
It's being worn by...

02:24:42.000 --> 02:24:44.000
LAURA: It's a cloak
that devours magic?

02:24:44.000 --> 02:24:47.000
MARISHA: A merchant warrior
with a missing eye.

02:24:47.000 --> 02:24:49.000
SAM: And there's one
in the bottom of the sea somewhere.

02:24:49.000 --> 02:24:53.170
LAURA: And there's a really beautiful 
strong bow in the Feywild.

02:24:53.170 --> 02:24:55.620
TRAVIS: Yeah, let's go to the Feywild!
We at least know that place.

02:24:55.620 --> 02:25:01.000
TALIESIN: I say we drop everything--
we take a pit stop in Whitestone

02:25:01.000 --> 02:25:03.430
and head towards the Feywild.

02:25:03.430 --> 02:25:06.050
MARISHA: So, technically,

02:25:06.050 --> 02:25:09.000
we don't even have
to head towards the Feywild.

02:25:09.000 --> 02:25:10.500
Do you guys remember

02:25:10.500 --> 02:25:16.000
how I kind of did that thing
with Grog's evil sword

02:25:16.000 --> 02:25:19.000
and kind of
banished it away for forever?

02:25:19.000 --> 02:25:21.000
TRAVIS: Are we bringing it back?
MARISHA: No.

02:25:21.000 --> 02:25:22.500
LAURA: Yeah, to the Dread Emperor's.
MARISHA: Right.

02:25:22.500 --> 02:25:25.000
LIAM: Not a good idea, Grog.

02:25:25.000 --> 02:25:26.500
MARISHA: No, we're not
bringing it back.

02:25:26.500 --> 02:25:30.000
I can do that with the rest of us.

02:25:30.000 --> 02:25:32.000
LAURA: You can banish us
to the Dread Emperor's island?

02:25:32.000 --> 02:25:33.500
MARISHA: No, it's not like
a banishment.

02:25:33.500 --> 02:25:36.110
I can Plane Shift us
wherever we want to go,

02:25:36.110 --> 02:25:38.000
to an alternate plane.

02:25:38.000 --> 02:25:39.500
LAURA: To the Feywild?

02:25:39.500 --> 02:25:41.000
So we don't even
have to find an entrance?

02:25:41.000 --> 02:25:43.000
MARISHA: Yeah, we just hold hands
and think about it really hard.

02:25:43.000 --> 02:25:44.500
TRAVIS: No way.

02:25:44.500 --> 02:25:47.000
MARISHA: Yeah.
It's druid magic. It's great.

02:25:47.000 --> 02:25:48.500
LIAM: And you put us

02:25:48.500 --> 02:25:51.000
in a safe spot 
somewhere in there, somehow?

02:25:51.000 --> 02:25:52.500
MARISHA: I can take us

02:25:52.500 --> 02:25:57.000
to where we've been before,
to where it's familiar.

02:25:57.000 --> 02:25:58.500
LIAM: Have we been there before?
I don't know.

02:25:58.500 --> 02:26:00.000
MARISHA: Very briefly.
TALIESIN: Yes.

02:26:00.000 --> 02:26:02.000
LAURA: Is it somewhere
that you have to have been,

02:26:02.000 --> 02:26:05.000
or can it be somewhere
that we have been.

02:26:07.000 --> 02:26:12.000
MARISHA: It is somewhere
I am familiar with, I believe,

02:26:12.000 --> 02:26:16.000
through means that I am familiar...

02:26:16.000 --> 02:26:18.000
LAURA: Syngorn is in the Feywild.

02:26:18.000 --> 02:26:19.500
SAM: Normally?

02:26:19.500 --> 02:26:21.610
LIAM: No, not normally.

02:26:21.610 --> 02:26:23.500
LAURA: They transferred 
the entire city there.

02:26:23.500 --> 02:26:25.000
LIAM: I know, but you're saying
we've been there,

02:26:25.000 --> 02:26:26.500
but they just did that recently.

02:26:26.500 --> 02:26:28.000
SAM: Grog's been to the Feywild.

02:26:28.000 --> 02:26:29.500
MATT: You can specify a target

02:26:29.500 --> 02:26:31.000
MARISHA: In general terms.
MATT: In general terms.

02:26:31.000 --> 02:26:34.200
MARISHA: Such as "City of Brass
on the Elemental Plane of Fire."

02:26:34.200 --> 02:26:35.710
SAM: Oh, is that
where we're going?

02:26:35.710 --> 02:26:36.860
MARISHA: No.

02:26:36.860 --> 02:26:40.480
SAM: Oh. Sounds like fun.
TALIESIN: It does, actually.

02:26:40.480 --> 02:26:43.000
MARISHA: If you guys want to go
to the Plane of Fire,

02:26:43.000 --> 02:26:45.000
that's like,
a hike and a jump through a hole.

02:26:45.000 --> 02:26:46.500
TALIESIN: Ah.

02:26:46.500 --> 02:26:49.000
TRAVIS: No, no, not the Plane of Fire.
Just the Feywild.

02:26:49.000 --> 02:26:53.240
MARISHA: All right.
Yeah, I can get us there.

02:26:53.240 --> 02:26:54.400
SAM: To the Feywild.

02:26:54.400 --> 02:26:57.000
How big is the Feywild?
Is it like a football field?

02:26:57.000 --> 02:26:59.000
MARISHA: It's very big.
LAURA: It's a whole other plane.

02:26:59.000 --> 02:27:00.500
SAM: Well, how do--

02:27:00.500 --> 02:27:02.180
do we know where we're going
in the Feywild?

02:27:02.180 --> 02:27:04.500
MARISHA: I imagine we'll figure it out
once we get there.

02:27:04.500 --> 02:27:06.660
TALIESIN: Do I know anything
about the Feywild?

02:27:06.660 --> 02:27:09.300
MATT: You have
no knowledge of the Feywild.

02:27:09.300 --> 02:27:11.650
ASHLEY: Would I know anything else?
MARISHA: What about me?

02:27:11.650 --> 02:27:13.780
LAURA: Would we have learned 
something about it in Syngorn?

02:27:13.780 --> 02:27:16.500
MATT: You have
a general idea of it, somewhat--

02:27:16.500 --> 02:27:18.000
MARISHA: Team Half-Elf, yeah.

02:27:18.000 --> 02:27:19.500
MATT: Somewhat,
just through your learning.

02:27:19.500 --> 02:27:21.000
You never actually visited there.

02:27:21.000 --> 02:27:24.000
The Feywild is a near plane,

02:27:24.000 --> 02:27:28.210
a plane that overlaps
this Prime Material Plane.

02:27:28.210 --> 02:27:32.000
It's a version
of the world you live in right now

02:27:32.000 --> 02:27:34.000
that is shifted and changed

02:27:34.000 --> 02:27:41.000
in a place where time,
distance is relative and shifts.

02:27:41.000 --> 02:27:44.000
Nature grows rampant and in cases

02:27:44.000 --> 02:27:50.000
is hard to really expect its direction.

02:27:50.000 --> 02:27:52.000
Things and entities exist there

02:27:52.000 --> 02:27:58.000
that prefer to trick and lose wanderers.

02:27:58.000 --> 02:28:02.000
It's a very strange place
where some believe

02:28:02.000 --> 02:28:06.000
elves initially come from
or craft from there, at least.

02:28:06.000 --> 02:28:07.500
LIAM: Do the two of us know enough

02:28:07.500 --> 02:28:10.620
that were you to jump
from the same place here,

02:28:10.620 --> 02:28:14.000
would you necessarily end up
in the same spot in the Feywild?

02:28:14.000 --> 02:28:15.500
MATT: You have no idea.

02:28:15.500 --> 02:28:17.000
LIAM: We don't know. All right.

02:28:17.000 --> 02:28:18.500
MATT: You don't know anything
about the transition to the Feywild.

02:28:18.500 --> 02:28:21.000
You just know that certain doors open
at certain times,

02:28:21.000 --> 02:28:24.000
especially with full moons
in certain locations,

02:28:24.000 --> 02:28:26.000
the classic toadstool rings,

02:28:26.000 --> 02:28:30.630
areas where the moonlight
in the realms

02:28:30.630 --> 02:28:33.680
can be a little thinner
and the barrier doors do open,

02:28:33.680 --> 02:28:37.700
and those are where creatures
can transition out or through.

02:28:37.700 --> 02:28:43.000
You do know it's a place of fey magic,

02:28:43.000 --> 02:28:48.000
it's tricky, it's difficult to follow.

02:28:48.000 --> 02:28:50.000
SAM: Terrible.
LAURA: It sounds awful.

02:28:50.000 --> 02:28:55.650
MATT: Very, like, Oberon and Titania.
Weird. Interesting.

02:28:55.650 --> 02:29:00.000
MARISHA: Question.
MATT: Yes?

02:29:00.000 --> 02:29:04.000
MARISHA: Hmm, okay.
SAM: Good question.

02:29:04.000 --> 02:29:08.000
MARISHA: It says
the Wrath of the Fey Warden

02:29:08.000 --> 02:29:11.000
is what we're looking for, the bow,
and that it now acts

02:29:11.000 --> 02:29:17.000
as the heart of a cancerous tree,
corrupting the verdant land.

02:29:17.000 --> 02:29:21.000
Is there something I can do,
maybe try and...

02:29:21.000 --> 02:29:26.000
TRAVIS: Hold on, is our stream up?
Are we offline right now?

02:29:27.660 --> 02:29:29.960
LUCAS: (muffled, from offscreen)
I'm checking. Just wait.

02:29:30.780 --> 02:29:33.000
ASHLEY: Hold, please.

02:29:33.000 --> 02:29:35.940
LUCAS: It says we're still online.
Hang on.

02:29:35.940 --> 02:29:39.000
LIAM: Loot Crate. Check out Loot Crate.
SAM: No one can see it.

02:29:39.000 --> 02:29:41.000
LAURA: No, it says it's offline.

02:29:41.000 --> 02:29:42.500
LIAM: Refresh it.
MARISHA: It says offline?

02:29:42.500 --> 02:29:44.170
LIAM: Quit the program
and go back in.

02:29:44.170 --> 02:29:46.000
TRAVIS: The chat is saying it's off.

02:29:47.480 --> 02:29:50.000
LUCAS: No, we're still online.
LAURA: Okay.

02:29:50.000 --> 02:29:51.810
LIAM: Tell them to quit and re-login.
SAM: It's back. It's back.

02:29:51.810 --> 02:29:53.400
LUCAS: I'm not sure what happened.

02:29:53.400 --> 02:29:55.140
I'm not sure it even 
dropped frames on my end.

02:29:55.140 --> 02:29:56.920
LIAM: Whoa, we were
in the Feywild for a second there.

02:29:56.920 --> 02:29:59.000
ASHLEY: Oh, it was crazy.
MATT: You guys missed six episodes.

02:29:59.000 --> 02:30:01.000
(exaggerated sounds of relief)

02:30:01.000 --> 02:30:03.000
MATT: Everything turned out okay.

02:30:03.000 --> 02:30:06.360
LAURA: Yay! And we got the warden thing.
LIAM: Dragons are dead.

02:30:06.360 --> 02:30:09.000
MARISHA: Guys, I'm so glad
we won DND. We beat it.

02:30:09.000 --> 02:30:11.230
LAURA: Yeah, that was the best.

02:30:12.200 --> 02:30:14.200
TALIESIN: Roll the credits scroll.

02:30:16.000 --> 02:30:20.570
MARISHA: Can I maybe sense a sick tree?

02:30:23.000 --> 02:30:25.030
You know what?
Let's go to Whitestone.

02:30:25.030 --> 02:30:27.110
Let's go to Whitestone
and drop some stuff off.

02:30:27.110 --> 02:30:29.000
LAURA: You know,
because the more I think about it,

02:30:29.000 --> 02:30:32.000
I mean, we almost just
died many times

02:30:32.000 --> 02:30:33.500
and the last time we tried
to get a Vestige

02:30:33.500 --> 02:30:35.000
it almost killed us,
and maybe we just need

02:30:35.000 --> 02:30:37.000
a little bit
more preparation, maybe?

02:30:37.000 --> 02:30:42.000
TALIESIN: Let's empty our bags,
let's prepare ourselves.

02:30:42.000 --> 02:30:44.540
There are certainly stories
in the woods of Whitestone

02:30:44.540 --> 02:30:45.970
of strange happenings,

02:30:45.970 --> 02:30:48.750
so I'm sure
there's probably some connection

02:30:48.750 --> 02:30:51.000
to the Feywild,
and we'll see what happens.

02:30:51.000 --> 02:30:52.500
LAURA: Make sure Whitestone 
is actually

02:30:52.500 --> 02:30:55.000
preparing something underground
just like Westruun.

02:30:55.000 --> 02:30:57.000
TALIESIN: Well, we have something.

02:30:57.000 --> 02:30:59.000
MARISHA: Yes, they have
something underground already.

02:30:59.000 --> 02:31:03.000
LAURA: Exactly, but there's
a spinning orb of death there.

02:31:03.000 --> 02:31:04.500
TALIESIN: Which, to be fair,

02:31:04.500 --> 02:31:06.000
is probably going
to keep a dragon away.

02:31:06.000 --> 02:31:08.000
LIAM: But I also think

02:31:08.000 --> 02:31:10.000
we've earned more
than a single day of rest.

02:31:10.000 --> 02:31:12.000
TALIESIN: Yes.

02:31:12.000 --> 02:31:14.000
LIAM: Let's go to Whitestone.
TALIESIN: Let's go to Whitestone.

02:31:14.000 --> 02:31:16.000
MARISHA: All right.
ASHLEY: Where's the sea?

02:31:16.000 --> 02:31:18.000
SAM: The Ozmit Sea?
ASHLEY: Yeah.

02:31:18.000 --> 02:31:22.000
MATT: The Ozmit Sea is
to the east of you, east-southeast,

02:31:22.000 --> 02:31:25.000
and that is a wide gulf that separates--

02:31:25.000 --> 02:31:27.000
from your perspective, looking at me,

02:31:27.000 --> 02:31:33.000
there's Othanzia, Ozmit Sea,
and there's Tal'Dorei right here.

02:31:33.000 --> 02:31:35.000
LAURA: Oh, okay.

02:31:35.000 --> 02:31:36.220
LIAM: (sneezes)

02:31:36.220 --> 02:31:37.770
TALIESIN AND MARISHA: Bless you.
LAURA: Bless you.

02:31:37.770 --> 02:31:43.000
MARISHA: The Water Ashari
live in the Ozmit Sea.

02:31:43.000 --> 02:31:45.000
LAURA: Are they like mermaids?

02:31:45.000 --> 02:31:47.000
MARISHA: No, I think they've got an island.

02:31:47.000 --> 02:31:49.000
ASHLEY: It's also the sea that I sailed.

02:31:49.000 --> 02:31:50.200
MARISHA: Really?
LAURA: (gasps)

02:31:50.200 --> 02:31:51.460
SAM: Ohhh.
TALIESIN: Really?

02:31:51.460 --> 02:31:53.500
LAURA: In your roving pirate days.

02:31:53.500 --> 02:31:55.160
ASHLEY: I know it well.

02:31:55.160 --> 02:31:57.500
MARISHA: How familiar are you 
with the sea?

02:31:57.500 --> 02:32:00.000
ASHLEY: I'm pretty familiar with it.

02:32:00.000 --> 02:32:01.680
TRAVIS: What if we go there?

02:32:01.680 --> 02:32:03.120
SAM: We could.

02:32:03.120 --> 02:32:05.000
LAURA: Wait, could I see 
the list of Vestiges?

02:32:05.000 --> 02:32:08.000
SAM: The one in the bottom of the sea
is called Whisper, right?

02:32:08.000 --> 02:32:09.610
LAURA: Whisper?

02:32:09.610 --> 02:32:15.000
MARISHA: A blade forged from metal
pulled from the Far Realm,

02:32:15.000 --> 02:32:17.000
it was the center of many dark rituals.

02:32:17.000 --> 02:32:19.000
SAM: It now lies
at the bottom of the Ozmit Sea,

02:32:19.000 --> 02:32:22.000
sunken with the lost ship,
The Shrew.

02:32:22.000 --> 02:32:24.000
LAURA: (sing-song) The Shrew?
ASHLEY: (deep voice) The Shrew.

02:32:24.000 --> 02:32:27.000
SAM: A storm three hundred years ago
near an island of glass.

02:32:27.000 --> 02:32:29.000
Anyone know about the island of glass?

02:32:29.000 --> 02:32:30.500
LAURA: Have you heard
about an island of glass?

02:32:30.500 --> 02:32:32.300
MARISHA: Have I heard
about an island of glass?

02:32:32.300 --> 02:32:33.990
Have Pike or I heard
of an island of glass?

02:32:33.990 --> 02:32:36.320
MATT: I'll have both of you guys
make history checks.

02:32:36.320 --> 02:32:37.430
MARISHA: All right.

02:32:39.660 --> 02:32:41.390
I rolled a natural 1.

02:32:43.000 --> 02:32:46.000
MATT: You barely know
what glass is right now.

02:32:46.000 --> 02:32:48.000
MARISHA: Guys, water isn't glass,
that's stupid.

02:32:48.000 --> 02:32:50.000
TALIESIN: I would have
a theory as to what it was.

02:32:50.000 --> 02:32:51.500
TRAVIS: She rolled a 20.

02:32:51.500 --> 02:32:54.520
MARISHA: You rolled a 20? Oh, go Pike!
ASHLEY: Not a natural 20. Total.

02:32:54.520 --> 02:32:56.000
MATT: Explain.

02:32:56.000 --> 02:33:02.000
TALIESIN: Should I roll to figure out
that this is probably an active volcano?

02:33:02.000 --> 02:33:04.000
MATT: Make an intelligence check.

02:33:04.000 --> 02:33:05.700
TALIESIN: I'm down.

02:33:05.700 --> 02:33:07.390
LIAM: Come on, man.

02:33:07.390 --> 02:33:09.500
TALIESIN: No! Wow.

02:33:09.500 --> 02:33:11.420
SAM: Onesies.
MARISHA: Team ones. Whoo.

02:33:11.420 --> 02:33:13.190
MATT: Natural 1?
TALIESIN: Natural 1.

02:33:13.190 --> 02:33:14.470
LIAM: Snitch.

02:33:14.470 --> 02:33:15.950
MATT: Doesn't quite come to you,
but what it could be.

02:33:15.950 --> 02:33:18.000
The idea of a volcano
possibly comes to mind, but--

02:33:18.000 --> 02:33:19.500
TALIESIN: I'm distracted.

02:33:19.500 --> 02:33:21.000
MATT: Yeah.

02:33:21.000 --> 02:33:24.000
You have not been there,
you haven't seen it,

02:33:24.000 --> 02:33:26.000
but some of your crewmates
while you were traveling

02:33:26.000 --> 02:33:32.000
aboard your ship
for that five, six-month period,

02:33:32.000 --> 02:33:35.000
a couple of them did mention something
about on the sea,

02:33:35.000 --> 02:33:39.000
a mirage-like island
that glistens in the distance,

02:33:39.000 --> 02:33:41.730
but they said to avoid it,
said it was dangerous.

02:33:41.730 --> 02:33:44.060
SAM: Did they say where it was?

02:33:44.060 --> 02:33:45.500
MATT: No.
SAM: Damn it.

02:33:45.500 --> 02:33:47.500
ASHLEY: Heard many tales of The Shrew.

02:33:47.500 --> 02:33:48.950
LAURA: Yeah?
ASHLEY: Yeah, the ship lost at sea.

02:33:48.950 --> 02:33:52.000
MATT: You know of The Shrew,
you definitely know of The Shrew.

02:33:52.000 --> 02:33:53.500
ASHLEY: All sailors know of The Shrew.

02:33:53.500 --> 02:33:57.000
MARISHA: What's the story of The Shrew?
SAM: Come on, sailor.

02:33:57.000 --> 02:34:01.000
ASHLEY: There was a storm
three hundred years ago.

02:34:01.000 --> 02:34:04.000
LAURA: Near an island of glass?
ASHLEY: Near an island of glass.

02:34:04.000 --> 02:34:05.500
MARISHA: It was really bad.

02:34:05.500 --> 02:34:07.000
ASHLEY: And The Shrew
just didn't sail on.

02:34:07.000 --> 02:34:09.000
SAM: It was tamed.
ASHLEY: It was tamed.

02:34:09.000 --> 02:34:11.000
LAURA: (laughs) I was waiting for it to--

02:34:11.000 --> 02:34:12.500
MATT: Come around again?
Yeah, it was good.

02:34:12.500 --> 02:34:14.000
LAURA: Come around, yep.
TALIESIN: Taming of the Shrew fits, yeah.

02:34:14.000 --> 02:34:16.500
ASHLEY: Good tale,
but we'll get there one day.

02:34:16.500 --> 02:34:18.000
MATT: What's the plan?

02:34:18.000 --> 02:34:19.500
LIAM: Whitestone.
SAM: Yes, Whitestone.

02:34:19.500 --> 02:34:21.860
TRAVIS: Can I make 
one other suggestion?

02:34:21.860 --> 02:34:23.360
Emon...

02:34:23.360 --> 02:34:25.360
go take Thordak right now.

02:34:25.360 --> 02:34:28.010
SAM: Good call...
TRAVIS: Yeah, one taker?

02:34:28.010 --> 02:34:30.420
MARISHA: You know what, Grog?
LAURA: It's a good plan, Grog.

02:34:30.420 --> 02:34:31.830
LIAM: It's cheeky.

02:34:31.830 --> 02:34:34.000
MARISHA: We will put that
in our back pocket

02:34:34.000 --> 02:34:35.870
and we will think about it.

02:34:35.870 --> 02:34:38.010
LIAM: That helmet
is really something else.

02:34:38.010 --> 02:34:40.500
LAURA: You could really do 
something terrible to him with that thing.

02:34:40.500 --> 02:34:43.000
TRAVIS: I'm just saying,
I think we have an edge now.

02:34:43.000 --> 02:34:45.000
LAURA: I think you're probably right.
SAM: (chuckle) Attaboy.

02:34:45.000 --> 02:34:48.500
LIAM: That's technically true, yes.
TALIESIN: You do... have a point.

02:34:48.500 --> 02:34:50.700
LAURA: But let's make sure 
that Whitestone is safe

02:34:50.700 --> 02:34:52.020
before we do such a thing.

02:34:52.020 --> 02:34:54.570
SAM: Percy, we are in a place
that has an airship dock.

02:34:54.570 --> 02:34:56.000
TALIESIN: That is true.

02:34:56.000 --> 02:34:57.500
SAM: We could go steal an airship.

02:34:57.500 --> 02:34:59.000
TALIESIN: We could go steal an airship!

02:34:59.000 --> 02:35:01.000
LAURA: We don't need an airship.
MARISHA: We don't need an airship.

02:35:01.000 --> 02:35:02.500
LAURA: We have an instant ability
to transport anywhere.

02:35:02.500 --> 02:35:04.460
SAM: It would be so cool, though.

02:35:04.460 --> 02:35:06.340
TALIESIN: Then we wouldn't
have to go to Whitestone.

02:35:06.340 --> 02:35:08.000
It would hold all of our things.

02:35:08.000 --> 02:35:09.500
LAURA AND MARISHA: 
When we kill all the dragons...

02:35:09.500 --> 02:35:11.000
TALIESIN: We could hold 
all of our things on the airship,

02:35:11.000 --> 02:35:12.660
and I could have cannonades...

02:35:12.660 --> 02:35:15.000
LAURA: That will be the first thing we do
when Thordak dies

02:35:15.000 --> 02:35:16.500
is we jump on an airship.

02:35:16.500 --> 02:35:17.500
ASHLEY: Party on the airship.

02:35:17.500 --> 02:35:19.320
MARISHA: We'll buy it
with all of the gold

02:35:19.320 --> 02:35:20.720
that we've stolen
from all the dragons.

02:35:20.720 --> 02:35:21.930
It'll be great.

02:35:21.930 --> 02:35:24.500
TALIESIN: We won't need the airship
if the dragons are dead.

02:35:24.500 --> 02:35:26.790
LAURA: All the fun has gone out of it.
TRAVIS: What are we doing?

02:35:26.790 --> 02:35:28.510
LAURA: We're going to Whitestone.
MARISHA: We're going to Whitestone.

02:35:28.510 --> 02:35:29.720
MARISHA: (piercing spell noise)

02:35:29.720 --> 02:35:32.000
SAM: Before we leave, do you want 
to sell these stupid white dragon scales?

02:35:32.000 --> 02:35:32.920
TALIESIN: No.
SAM: All right, let's go.

02:35:32.920 --> 02:35:34.010
LIAM: Let's go to Whitestone.

02:35:34.010 --> 02:35:35.650
MARISHA: (repeats piercing spell noise) 
Through a tree!

02:35:35.650 --> 02:35:38.000
MATT: All right, as you guys walk 
outside of the Slayer's Take guildhall,

02:35:38.000 --> 02:35:40.470
you find the nearest tree,
which you've used before to traverse.

02:35:40.470 --> 02:35:43.290
As you all step through the portal,
Percy and Scanlan

02:35:43.290 --> 02:35:46.000
look over their shoulder
at the distant skyport

02:35:46.000 --> 02:35:50.000
and see the one airship docked there
and think, "One day..."

02:35:50.000 --> 02:35:52.280
LIAM: So handsome.

02:35:52.280 --> 02:35:56.000
SAM: Someday, it will be ours.
TALIESIN: You'll make a fine sailor.

02:35:56.000 --> 02:35:59.000
SAM: Passenger.
LIAM: Swabby.

02:35:59.000 --> 02:36:03.540
MATT: You jump through
and emerge out the other side.

02:36:03.540 --> 02:36:07.000
As you step out of the portal,
you find yourself

02:36:07.000 --> 02:36:10.000
jumping out of the center
of the Sun Tree.

02:36:10.000 --> 02:36:12.000
MARISHA: Can I do something?
SAM: Nope.

02:36:12.000 --> 02:36:14.000
MATT: What do you want to do?

02:36:14.000 --> 02:36:18.950
MARISHA: While I'm in the tree,
can I do something?

02:36:18.950 --> 02:36:20.960
TRAVIS: Like kill us all?

02:36:20.960 --> 02:36:24.000
No no no. Say they go first.
"Go, go, go, go."

02:36:24.000 --> 02:36:26.000
And I kind of start teleporting
through the tree

02:36:26.000 --> 02:36:31.000
and while I'm in the Sun Tree
I just want to be like,

02:36:31.000 --> 02:36:34.000
"Hey, boo."

02:36:34.000 --> 02:36:36.000
LAURA: (laughs)

02:36:36.000 --> 02:36:38.000
MARISHA: "I missed you.

02:36:38.000 --> 02:36:42.000
"Have you heard of this whole
cancerous tree situation

02:36:42.000 --> 02:36:43.630
"in the Feywild?"

02:36:43.630 --> 02:36:45.500
SAM: (whispering) You're talking to a tree?

02:36:45.500 --> 02:36:47.000
MARISHA: Shh, no.
I'm in the middle of the tree.

02:36:47.000 --> 02:36:48.500
I'm in the tree.

02:36:48.500 --> 02:36:50.390
LAURA: You're stuck in the tree?

02:36:50.390 --> 02:36:53.000
MATT: As you finish this thought,
you hear this sound emerge

02:36:53.000 --> 02:36:56.570
(vacuum sealing sound)
and realize it's the sound

02:36:56.570 --> 02:36:58.500
of the whole portal you've made
closing behind you

02:36:58.500 --> 02:37:00.000
because it only lasts for six seconds

02:37:00.000 --> 02:37:01.500
and you should probably
get the hell out of the tree.

02:37:01.500 --> 02:37:03.000
MARISHA: Aww. I step out of the tree.

02:37:03.000 --> 02:37:04.190
ASHLEY: Good try.

02:37:04.190 --> 02:37:06.000
MATT: As you step out, a voice goes,

02:37:06.000 --> 02:37:07.500
"Hey, boo, sorry.(kiss noise)"

02:37:07.500 --> 02:37:09.000
(laughter)

02:37:09.000 --> 02:37:12.000
MATT: And it closes behind you.

02:37:12.000 --> 02:37:14.720
MARISHA: I'll talk to him later.

02:37:17.000 --> 02:37:19.000
MATT: You guys emerge.

02:37:19.000 --> 02:37:23.000
Due to the time differences,
you land here in Whitestone,

02:37:23.000 --> 02:37:29.000
looking at where the sun is in the sky,
it's early afternoon,

02:37:29.000 --> 02:37:33.000
as opposed to the morning
where you guys just stepped away from.

02:37:33.000 --> 02:37:36.000
There are people in the streets,
and you see a few,

02:37:37.570 --> 02:37:40.000
a little bit of life
has returned to this town square,

02:37:40.000 --> 02:37:42.000
though still, by comparison--

02:37:42.000 --> 02:37:45.000
there are folks now
that are bringing in actual,

02:37:45.000 --> 02:37:49.000
healthy, looks to be fruits
from nearby trees.

02:37:49.000 --> 02:37:50.500
There's a little bit of trade going on.

02:37:50.500 --> 02:37:52.000
This is the first real chance you've had

02:37:52.000 --> 02:37:56.000
to see a little bit of Whitestone
coming to life again.

02:37:56.000 --> 02:37:59.000
As you emerge from the tree,
a few individuals nearby

02:37:59.000 --> 02:38:04.000
stop and look and smile and wave,
recognizing you as you approach.

02:38:04.000 --> 02:38:06.000
LAURA: Are there any leaves
on the Sun Tree yet?

02:38:06.000 --> 02:38:10.530
MATT: Actually, no, there are not.
There are no leaves on the Sun Tree.

02:38:10.530 --> 02:38:12.470
SAM: (quietly) Because it's winter.

02:38:12.470 --> 02:38:14.060
LAURA: Whatever.

02:38:14.060 --> 02:38:16.000
TRAVIS: We should check
with the border patrol.

02:38:16.000 --> 02:38:18.500
SAM: There's a border patrol?

02:38:18.500 --> 02:38:20.000
TRAVIS: Yeah.
LAURA: A wolf.

02:38:20.000 --> 02:38:21.500
SAM: Oh, the wolf.

02:38:21.500 --> 02:38:24.000
TRAVIS: (whistles) I whistle
as loud as I can.

02:38:24.000 --> 02:38:27.040
MATT: Okay.
SAM: What's his name?

02:38:27.040 --> 02:38:30.000
MARISHA: I don't know.
Let me find it.

02:38:30.000 --> 02:38:32.130
SAM: Oh, boy. Harold?

02:38:34.000 --> 02:38:36.000
LAURA: I just want to go find Zahra

02:38:36.000 --> 02:38:38.000
and give her a hug and say hello
and see how she's doing

02:38:38.000 --> 02:38:41.000
while he's talking.

02:38:41.000 --> 02:38:45.000
MATT: You whistle as loud as you can
for a little bit. Nothing.

02:38:45.000 --> 02:38:49.000
TRAVIS: Must be off doing something
(belches) important.

02:38:49.000 --> 02:38:50.340
TALIESIN: Quite.

02:38:50.340 --> 02:38:53.000
MATT: You head off and, asking around,

02:38:53.000 --> 02:38:57.000
you find Zahra is actually
up in Castle Whitestone right now,

02:38:57.000 --> 02:39:00.000
just poring through
one of the studies of books,

02:39:00.000 --> 02:39:01.500
and is just currently
reading and reading on her own.

02:39:01.500 --> 02:39:03.000
As you eventually ask around
and find your way there,

02:39:03.000 --> 02:39:05.000
entering the room, you see her

02:39:05.000 --> 02:39:07.000
with a small set of spectacles
at the end of her nose.

02:39:07.000 --> 02:39:09.000
She takes them off and,

02:39:09.000 --> 02:39:11.000
"My darling Vex'ahlia!"

02:39:11.000 --> 02:39:12.500
And comes up
and just gives you a big hug

02:39:12.500 --> 02:39:14.450
and picks you up and sets you down.

02:39:14.450 --> 02:39:16.640
"I'm so glad to see 
you're all right."

02:39:16.640 --> 02:39:19.140
LAURA: Dear, the dragon arrow 
you gave me? Killed him.

02:39:19.140 --> 02:39:21.500
Well, I didn't kill him,
actually, with it,

02:39:21.500 --> 02:39:23.000
but I did a lot of damage.

02:39:23.000 --> 02:39:26.000
MATT: "You killed a dragon?"
LAURA: Umbrasyl. Dead. One down.

02:39:26.000 --> 02:39:30.000
MATT: "I knew you would."

02:39:30.000 --> 02:39:31.500
LAURA: Where's Cashew?

02:39:31.500 --> 02:39:34.000
MATT: "I don't know.
He's testy these days.

02:39:34.000 --> 02:39:35.500
"I'm sure he's around."

02:39:35.500 --> 02:39:38.000
LAURA: I know his name 
is fucking Kashaw.

02:39:38.000 --> 02:39:41.000
So he's not there.

02:39:41.000 --> 02:39:43.000
MATT: "Probably down
in the city somewhere.

02:39:43.000 --> 02:39:47.000
"He's helping where he can.
You know broody types."

02:39:47.000 --> 02:39:49.000
LAURA: I do know broody types.

02:39:49.000 --> 02:39:50.500
MATT: Yes, you do.

02:39:50.500 --> 02:39:52.000
LAURA: What are you reading?

02:39:52.000 --> 02:39:54.000
MATT: "Oh, I'm just learning
about the history of Whitestone

02:39:54.000 --> 02:39:56.000
"and I'm very intrigued
as to the actual properties

02:39:56.000 --> 02:39:59.000
"of this stone 
the entire town is built on.

02:39:59.000 --> 02:40:03.000
"There's a lot of really,
really interesting things

02:40:03.000 --> 02:40:06.000
"that can be done with the materials
in these mountains."

02:40:06.000 --> 02:40:08.000
LAURA: I'm sure you have ideas.
MATT: "I do."

02:40:08.000 --> 02:40:10.000
LAURA: I sit down next to her and ask,
just catching up,

02:40:10.000 --> 02:40:14.000
and see if they've spotted any dragons.

02:40:14.000 --> 02:40:16.000
MATT: You guys continue your conversation,
catching up,

02:40:16.000 --> 02:40:18.000
letting her know how things happened,
and vice versa.

02:40:18.000 --> 02:40:20.000
You don't get any info
that any dragons have come by.

02:40:20.000 --> 02:40:25.000
Apparently, there have been
a few other arcane practitioners

02:40:25.000 --> 02:40:30.000
that have been helping set up
some sort of barrier to help,

02:40:30.000 --> 02:40:34.000
essentially,
dissuade attention towards the city.

02:40:34.000 --> 02:40:37.000
The idea of keeping this place
as far off the map as possible,

02:40:37.000 --> 02:40:40.000
should any prying eyes
find their way there.

02:40:40.000 --> 02:40:43.000
It's in the process
of being set up right now.

02:40:44.400 --> 02:40:50.000
LAURA: Zahra, how long did it take you
to make that arrow?

02:40:50.000 --> 02:40:55.000
MATT: "A few weeks."

02:40:55.000 --> 02:40:58.000
LAURA: If I were to give you
some more money,

02:40:58.000 --> 02:41:00.000
do you think you could do it again?

02:41:02.000 --> 02:41:09.000
MATT: "Probably, based on what--
(sighs) if I'm able to use

02:41:09.000 --> 02:41:13.000
"some of the resources
here within the castle, maybe."

02:41:13.000 --> 02:41:16.000
LAURA: I'll talk to Percy,
but I'm sure, if it's for a good cause...

02:41:16.000 --> 02:41:18.000
MATT: "All right, perhaps I can."

02:41:18.000 --> 02:41:19.500
LAURA: All right. 
I'll come find you, dear.

02:41:19.500 --> 02:41:21.000
MATT: "Wondrous."

02:41:24.000 --> 02:41:26.000
What else are you guys 
trying to achieve here?

02:41:26.000 --> 02:41:28.500
LIAM: I am trying to find Shaun Gilmore.

02:41:28.500 --> 02:41:30.490
LAURA: That's his first name?
SAM: Shaun Gilmore?

02:41:30.490 --> 02:41:31.920
MATT AND MARISHA: Yeah.
TALIESIN: Yeah, Shaun.

02:41:31.920 --> 02:41:34.240
LAURA: Shaun? 
How did you know that?

02:41:34.240 --> 02:41:35.500
MARISHA: He told us.

02:41:35.500 --> 02:41:37.000
MATT: He told you guys that
a long time ago.

02:41:37.000 --> 02:41:39.500
LAURA: I fucking know, I remember.
MATT: (laughs)

02:41:39.500 --> 02:41:41.000
TALIESIN: Tattooed
at the small of his back.

02:41:41.000 --> 02:41:43.060
MARISHA: Yeah, he's got a tramp stamp.
ASHLEY: Tramp stamp.

02:41:43.060 --> 02:41:47.400
SAM: Can I accompany Vax on this trip?
LIAM: Sure, come on.

02:41:47.400 --> 02:41:50.000
SAM: I want to see Gilmore.

02:41:50.000 --> 02:41:52.000
LIAM: Let's start
asking around town for him.

02:41:52.000 --> 02:41:55.000
MATT: You start asking around.

02:41:55.000 --> 02:42:01.000
You come across
a few folks you recognize,

02:42:01.000 --> 02:42:05.000
you find a few of the guards
who helped you

02:42:05.000 --> 02:42:08.000
with the initial reconstruction
of this city and such

02:42:08.000 --> 02:42:10.000
and asking around.

02:42:10.000 --> 02:42:12.000
One of the nearby guards
takes his helmet off and is like,

02:42:12.000 --> 02:42:13.500
"First off, I am so excited

02:42:13.500 --> 02:42:16.000
"that you guys are back.
I'm so glad you're all safe.

02:42:16.000 --> 02:42:19.000
"I heard that you were
off to do some dangerous things."

02:42:19.000 --> 02:42:21.000
LIAM: You heard right.

02:42:21.000 --> 02:42:25.000
MATT: "Well, great,
I'm glad that you've survived.

02:42:25.000 --> 02:42:27.000
"Looking for Mr. Gilmore,

02:42:27.000 --> 02:42:32.000
"he's actually down with the Realmseer.

02:42:32.000 --> 02:42:35.000
"They're inspecting
the ziggurat underneath the city,

02:42:35.000 --> 02:42:38.540
"so you could head down there
if you wanted to find him."

02:42:40.000 --> 02:42:42.000
LIAM: Thank you.

02:42:42.000 --> 02:42:45.000
I'm not terribly familiar
with Whitestone,

02:42:45.000 --> 02:42:46.500
could you point us
in the right direction?

02:42:46.500 --> 02:42:48.000
MATT: "It's under the castle."

02:42:48.000 --> 02:42:49.500
LIAM: The castle.
MATT: "Yes."

02:42:49.500 --> 02:42:51.000
LIAM: Can't miss that.

02:42:51.000 --> 02:42:52.940
SAM: Yeah, we've been there before.
Yeah, let's go.

02:42:52.940 --> 02:42:54.110
LIAM: Let's go.

02:42:54.110 --> 02:42:55.320
MATT: He puts his helmet back on.

02:42:55.320 --> 02:42:57.400
"Thank you again 
for all that you do."

02:42:57.400 --> 02:43:01.000
He clicks his heels together
and continues walking through the city.

02:43:01.000 --> 02:43:03.000
LIAM: All right, yeah.

02:43:03.000 --> 02:43:05.000
SAM: I guess we'll head
down to the ziggurat.

02:43:05.000 --> 02:43:06.500
LIAM: Let's do it.

02:43:06.500 --> 02:43:08.000
MATT: Everyone else going with?

02:43:08.000 --> 02:43:10.000
TRAVIS: Fuck yeah, let's go.
ASHLEY: Yeah. Yeah.

02:43:10.000 --> 02:43:11.500
LAURA: We taking a trip?
TALIESIN: Sure.

02:43:11.500 --> 02:43:13.960
MARISHA: Oh, are we all
going down to the ziggurat?

02:43:13.960 --> 02:43:15.460
LAURA: Yeah.
TRAVIS: Nothing else to do.

02:43:15.460 --> 02:43:16.620
MARISHA: Sure.

02:43:16.620 --> 02:43:17.690
MATT: All right. You make your way

02:43:17.690 --> 02:43:20.080
down to the basement area
of Whitestone Castle,

02:43:20.080 --> 02:43:21.930
into the family catacombs,

02:43:21.930 --> 02:43:24.880
which have been cleaned up
and you can see

02:43:24.880 --> 02:43:30.000
Cassandra has put a little bit of care
into restoring it to what it was before.

02:43:30.000 --> 02:43:33.560
The tunnel that was carved in
has been given a little more support,

02:43:33.560 --> 02:43:37.000
and as you're making your way
down a familiar tunnel,

02:43:37.000 --> 02:43:42.000
the same tunnel where you had
the showdown with Orthax,

02:43:42.000 --> 02:43:44.850
you hear a few voices 
from up ahead.

02:43:44.850 --> 02:43:46.020
Two familiar voices.

02:43:46.020 --> 02:43:50.510
You hear the echo of some older,
gruff, elderly gentleman

02:43:50.510 --> 02:43:54.000
and a little more rambunctious
familiar voice.

02:43:54.000 --> 02:43:57.000
As they turn the corner,
you see them deep in conversation.

02:43:57.000 --> 02:43:59.000
It's the Realmseer himself
hunched forward

02:43:59.000 --> 02:44:04.000
with his white hair
and balding top, turns around,

02:44:04.000 --> 02:44:07.250
"And it's a great mystery to me

02:44:07.250 --> 02:44:11.940
"that they can put a--
Oh, look! They've returned.

02:44:11.940 --> 02:44:14.000
"Vox Machina themselves."

02:44:14.000 --> 02:44:19.510
Gilmore, at this point,
opens his arms, standing and healthy.

02:44:19.510 --> 02:44:21.500
"My god, I've been waiting for you."

02:44:21.500 --> 02:44:23.000
LAURA: (laughs)
ASHLEY AND MARISHA: Aww.

02:44:23.000 --> 02:44:26.000
MATT: "And all of you
so graciously clean!"

02:44:26.000 --> 02:44:27.500
LAURA: You look so healthy, Gilmore!
ASHLEY: Very healthy.

02:44:27.500 --> 02:44:29.000
MATT: "Well, I have you
to thank for that.

02:44:29.000 --> 02:44:31.000
"Still a ways to go."

02:44:31.000 --> 02:44:35.000
LIAM: But in two or three weeks,
it's not bad. You're looking well.

02:44:35.000 --> 02:44:37.000
MATT: "Well, you all have Kima
to thank for that.

02:44:37.000 --> 02:44:41.000
"She's been quite attentive
to my needs."

02:44:43.000 --> 02:44:45.000
MARISHA: How is Whitestone finding you?

02:44:45.000 --> 02:44:47.480
MATT: "Curious place, this Whitestone.

02:44:47.480 --> 02:44:50.910
"Well, the company's interesting."

02:44:50.910 --> 02:44:52.000
MARISHA: Sure.

02:44:52.000 --> 02:44:53.500
MATT: The Realmseer laughs. He's like,

02:44:53.500 --> 02:44:57.000
"(chuckles) So I've heard."

02:44:57.000 --> 02:45:00.000
"We've spent a little bit of time

02:45:00.000 --> 02:45:02.000
"looking at this strange oddity
beneath the city,

02:45:02.000 --> 02:45:05.000
"and I'm not going to lie to you,
it's really confusing.

02:45:05.000 --> 02:45:10.000
"I've a few theories on it,
as does the Arcanist,

02:45:10.000 --> 02:45:11.500
"but we're still comparing notes

02:45:11.500 --> 02:45:14.000
"and we don't want
to jump to any conclusions,

02:45:14.000 --> 02:45:18.000
"as tests have been inconclusive
and rather dangerous so far.

02:45:18.000 --> 02:45:22.000
"However, before anything else
goes underway, I believe there's

02:45:22.000 --> 02:45:26.000
"a very important bit of business
that we must attend to."

02:45:26.000 --> 02:45:28.000
SAM: Business?
What business, Gilmore?

02:45:28.000 --> 02:45:32.000
MATT: And he walks straight up to Grog
and just gives you a big hug.

02:45:32.000 --> 02:45:34.000
SAM: Aww.
LAURA: Oh?

02:45:34.000 --> 02:45:35.500
MATT: And pats you on the shoulder
and is like,

02:45:35.500 --> 02:45:37.000
"(chuckling) You big lug."

02:45:37.000 --> 02:45:39.000
TRAVIS: You... Gilmore.

02:45:39.000 --> 02:45:41.000
(laughter)

02:45:41.000 --> 02:45:43.000
MATT: Walks over to you, Pike,
and kneels down and gives you

02:45:43.000 --> 02:45:45.000
a little pinch on the cheek
and is like,

02:45:45.000 --> 02:45:47.670
"Looking as spry
and smiley as ever, I see."

02:45:47.670 --> 02:45:49.060
ASHLEY: Hello, Shaun.

02:45:49.060 --> 02:45:51.570
(more laughter)

02:45:51.570 --> 02:45:53.340
ASHLEY: I give him a kiss
on the cheek.

02:45:53.340 --> 02:45:57.030
MATT: "Ooh."
ASHLEY: (laughs) "Ooh."

02:45:57.030 --> 02:45:59.000
MATT: He turns to you.

02:45:59.000 --> 02:46:02.000
"Vex'ahlia, look at you.
I hear, if my words say correct,

02:46:02.000 --> 02:46:05.000
"that you folks are
a recent dragon-slaying bunch, hmm?"

02:46:05.000 --> 02:46:08.450
LAURA: That we are.
MATT: "(chuckles) Good to know."

02:46:08.450 --> 02:46:10.400
MATT: Skips over you.

02:46:10.400 --> 02:46:12.100
LAURA: Oh.
ASHLEY: Save the best for last.

02:46:12.100 --> 02:46:15.000
MATT: And goes to Scanlan
and goes to ruffle your hair, and goes,

02:46:15.000 --> 02:46:18.500
"And you, you,
my little bardish friend."

02:46:18.500 --> 02:46:20.000
SAM: Little?

02:46:20.000 --> 02:46:21.500
MATT: "No, you're actually
physically little."

02:46:21.500 --> 02:46:24.000
SAM: Oh, I know.
MATT: "You are a tinier person."

02:46:24.000 --> 02:46:25.500
MATT: "Embrace it!
It's what makes you different."

02:46:25.500 --> 02:46:30.000
SAM: That's true, I suppose.
I suppose. Yes, absolutely.

02:46:30.000 --> 02:46:33.000
We've been spreading the good word
about you and your works.

02:46:33.000 --> 02:46:37.000
MATT: "So I've heard
from all sorts of interesting folk.

02:46:37.000 --> 02:46:40.000
"I only hope one day
to wear clothes as fine as you."

02:46:40.000 --> 02:46:44.000
SAM: Oh! That's a nice compliment.

02:46:44.000 --> 02:46:45.500
MATT: "Percival."
TALIESIN: Good patron.

02:46:45.500 --> 02:46:47.000
MATT: "Thank you
for taking me into your home."

02:46:47.000 --> 02:46:50.000
TALIESIN: You do nothing
but brighten these halls.

02:46:50.000 --> 02:46:55.350
MATT: "I'm...
happy to keep things lit. (sighs)"

02:46:55.350 --> 02:46:58.570
At which point,
he goes to look towards you.

02:46:58.570 --> 02:47:00.500
The Realmseer's sitting there
tapping his arm; he's like,

02:47:00.500 --> 02:47:05.000
"Right, get on with it,
we've got work to be done."

02:47:05.000 --> 02:47:09.000
And, "Shh. You be quiet.
These people have saved my life.

02:47:09.000 --> 02:47:13.000
"Keyleth. Sweet Ashari princess."

02:47:13.000 --> 02:47:15.490
MARISHA: Hi, Gilmore.

02:47:15.490 --> 02:47:19.000
MATT: "You've grown.
I can see it in your eyes."

02:47:19.000 --> 02:47:21.000
He gives you a big hug.

02:47:21.000 --> 02:47:24.000
MARISHA: I give him a hug back.

02:47:24.000 --> 02:47:25.580
MATT: "Vax."

02:47:25.580 --> 02:47:27.510
LAURA: (giggles)

02:47:27.510 --> 02:47:34.000
MATT: "Vax'ildan.
Light of my eye. Smiling boy."

02:47:34.000 --> 02:47:37.000
(laughter)

