of the ziggurat beneath the city.

02:56:30.000 --> 02:56:33.000
"The ziggurat itself is built over

02:56:33.000 --> 02:56:37.000
"what appears to be
an ancient temple of Ioun.

02:56:37.000 --> 02:56:39.000
"The glass substance,

02:56:39.000 --> 02:56:43.000
"the diluted whitestone
that has been reformed into glass,

02:56:43.000 --> 02:56:47.000
"is used as a very strong arcane current.

02:56:47.000 --> 02:56:50.000
"A lot of energy was being placed
in this location,

02:56:50.000 --> 02:56:52.000
"as there is an actual,
what appears to be

02:56:52.000 --> 02:56:57.810
"an arcane leyline, a nexus point,

02:56:57.810 --> 02:57:02.000
"near and above Whitestone,
hence the Sun Tree's placement."

02:57:02.000 --> 02:57:05.000
TALIESIN: Yes, of course.

02:57:05.000 --> 02:57:08.000
MATT: "And why it flourishes
so well in this region.

02:57:08.000 --> 02:57:12.000
"But everything within
a certain vicinity of this temple,

02:57:12.000 --> 02:57:19.000
"of this dark spot, if you will,
is eaten.

02:57:19.000 --> 02:57:25.000
"Doesn't vanish, it's not cancelled,
it's taken. Devoured.

02:57:25.000 --> 02:57:30.580
"Everything placed within
that small little globule of darkness

02:57:30.580 --> 02:57:34.000
"is taken somewhere as well.

02:57:34.000 --> 02:57:36.000
"Now, at first, we thought
maybe it was just destroying,

02:57:36.000 --> 02:57:39.000
"but the arcane energy we feel,

02:57:39.000 --> 02:57:43.000
"the flow of it,
it's drawing it somewhere.

02:57:43.000 --> 02:57:47.000
"Meaning that this is not
what I had feared to be

02:57:47.000 --> 02:57:50.000
"a sphere of annihilation,
an object of complete destruction.

02:57:50.000 --> 02:57:52.490
"Instead it feels like it's a siphon.

02:57:55.000 --> 02:58:01.000
"Now, a siphon. Siphons are very old.
Siphons were used in the First War.

02:58:01.000 --> 02:58:04.000
"They were used as a means

02:58:04.000 --> 02:58:07.740
"of transferring extremely powerful...

02:58:11.430 --> 02:58:14.000
"raw magical powers.

02:58:14.000 --> 02:58:17.000
"They were placed strategically
throughout the world's crust

02:58:17.000 --> 02:58:19.600
"at these various nexus points

02:58:19.600 --> 02:58:23.000
"as a means of creating
extremely powerful relics.

02:58:23.000 --> 02:58:26.000
"The ones that you seek, the ones
that made the Vestiges themselves,

02:58:26.000 --> 02:58:31.000
"were crafted through the use
of some of these siphons,

02:58:31.000 --> 02:58:32.500
"but they have been lost and,
many thought,

02:58:32.500 --> 02:58:37.000
"destroyed for a very long time,
or at least inert.

02:58:37.000 --> 02:58:40.000
"I have reason to believe
that this may be one.

02:58:40.000 --> 02:58:41.500
"And it may be active.

02:58:41.500 --> 02:58:44.000
"As to where the other side lies,
I do not know.

02:58:44.000 --> 02:58:47.000
"Because each siphon has two points."

02:58:47.000 --> 02:58:50.000
TALIESIN: So it's fair to assume
that at the other end of this

02:58:50.000 --> 02:58:55.000
is something old, something trapped,
something hungry.

02:58:55.000 --> 02:58:56.500
MATT: "Perhaps."

02:58:56.500 --> 02:58:59.000
LAURA: Would it be in this plane
or another?

02:58:59.000 --> 02:59:00.500
MATT: "I have no idea.

02:59:00.500 --> 02:59:02.000
"Everything we've attempted
to put through it

02:59:02.000 --> 02:59:05.000
"that had any sort
of magical connection,

02:59:05.000 --> 02:59:08.000
"whether it be
through inter-planal scrying,

02:59:08.000 --> 02:59:10.000
"anything that would bring us
to the other side of this,

02:59:10.000 --> 02:59:14.000
"is crushed, consumed,
and transferred as part of it.

02:59:14.000 --> 02:59:15.500
"None of our rituals 
or enchantments

02:59:15.500 --> 02:59:19.000
"will let us see through this
spinning marble, as you call it."

02:59:19.000 --> 02:59:21.000
LAURA: You haven't
put any blood through it, though?

02:59:21.000 --> 02:59:22.500
TALIESIN: Let's not.

02:59:22.500 --> 02:59:24.000
LAURA: No, I'm hoping 
that hasn't happened.

02:59:24.000 --> 02:59:28.000
MARISHA: So nothing survives 
the transfer.

02:59:28.000 --> 02:59:33.000
It is destroyed into its...
purest components, it sounds.

02:59:33.000 --> 02:59:34.530
MATT: "Seemingly, yes."

02:59:34.530 --> 02:59:36.000
LIAM: Or is it? Don't know?

02:59:36.000 --> 02:59:40.000
Is it that you have no idea
what happened to things put through?

02:59:40.000 --> 02:59:41.500
MATT: "We're still delving into it,

02:59:41.500 --> 02:59:43.000
"and it may be a little while
before we figure this out,

02:59:43.000 --> 02:59:46.000
"but this is the best I can ascertain
with my knowledge at my disposal.

02:59:46.000 --> 02:59:51.690
"And the Realmseer and Gilmore
can back up this research.

02:59:51.690 --> 02:59:53.500
"We've all worked together
these past weeks

02:59:53.500 --> 02:59:57.000
"and we're all kind of
coming to the same conclusion."

02:59:57.000 --> 03:00:01.000
She gestures to Gilmore.
Gilmore says,

03:00:01.000 --> 03:00:04.000
"I've only been
on this case personally

03:00:04.000 --> 03:00:06.990
"for a few days

03:00:06.990 --> 03:00:12.000
"of rising health standards
in my body

03:00:12.000 --> 03:00:16.000
"and I've thrown everything
I can at it, honestly,

03:00:16.000 --> 03:00:19.000
"and it's all just come to nothing.
Gone. (pthbbt)"

03:00:19.000 --> 03:00:22.000
TALIESIN: This is disappointing.

03:00:22.000 --> 03:00:26.000
MATT: "You're telling me."
TRAVIS: What about a person?

03:00:26.000 --> 03:00:29.000
MATT: "(laughing) I'm not
sending a person through there."

03:00:29.000 --> 03:00:33.970
MARISHA: To be fair, Grog,
I might have tried that, a little.

03:00:33.970 --> 03:00:36.000
SAM: What?
TALIESIN: Yes, that's right.

03:00:36.000 --> 03:00:41.000
MARISHA: I sort of stuck my hand
in the spinning ball of death

03:00:41.000 --> 03:00:45.000
and let's just say

03:00:45.000 --> 03:00:47.000
I'm glad I'm still here
standing with you all.

03:00:47.000 --> 03:00:48.810
LAURA: Was it sucking you in?

03:00:48.810 --> 03:00:52.040
MARISHA: It did a considerable 
amount of damage to my hand

03:00:52.040 --> 03:00:56.000
and definitely felt
like it was sucking me in

03:00:56.000 --> 03:00:59.700
and I had to resist pretty hard.

03:00:59.700 --> 03:01:01.500
But it seems like anything
that goes in that sphere

03:01:01.500 --> 03:01:06.550
doesn't come out the other end intact.

03:01:06.550 --> 03:01:09.000
LAURA: Gilmore-- any of you, Allura--

03:01:09.000 --> 03:01:16.000
have you experienced
any kind of draw toward the orb?

03:01:16.000 --> 03:01:20.000
Do you feel different,
having been around it for very long?

03:01:20.000 --> 03:01:24.000
MATT: Gilmore cocks a curious eye
to the Realmseer.

03:01:24.000 --> 03:01:25.500
The Realmseer thinks
and scratches his chin,

03:01:25.500 --> 03:01:27.000
looks to Allura.

03:01:27.000 --> 03:01:30.210
Allura looks down at the table
with her arms crossed,

03:01:30.210 --> 03:01:32.000
looks to Kima.

03:01:32.000 --> 03:01:35.000
Kima's finishing her big drink.

03:01:35.000 --> 03:01:38.020
"I stay away from it.
It creeps the hell out of me."

03:01:40.000 --> 03:01:45.000
"Not to my knowledge.
Do you think we should be worried?"

03:01:45.000 --> 03:01:46.500
LAURA: Well, I don't know.

03:01:46.500 --> 03:01:51.000
I mean, it is a very strong relic
that we don't know how it works.

03:01:51.000 --> 03:01:53.000
MATT: "The difficulty
in our research

03:01:53.000 --> 03:01:56.000
"is most of our means of inspection
are, well,"

03:01:56.000 --> 03:01:59.000
LAURA: Up close and personal.
MATT: "Of arcane nature."

03:01:59.000 --> 03:02:00.500
TALIESIN: I was hoping
that perhaps we could talk

03:02:00.500 --> 03:02:04.000
about some engineering possibilities
of finding ways

03:02:04.000 --> 03:02:07.000
that science can measure what it is
where magic cannot.

03:02:07.000 --> 03:02:09.000
Something safe.

03:02:09.000 --> 03:02:11.000
SAM: (scoffs) Science, Percy?

03:02:11.000 --> 03:02:15.000
TALIESIN: In this sense, as it stands.

03:02:15.000 --> 03:02:17.000
MATT: "We're open
to all possible suggestions.

03:02:17.000 --> 03:02:20.000
"We're kind of at the end of our rope
for the time being.

03:02:20.000 --> 03:02:25.000
"We may send a few of us
across the way to, well,

03:02:25.000 --> 03:02:28.000
"a few different places
for more information.

03:02:28.000 --> 03:02:30.000
"May do a bit
of traveling ourselves, it seems."

03:02:30.000 --> 03:02:33.000
TALIESIN: I'll sketch something
with my copious free time.

03:02:33.000 --> 03:02:36.000
MATT: "Hm. Please do."

03:02:36.000 --> 03:02:39.000
SAM: No dragons
have buzzed by here in our absence?

03:02:39.000 --> 03:02:41.000
MATT: They kind of
look to themselves.

03:02:41.000 --> 03:02:43.000
"None yet,
but we've been very careful.

03:02:43.000 --> 03:02:47.000
"We're in the process of installing
some semblance of,

03:02:47.000 --> 03:02:51.000
"(sighs) for lack of a better term,
sort of a screen.

03:02:51.000 --> 03:02:56.000
"Ways to reflect
and perhaps cloud anyone

03:02:56.000 --> 03:02:59.000
"who attempts to peer too far
into the northern regions of Whitestone.

03:02:59.000 --> 03:03:00.500
"The last thing we need

03:03:00.500 --> 03:03:02.000
"is any of these dragons
finding their way up north

03:03:02.000 --> 03:03:04.000
"where you've kept all of us
and the refugees safe,

03:03:04.000 --> 03:03:08.000
"so we're trying not
to piss any of them off,

03:03:08.000 --> 03:03:11.000
"while also trying to make sure
that maybe they're

03:03:11.000 --> 03:03:13.000
"not really looking
behind this curtain of cloud."

03:03:13.000 --> 03:03:16.000
TALIESIN: Any fortifications
would be helpful.

03:03:16.000 --> 03:03:20.570
LAURA: Don't dragons sort of
see past those things?

03:03:22.000 --> 03:03:25.000
MATT: "We're doing our best
to try and meet those standards."

03:03:25.000 --> 03:03:30.000
TALIESIN: I have another request
in that direction that might help.

03:03:30.000 --> 03:03:33.000
If there was a way
to spread the word in this city

03:03:33.000 --> 03:03:38.000
and amongst those who travel,
to not speak of us.

03:03:38.000 --> 03:03:44.000
We should probably not be hailed
in this city at all.

03:03:44.000 --> 03:03:46.000
Our names should be stricken
from any record of it.

03:03:46.000 --> 03:03:48.000
MATT: Allura leans forward 
on the table.

03:03:48.000 --> 03:03:50.000
"No, I see. You're right.

03:03:50.000 --> 03:03:52.000
"There is merit in that,
though it will be difficult.

03:03:52.000 --> 03:03:53.500
"Many here look up to you.

03:03:53.500 --> 03:03:56.000
"They see you as the salvation
of this city.

03:03:56.000 --> 03:04:00.000
"But I believe we can go about
and speak with them

03:04:00.000 --> 03:04:03.840
"and help instill the idea
that it's for the better good

03:04:03.840 --> 03:04:08.000
"that you are not mentioned."

03:04:08.000 --> 03:04:10.000
TALIESIN: Best to be nameless,
at this point.

03:04:10.000 --> 03:04:13.000
MARISHA: It's for their own safety.
TALIESIN: It's for everybody's.

03:04:13.000 --> 03:04:15.000
LAURA: We-who-must-not-be-named.
SAM: The Unmentionables.

03:04:15.000 --> 03:04:17.000
TALIESIN: (cracks up)
You're a terrible person.

03:04:17.000 --> 03:04:18.500
LAURA: (gasps) I love it.

03:04:18.500 --> 03:04:21.000
MARISHA: Yeah. My choice is
The Unmentionables. I like it.

03:04:21.000 --> 03:04:24.000
MATT: Allura says,
"I did find some research

03:04:24.000 --> 03:04:27.000
"on some of these Vestiges
you are seeking."

03:04:27.000 --> 03:04:29.000
TALIESIN: Oh!
LAURA: Yes!

03:04:29.000 --> 03:04:31.000
MATT: "From what I could bring forth

03:04:31.000 --> 03:04:34.940
"from the Cobalt Reserve in Westruun,

03:04:34.940 --> 03:04:38.000
"there is an artifact
that lies in the Feywild,

03:04:38.000 --> 03:04:39.500
"swallowed by a terrible tree."

03:04:39.500 --> 03:04:42.000
LAURA: Yes, the Warden.

03:04:42.000 --> 03:04:45.000
MATT: "Is that the name of it?"
LAURA: The Wrath of the Fey Warden.

03:04:45.000 --> 03:04:46.500
MATT: "So you've found
some information yourself?"

03:04:46.500 --> 03:04:48.000
LAURA: Just the name.

03:04:48.000 --> 03:04:51.920
SAM: And that it's
in the Feywild, but nothing more.

03:04:51.920 --> 03:04:55.100
MATT: "(sighs) This tree that holds it,
it's a tree seeded by the betrayal

03:04:55.100 --> 03:04:59.000
"of an archfey whose hatred burned
into a black heart of disease.

03:04:59.000 --> 03:05:01.000
"The cleansing rivers
of the Gilded Run

03:05:01.000 --> 03:05:05.090
"prevent the spread 
of the Shademirk Bog that seeps from it."

03:05:09.000 --> 03:05:10.280
TRAVIS: Sounds nasty.

03:05:10.280 --> 03:05:12.000
MATT: "It doesn't sound very fun, no."

03:05:12.000 --> 03:05:14.000
SAM: The Shademark Balg?

03:05:14.000 --> 03:05:17.000
MATT: "The Shademirk Bog."
SAM: Ugh, it sounds awful.

03:05:17.000 --> 03:05:19.000
MATT: "It seeps from this tree.

03:05:19.000 --> 03:05:22.790
"It is held at bay
by the rivers of the Gilded Run."

03:05:24.730 --> 03:05:26.500
MARISHA: The rivers are called
the Gilded Run?

03:05:26.500 --> 03:05:28.000
MATT: "Mm-hm."

03:05:29.730 --> 03:05:32.000
SAM: Okay. Well, that helps us.
Those are clues.

03:05:32.000 --> 03:05:34.000
LAURA: Yeah, yeah, yeah.

03:05:34.000 --> 03:05:37.320
MARISHA: And the Shademirk Bog 
pours out of the tree?

03:05:37.320 --> 03:05:39.000
LAURA: Out of the cancerous tree.

03:05:39.000 --> 03:05:41.000
MARISHA: The tree is responsible
for a swampy bog.

03:05:41.000 --> 03:05:43.370
MATT: "From best I could ascertain
from my research, yes."

03:05:43.370 --> 03:05:47.000
LAURA: And Fen-wraths?
What's the name?

03:05:47.000 --> 03:05:49.610
SAM: Fenthras,
Wrath of the Fey Warden.

03:05:49.610 --> 03:05:54.000
LAURA: Fenthras is inside of the tree
that is terrible.

03:05:54.000 --> 03:05:56.000
MATT: "It is very possible."

03:05:56.000 --> 03:05:57.140
TALIESIN: Oh no.
SAM: Okay.

03:05:57.140 --> 03:05:59.000
LIAM: Do you know anything
about the Vestige itself?

03:05:59.000 --> 03:06:02.010
MATT: "I don't, unfortunately.
Most of the Cobalt Reserve was destroyed

03:06:02.010 --> 03:06:07.050
"and I was under siege at the moment
from the return of the dragons. (sighs)"

03:06:07.050 --> 03:06:10.000
LAURA: Did you happen to find
in your research what, perhaps,

03:06:10.000 --> 03:06:13.000
we might face in the Feywild?

03:06:13.000 --> 03:06:14.500
I mean, we've learned
a little bit of it,

03:06:14.500 --> 03:06:18.420
but I know
that it's going to be rather dangerous.

03:06:18.420 --> 03:06:21.680
MATT: "I've not been there myself, 
to be honest. It creeps me out."

03:06:21.680 --> 03:06:25.500
LAURA: (laughs)
TRAVIS: (laughs) No? Sorry.

03:06:25.500 --> 03:06:28.170
MATT: "I did find also
about the Spire of Conflux.

03:06:28.170 --> 03:06:31.000
"It is a staff
that can bend the elements

03:06:31.000 --> 03:06:32.500
"and was taken into The Abyss

03:06:32.500 --> 03:06:36.000
"by Joran the Sea-Speaker,
hero of the Verdant Expanse,

03:06:36.000 --> 03:06:40.000
"about four centuries back,
and was never heard from again."

03:06:40.000 --> 03:06:43.000
MARISHA: Joran the what?
MATT: "Joran the Sea-Speaker."

03:06:43.000 --> 03:06:45.000
SAM: He speaks to the sea?

03:06:45.000 --> 03:06:46.180
MATT: "Perhaps."

03:06:46.180 --> 03:06:48.420
TALIESIN: Or just the letter C.
LAURA: (laughs)

03:06:48.420 --> 03:06:51.430
SAM: Cookie Monster.
TRAVIS: Hero.

03:06:51.430 --> 03:06:54.000
MATT: "I do have some research
about the dragons, as well."

03:06:54.000 --> 03:06:56.000
LAURA: Oh.

03:06:56.000 --> 03:07:01.000
MATT: "I've done a bit
of looking into the personality types,

03:07:01.000 --> 03:07:07.000
"the habits of some of these chromatics
you may be coming up against.

03:07:07.000 --> 03:07:10.630
"The black dragon,
you seemingly already dealt with,

03:07:10.630 --> 03:07:12.770
"if word has come to me correctly."

03:07:12.770 --> 03:07:13.720
LAURA: Yes.

03:07:13.720 --> 03:07:17.000
MATT: "Which is magnificent
and well done. Very dangerous.

03:07:17.000 --> 03:07:24.000
"Let's hope they don't decide
to strike back soon."

03:07:24.000 --> 03:07:29.000
LAURA: Good thing we didn't provoke them
in the cave at all, Percival.

03:07:29.000 --> 03:07:31.000
TALIESIN: If they came there,
they would've been provoked,

03:07:31.000 --> 03:07:34.000
I figured.

03:07:34.000 --> 03:07:38.000
MATT: "I did find that
the white dragons, they're more primal.

03:07:38.000 --> 03:07:41.000
"They're overall less intelligent
than other chromatics."

03:07:41.000 --> 03:07:42.500
And some 
of this information you know.

03:07:42.500 --> 03:07:45.000
LAURA: Yeah, why am I writing this down?
I know this shit.

03:07:45.000 --> 03:07:49.000
MATT: "But what they do is they--

03:07:49.000 --> 03:07:52.000
"(sighs) well, don't let
the lack of intelligence

03:07:52.000 --> 03:07:54.000
"lull you into comfort.

03:07:54.000 --> 03:07:56.000
"They are also unpredictable and raw.

03:07:56.000 --> 03:07:57.500
"Dangerous hunters,

03:07:57.500 --> 03:08:01.000
"they stalk in ruined lands
of ice and vengeance.

03:08:01.000 --> 03:08:03.000
"Their memory is eternal.

03:08:03.000 --> 03:08:06.000
"They recall every slight defeat

03:08:06.000 --> 03:08:11.000
"and have been known to hold vendettas
for centuries and centuries.

03:08:11.000 --> 03:08:15.000
"They despise other dragons

03:08:15.000 --> 03:08:18.000
"and this loose alignment with Thordak

03:08:18.000 --> 03:08:21.000
"is stranger than the others
for the white dragon.

03:08:21.000 --> 03:08:24.400
"Though Vorugal's distance to the others
is intentional, most likely.

03:08:27.120 --> 03:08:31.000
"I mean, the entire alignment
between them is strange, anyway,

03:08:31.000 --> 03:08:33.000
"but particularly
with the white dragon.

03:08:33.000 --> 03:08:37.000
"They generally steer very clear of,
or are bent on destroying,

03:08:37.000 --> 03:08:41.000
"any other types of dragons
that may wander in their midst."

03:08:41.000 --> 03:08:42.930
LAURA: (whispering) Interesting.

03:08:42.930 --> 03:08:47.000
MATT: "Green dragons, in particular,
are manipulative.

03:08:47.000 --> 03:08:52.000
"Liars, by nature, finding pleasure
in power over others.

03:08:52.000 --> 03:08:54.000
"Through deceit and promises
of wealth and glory, they corrupt.

03:08:54.000 --> 03:08:59.000
"They play subservience
to other dragons,

03:08:59.000 --> 03:09:02.000
"then plot their demise
to claim their hoards.

03:09:02.000 --> 03:09:08.280
"They're the seedy underbelly
of the chromatic world, if you will.

03:09:08.280 --> 03:09:13.000
"They amass powerful allies,
human and beyond, to their will,

03:09:13.000 --> 03:09:17.000
"bending them and using them as tools.

03:09:17.000 --> 03:09:18.500
"Their life and their very presence

03:09:18.500 --> 03:09:21.000
"is poison to those around them,

03:09:21.000 --> 03:09:26.000
"and is the very basis 
of their danger.

03:09:26.000 --> 03:09:30.000
"They corrupt the air around them
to be venomous.

03:09:30.000 --> 03:09:34.000
"I found a bit about
this Raishan you mentioned,

03:09:34.000 --> 03:09:38.000
"and word has spoken,
though little that exists out there,

03:09:38.000 --> 03:09:43.000
"that she is also
a very practitioned

03:09:43.000 --> 03:09:48.000
"weaver of the arcane arts,
so be warned."

03:09:48.000 --> 03:09:50.000
MARISHA: So much so

03:09:50.000 --> 03:09:57.000
that she could almost pass
as a druid wielding natural magic?

03:09:57.000 --> 03:10:00.000
MATT: "I can imagine
that's quite within her grasp.

03:10:00.000 --> 03:10:04.000
"I've heard rumors of her
calling the sky down upon her enemies.

03:10:04.000 --> 03:10:06.460
"Previous individuals
that hoped to raid her space

03:10:06.460 --> 03:10:10.000
"were swallowed in quaking earth
as she laughed from above."

03:10:12.000 --> 03:10:13.500
SAM: Druid-y things.

03:10:13.500 --> 03:10:17.000
MARISHA: I want to kill her so hard.
(strained) I want her to die.

03:10:17.000 --> 03:10:18.500
TALIESIN: Do we know where these--

03:10:18.500 --> 03:10:21.000
where these dragons have been
all this time,

03:10:21.000 --> 03:10:24.000
where they were banished to?

03:10:24.000 --> 03:10:25.500
MATT: "I mean, most of these dragons

03:10:25.500 --> 03:10:27.000
"lived their lives
wherever they once were before.

03:10:27.000 --> 03:10:32.000
"Raishan used to exist
in the mountains outside of Syngorn

03:10:32.000 --> 03:10:33.500
"and actually had amassed

03:10:33.500 --> 03:10:39.000
"a sizeable horde of followers,
lizard-men. Lizardfolk, all sorts."

03:10:39.000 --> 03:10:43.000
TALIESIN: Wait, then Thordak
was banished to the Fire Plane?

03:10:43.000 --> 03:10:48.000
MATT: "Thordak we had banished, yes.
Thordak, in particular.

03:10:48.000 --> 03:10:54.000
"Now, red dragons are true tyrants,
built on impulse and rage.

03:10:54.000 --> 03:10:55.500
"Arrogant to the core,

03:10:55.500 --> 03:11:01.000
"they see themselves
as rightful rulers over all.

03:11:01.000 --> 03:11:05.000
"And Thordak, the king
of all other dragons, as well.

03:11:05.000 --> 03:11:07.000
"He is powerful enough
to amass networks

03:11:07.000 --> 03:11:09.000
"of spies and followers far beyond

03:11:09.000 --> 03:11:15.000
"just the dragons that we've battled,
I'm sure.

03:11:15.000 --> 03:11:16.500
"So the more time that passes,

03:11:16.500 --> 03:11:19.000
"the more powerful
that network will become."

03:11:19.000 --> 03:11:20.500
LAURA: (muffled) Oh, fuck.

03:11:20.500 --> 03:11:22.000
TALIESIN: I've had a terrible thought,

03:11:22.000 --> 03:11:25.520
and it is sort of my business
to have terrible thoughts.

03:11:25.520 --> 03:11:29.000
What else has been banished
to the Fire Plane?

03:11:29.000 --> 03:11:31.000
TRAVIS: The djinn?

03:11:31.000 --> 03:11:32.500
TALIESIN: Well, I say this

03:11:32.500 --> 03:11:36.000
because if I were to slowly
open the portal to the Fire Plane

03:11:36.000 --> 03:11:39.000
and power it and make it bigger
and bigger and bigger,

03:11:39.000 --> 03:11:42.000
eventually it would be
a hole into that dimension

03:11:42.000 --> 03:11:44.000
that's big enough
for a dragon to fit through,

03:11:44.000 --> 03:11:47.000
but still not big enough for me,

03:11:47.000 --> 03:11:49.830
so I need to keep eating,
to make it bigger.

03:11:49.830 --> 03:11:52.220
LAURA: (gasps)

03:11:52.220 --> 03:11:56.000
TALIESIN: And maybe they might
be looking for what's down there

03:11:56.000 --> 03:12:00.000
