LAURA: Ohhh.
LIAM: Sorry, buddy, it's a 31.

03:36:22.600 --> 03:36:25.000
MATT: As you approach the door,
you look down

03:36:25.000 --> 03:36:28.000
and see a smear of dark,
reflective oil

03:36:28.000 --> 03:36:33.000
across the walkway about two feet 
leading up to your room.

03:36:33.000 --> 03:36:36.000
You guys have a cluster of rooms
in this long hallway,

03:36:36.000 --> 03:36:38.000
and it arcs around like an L.

03:36:38.000 --> 03:36:39.500
So you guys are in this big L

03:36:39.500 --> 03:36:42.000
of all your rooms scattered throughout.

03:36:42.000 --> 03:36:44.000
LIAM: How thick is it? Is it viscous?

03:36:44.000 --> 03:36:48.000
MATT: Yeah, it's pretty slippery.
LIAM: Put my hand in it. Does that stay?

03:36:48.000 --> 03:36:51.000
MATT: The hand stays for a minute, then--
LIAM: Goes away.

03:36:51.000 --> 03:36:53.710
MATT: Yeah, it's pretty thick.
LIAM: All right.

03:36:56.000 --> 03:36:59.000
MATT: Also has a fume to it.

03:36:59.000 --> 03:37:00.000
LIAM: Okay.

03:37:00.000 --> 03:37:02.000
I'm going to scrape
a bunch of it up just into my hand,

03:37:02.000 --> 03:37:05.000
so I have a big handful of it,

03:37:05.000 --> 03:37:08.000
and I'm just going
to go to Grog's room,

03:37:08.000 --> 03:37:11.000
and I'm going to slowly,
just at the door, take time to write,

03:37:11.000 --> 03:37:16.000
Grog smells

03:37:16.000 --> 03:37:22.200
like farts and--

03:37:22.200 --> 03:37:25.000
LAURA: I walk by him
as he's doing this and say,

03:37:25.000 --> 03:37:27.000
You know he can't read, right?

03:37:27.000 --> 03:37:29.000
MARISHA: (laughs)

03:37:29.000 --> 03:37:31.000
LIAM: I picked specifically small words!

03:37:31.000 --> 03:37:33.000
(laughter)

03:37:33.000 --> 03:37:34.500
LIAM: Poo.

03:37:34.500 --> 03:37:36.000
TALIESIN: Oh, he can read that.

03:37:36.000 --> 03:37:37.000
LIAM: And I draw--

03:37:37.000 --> 03:37:41.980
No. I'll tell you what I do.
Pull down my breeches

03:37:41.980 --> 03:37:44.500
and I put the oil on my butt
and I go (squelch).

03:37:44.500 --> 03:37:46.000
(laughter)

03:37:46.000 --> 03:37:48.000
LIAM: A little signature.

03:37:48.000 --> 03:37:51.050
MATT: All right. Well done.

03:37:53.000 --> 03:37:55.000
TALIESIN: Preschoolers run amok
in my gentle abode.

03:37:55.000 --> 03:37:59.000
LIAM: Get busy living
or get busy dying. Butt-print.

03:37:59.000 --> 03:38:00.490
MATT: All right.
You guys all get into bed.

03:38:00.490 --> 03:38:02.060
Anything else you want to get done?

03:38:02.060 --> 03:38:04.600
SAM: I just told Pike
she looked real pretty tonight

03:38:04.600 --> 03:38:06.950
and I go back to my reading.

03:38:06.950 --> 03:38:08.000
MATT: Okay.

03:38:08.000 --> 03:38:12.000
You guys all find yourselves
back to your respective rooms,

03:38:12.000 --> 03:38:13.500
resting for the night.

03:38:13.500 --> 03:38:17.180
Some doors
adorned differently than others.

03:38:20.000 --> 03:38:22.000
Partway into the evening's resting,

03:38:22.000 --> 03:38:27.000
we'll say the wee hours of the morning,
post-midnight or so,

03:38:27.000 --> 03:38:31.570
your door opens slightly, Vax.

03:38:34.000 --> 03:38:38.450
You hear a little
(knocking sound) on your door.

03:38:39.440 --> 03:38:41.100
LIAM: Yes?

03:38:41.100 --> 03:38:45.440
MATT: You look over and you see Gilmore
pop his head in with a soft smile.

03:38:46.910 --> 03:38:51.600
"I'm sorry if I'm waking you up."

03:38:52.880 --> 03:38:54.210
LIAM: It's all right.

03:38:54.210 --> 03:38:55.460
MATT: "Here."

03:38:55.460 --> 03:38:58.600
And he produces what looks like
a folded pile of material

03:38:58.600 --> 03:39:01.330
and throws it
on the foot of your bed and goes,

03:39:01.330 --> 03:39:04.590
"Come, Vax, I made you a gift.

03:39:04.590 --> 03:39:08.030
"Put it on, come walk with me awhile.
We have a lot to talk about."

03:39:08.030 --> 03:39:10.000
LIAM: I open it up.

03:39:10.000 --> 03:39:15.000
MATT: It's a very well-crafted silk robe
of dark blue and black.

03:39:15.000 --> 03:39:17.890
Beaded, nice against the skin.
It's really, really nice.

03:39:17.890 --> 03:39:19.420
LIAM: (quietly) Give me a minute.

03:39:19.420 --> 03:39:21.500
(louder) There's a wooden screen
in the room.

03:39:21.500 --> 03:39:25.160
I go behind it
and wipe any oil left off my butt.

03:39:25.160 --> 03:39:27.640
(laughter)

03:39:27.640 --> 03:39:29.590
MATT: That's fantastic.

03:39:29.590 --> 03:39:33.380
LIAM: Everything looks all right.
And I put it on.

03:39:33.380 --> 03:39:37.030
MATT: All right. 
He waits for you patiently in the hallway.

03:39:39.036 --> 03:39:45.013
So he begins walking along.
Puts his arm out to you.

03:39:45.013 --> 03:39:46.220
LIAM: Take it.

03:39:46.220 --> 03:39:49.500
MATT: You take his arm.
You guys walk up along the hallway.

03:39:49.500 --> 03:39:53.350
He leads you to a staircase
that leads up further, and he goes,

03:39:56.700 --> 03:39:59.500
"I know a lot has happened
these recent months.

03:39:59.500 --> 03:40:01.680
"I've been watching from afar,

03:40:01.680 --> 03:40:06.000
"keeping tabs on your journey
best that I can.

03:40:06.000 --> 03:40:09.000
"But I still know so little."

03:40:09.000 --> 03:40:11.000
You ascend the lengthy staircase

03:40:11.000 --> 03:40:13.000
and you make your way
to the higher floor.

03:40:13.000 --> 03:40:15.000
You eventually open
an intricate door

03:40:15.000 --> 03:40:18.450
and walk out
onto a wide balcony on that tower

03:40:18.450 --> 03:40:22.000
that overlooks the grounds
and the castle before you.

03:40:22.000 --> 03:40:26.000
Beautiful moonlight, the night air.

03:40:26.000 --> 03:40:29.000
You see the moon is nearly full
and the white light illuminates

03:40:29.000 --> 03:40:33.000
the densely-forested countryside
surrounding the castle.

03:40:33.000 --> 03:40:34.500
He closes the door

03:40:34.500 --> 03:40:38.000
and walks up to you
at the edge of the balcony,

03:40:38.000 --> 03:40:41.140
looking over it all,
elbows on the edge.

03:40:43.820 --> 03:40:47.000
"Some time has passed, Vax.

03:40:47.000 --> 03:40:50.630
"And much of the world
moves on to newer, greater threats.

03:40:52.670 --> 03:40:55.430
"But true pain never really heals."

03:40:59.320 --> 03:41:02.020
He turns to you

03:41:02.020 --> 03:41:08.000
and steps up to you,
looking you close in the face.

03:41:08.000 --> 03:41:14.000
"You hurt me deeply.
And continue to hurt.

03:41:14.000 --> 03:41:20.350
"Agony, for weeks, months.

03:41:20.350 --> 03:41:24.260
"Pain I had never experienced.

03:41:24.260 --> 03:41:26.390
"(deepening to a growl)
It's all I can think about."

03:41:26.390 --> 03:41:28.000
LIAM: Can I make an insight check?

03:41:28.000 --> 03:41:31.000
MATT: You would, if you had time.

03:41:31.000 --> 03:41:34.690
MARISHA: Oh my god!
LAURA: (gasps) I knew it. I knew it.

03:41:34.690 --> 03:41:36.160
MARISHA: No!

03:41:38.710 --> 03:41:41.700
MATT: The pain hits you suddenly,
before anything else does,

03:41:41.700 --> 03:41:44.540
as you're lost in that face
and the sudden feeling,

03:41:44.540 --> 03:41:48.080
the sensation 
of terror and horror.

03:41:51.000 --> 03:41:56.050
You suffer 18 points

03:41:56.880 --> 03:41:58.930
of piercing damage,

03:42:01.000 --> 03:42:04.000
and I need you to make
a constitution saving throw.

03:42:04.000 --> 03:42:06.610
LIAM: Oh, that's my specialty.

03:42:08.650 --> 03:42:11.000
TALIESIN: (whispering) We don't know
what the hell this is.

03:42:11.000 --> 03:42:13.840
LIAM: Constitution save?
MATT: Mm-hmm.

03:42:13.840 --> 03:42:16.070
LIAM: 11.

03:42:16.070 --> 03:42:18.000
MATT: You feel the poison--

03:42:18.000 --> 03:42:20.640
LIAM: I'll use luck.
MATT: Roll again.

03:42:23.000 --> 03:42:24.500
LIAM: 18.

03:42:24.500 --> 03:42:28.000
MATT: You feel what should be
a pulse of poison hit your system

03:42:28.000 --> 03:42:31.340
and you manage to fight it off
as suddenly you look down

03:42:31.340 --> 03:42:36.000
and there is Gilmore
holding a blade thrust into your stomach,

03:42:36.000 --> 03:42:41.000
your robes now beginning to fill
with crimson red around the wound.

03:42:41.000 --> 03:42:46.890
It's at that moment you see him
pull you in and stare into your face

03:42:46.890 --> 03:42:49.350
with a very low growl,

03:42:49.350 --> 03:42:53.000
"It's all I think about."

03:42:53.000 --> 03:42:55.000
And you watch
as a flicker to his form happens

03:42:55.000 --> 03:42:58.000
and you see for a second
there's a flash: not skin, but fur.

03:42:58.000 --> 03:43:00.000
You see teeth, you see whiskers,

03:43:00.000 --> 03:43:03.410
and the hand holding the dagger
is facing the other direction.

03:43:05.000 --> 03:43:06.500
That's where
we're going to end tonight's session.

03:43:06.500 --> 03:43:08.500
(shocked exclamations)

03:43:08.500 --> 03:43:11.000
MARISHA: Nooo!

03:43:11.000 --> 03:43:13.000
LAURA: The rakshasa?
MARISHA: Is it a rakshasa?

03:43:13.000 --> 03:43:16.000
MATT: (laughs)
LAURA: Oh my god.

03:43:16.000 --> 03:43:18.000
TRAVIS: Ohhhh.

03:43:18.000 --> 03:43:21.000
MATT: We'll be back next week.

03:43:21.000 --> 03:43:22.500
LIAM: That fucked 
with my head, Matt.

